{"id": "14125", "revid": "248911", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14125", "title": "Shakti Figurine", "text": "Shakti Figurine is an item which can be used to transform the user into a blue armored warrior wielding an +4 short sword for four rounds (24 seconds) with an armor class of -5 and hastens the user. This item is obtained by killing &lt;a href=\"Kiser%20Jhaeri\"&gt;Kiser Jhaeri&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Betrayal%20at%20the%20Gates\"&gt;Betrayal at the Gates&lt;/a&gt; quest in .\nShakti Short Sword +4.\nWhile classified as a short sword +4, with 4 enchantment level, it has a THAC0 bonus of a short sword +2. The item also has worn haste and a proficiency modifier for short swords, increasing it to specialized level. It should be noted that the weapon still has a strength requirement of 5."}
