{"id": "30388", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30388", "title": "Shapeshift", "text": "Unkitted &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Avenger\"&gt;Avenger&lt;/a&gt;s gain the ability to Shapeshift into various animals at level 7. &lt;a href=\"Totemic%20Druid\"&gt;Totemic Druid&lt;/a&gt;s cannot shapeshift, and &lt;a href=\"Shapeshifter\"&gt;Shapeshifter&lt;/a&gt;s have a unique ability instead ().\nThere are three default forms that the druid may each use once per day, and an extra three abilities that only the &lt;a href=\"Avenger\"&gt;Avenger&lt;/a&gt; receives.\nMany of the shapeshifting descriptions (only added in the Enhanced Editions) are incorrect; this page will only list the correct traits.\nIf a Druid dual-classes into Fighter, he loses his shapeshift abilities until he can reactivate his druid levels.\nEffects.\nAll forms have the following characteristics:\nStandard Druid Forms.\nThese forms are accessible by both the unkitted druid and the Avenger.\u00a0 All values were obtained from the Enhanced Editions. \nThe bear forms have\u00a0extremely high APR for when shapeshifting is unlocked, making them good melee fighters.\u00a0 However, their high AC and low enchantment level makes them unable to scale into higher levels effectively. The Black Bear form is exactly the same as the Brown Bear form, except it has worse AC.\nThe wolf form is defensively stronger and has the best damage dice, but its low APR makes it ineffective as a damage dealer.\n All three forms allow offhand weapons and shields to be used as normal. They all benefit from Sword and Shield Style while using shields and Single Weapon Style otherwise (even while equipped with an offhand weapon). In all forms, reequipping armor only provides bonuses (eg AC modifiers against damage types or Fire Resistance), it doesn't alter the character's Base AC.\nShields may be used as normal (if equipped before transforming), but offhand weapons cannot attack, they only provide bonuses (eg +1 APR from Belm or +50% Fire Resistance from Icingdeath) and charge abilities (eg 1x/day Summon Spectral Blade from the Spectral Brand). All forms benefit from Sword and Shield style while equipped with a shield, Single Weapon Style while the offhand is empty and no weapon style while the offhand has a weapon. In all forms, reequipping armor provides full benefits, including altering the character's Base AC (if better).\n1 - This is applied to the base movement speed of a normal brown/black bear. These forms actually move ~15% slower than normal speed.\n2 - This form moves ~25% faster than normal speed.\nAvenger Forms.\nThese forms are accessible by the Avenger only.\u00a0\u00a0All values were obtained from the Enhanced Editions.\nThe baby wyvern and sword spider forms have great synergy with &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, which the Avenger has access to as part of its kit bonuses.\u00a0 The Avenger can render groups of enemies helpless, then transform and pick off enemies.\nThe baby wyvern's poison is highly effective, dealing a total of 100 damage (even more, if the enemy is under a &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;) and interrupting almost all spellcasting.\u00a0 Its high save penalty and the wyvern's higher APR make it very reliable as well.\nThe fire salamander can easily reach over 100% fire resistance using spells such as &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Fire%20and%20Cold\"&gt;Resist Fire and Cold&lt;/a&gt; or equipment such as &lt;a href=\"Batalista%27s%20Passport\"&gt;Batalista's Passport&lt;/a&gt;, making it effective against\u00a0fire using enemies.\u00a0 It also has the highest enchantment level of any shapeshifting form, but has low APR. But its Breathe Fireball ability allows one to easily damage Mages, as it's considered a nonmagical ability and, therefore, ignores all spell protections (and even Fire Resistance won't prevent stagger, meaning the ability can still disrupt spellcasting while doing 0 damage). One is also able to renew the 3x Breathe Fireball casts once by using the Salamander shapeshift ability again (while already being in Salamander form), meaning one Avenger can use it a total of six times in a single encounter.\n The Baby Wyvern and Sword Spider forms allow offhand weapons and shields to be used as normal, while the Fire Salamander form does not, it can only use charge abilities from offhand shields or weapons. The Baby Wyvern and Sword Spider forms benefit from Sword and Shield Style while using shields and Single Weapon Style otherwise (even while equipped with an offhand weapon), while the Fire Salamander form benefits from the Two-Handed Weapon Style. In all forms, reequipping armor only provides bonuses (eg AC modifiers against damage types or Fire Resistance), it doesn't alter the character's Base AC.\nIn Baby Wyvern and Sword Spider forms, shields may be used as normal (if equipped before transforming), but offhand weapons cannot attack, they only provide bonuses (eg +1 APR from Belm or +50% Fire Resistance from Icingdeath) and charge abilities (eg 1x/day Summon Spectral Blade from the Spectral Brand), while in Fire Salamander form, shields and offhand weapons only provide charge abilities, if any. The Baby Wyvern and Sword Spider forms benefit from Sword and Shield style while equipped with a shield, Single Weapon Style while the offhand is empty and no weapon style while the offhand has a weapon, while the Fire Salamander form benefits from Two-Handed Weapon Style. In all forms, reequipping armor provides full benefits, including altering the character's Base AC (if better).\n3 - The fire salamander's weapon is a &lt;a href=\"Spear%20%2B1\"&gt;Spear +1&lt;/a&gt; and the caster gains the benefits of &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;Two-Handed Weapon Style&lt;/a&gt; if the caster has placed points into it.\n4 - In , movement speed is increased to 11 \u2014 by default, a humanoid character moves at 9. In the original edition of , the Salamander Form has a permanent &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Weak Haste effect&lt;/a&gt; and moves at speed 14 in addition to other Haste bonuses.\n5 - With the innate Haste effect, this is actually 5 APR."}
{"id": "9343", "revid": "268658", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9343", "title": "Shapeshifter", "text": "Shapeshifter is one of the three class kits for &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s. These druids have freely accepted to be infected with lycanthropy and as a result, they can turn into werewolves right from the start, instead of earning their transforming abilities at level 7. This shapeshifting ability is much stronger than the other ones and takes a lot effort to have control of this form, that they sacrifice the other shapeshifting abilities. At level 13, they may turn into a greater werewolf once per day. The second penalty is that a shapeshifter can't wear any body armor.\nAbility Scores.\nNote: For the information of this table the human race was used, because they have no character bonunes/penalties related to race and therefore act like a 'neutral'. For other races this may be slightly different. See &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; for more information.\nDruid abilities.\nImmunity to poison.\nAt lvl 15, druids become immune to poison.\nResistance.\nDruids gain 10% resistance to fire, cold, electricity and acid when they reach lvl 18. At lvl 21 and 24, they gain an additional bonus of 10%.\nPriest spells.\nFor the complete list of spells, see &lt;a href=\"Spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Spells (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt;. For the complete list of spell that can be used by clerics, druids and rangers, see &lt;a href=\"Priest%20spells%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Priest spells (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt;. Here are all spells that can be used by druids and their class kits.\nShapeshift: Werewolf.\nShapeshifters gain the ability Shapeshift: Werewolf once per day starting at level 1, and acquire additional uses every two levels thereafter (levels 3, 5, 7, etc.) until level 11, capping out at 6 uses per day. They lose access to the normal Shapeshift forms. At level 13, they gain the ability Shapeshift: Greater Werewolf once per day, and acquire additional uses every two levels thereafter (levels 15, 17, 18, etc.).\nA Shapeshifter who dual-classes into Fighter loses his shapeshifting abilities until he can re-activate his Druid levels.\nHigh-level class abilities.\nDruids receive quest level priest spells which are added to the level 7 spellbook. The spells can only be selected once. To druids, these abilities become available when they reach lvl 15.\nSpell progression.\nNotes: Priests gain additional spell slots for their &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt;.\n+Usable by priest whose &lt;a href=\"wisdom\"&gt;wisdom&lt;/a&gt; is 17 or higher.\nUsable by priest whose wisdom is 18 or highe.\nNote that the wisdom requirement is gone since , any priest whose wisdom is lower than 16 may learn lvl 6 and 7 spells, including "}
