{"id": "8837", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8837", "title": "Shareen Ophal", "text": "Lady Shareen Ophal and her husband, &lt;a href=\"Dermod%20Ophal\"&gt;Lord Dermod&lt;/a&gt;, are aristocrats who can be found sitting atop a platform in the southern part of &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nInteractions.\nIf spoken to, Lady Ophal will be dismissive and refuse to engage in dialogue. However, when speaking to Lord Opal, he will initiate a conversation seconds before realizing that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party are lacking 'social status,' at which point he will question (while whispering) his wife on whether to keep talking to them or not. The two will then try to guess the party's place of origin. After a short discussion on the party, the Lord will proclaim that the conversation is over, as Gorion's Ward is lacking in social status."}
