{"id": "5472", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5472", "title": "Shield of the Archons", "text": "Shield of the Archons is a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;spell protection&lt;/a&gt; that causes single-target spells cast against the priest to be deflected, nullified.\nGameplay.\nShield of the Archons relies on the same mechanics as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;. As such, it:\nLike most spell protections, Shield of the Archons cannot be &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;dispelled&lt;/a&gt;. It is also one of the only ways a Cleric can protect themselves from &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes Shield of the Archons to block the &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; Spell.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its effects, casting time, duration, and description. See below:\nShield of the Archons\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Protection\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nThis powerful abjuration spell causes spells cast against the priest to be absorbed and consumed. This spell will not protect the caster from dispel magic, but it will not be affected by dispel magic, either.\nThis spell also grants protection from spells cast from scrolls and innate spell-like abilities but will not protect against area effect spells that are not centered directly upon the priest (such as Fireball), or stationary area effect spells (such as Cloudkill and Stinking Cloud)."}
