{"id": "6928", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6928", "title": "Shipwreck's Coast", "text": "The Area West of High Hedge is also known as Shipwreck's Coast. It is a peninsula connecting only to &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge\"&gt;High Hedge&lt;/a&gt;.\nPlot.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Surgeon\"&gt;The Surgeon&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is the brother of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Davaeorn\"&gt;Davaeorn&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and mentions him in his dialogue.\nCharacters.\nShoal and Droth.\nUsing a character other than your main, talk to &lt;a href=\"Shoal%20the%20Nereid\"&gt;Shoal the Nereid&lt;/a&gt; (3043,436), who will ask for help. She will then kiss that party member. The kiss is an attack that will either kill or bring the recipient down to 1 hit point, unless they successfully save vs. breath, which will turn Shoal to enemy status. After taking some damage, Shoal will break in and say that she doesn't want to die for \"the master\". If you offer to help her, she will restore your dead party member and you must battle &lt;a href=\"Droth\"&gt;Droth&lt;/a&gt; - an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt;. Kill him and talk to Shoal afterwards for 750 xp. If you act quickly, you may still be able to kill Shoal for 5,000 xp with no loss to &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;. Killing her for the 5,000 xp without talking to her to get 750 xp more is much easier though.\nMad Arcand.\nTalk to &lt;a href=\"Mad%20Arcand\"&gt;Mad Arcand&lt;/a&gt; (2005, 1263). If your NPC Reaction is 15-20 he asks you to collect &lt;a href=\"Discipliner\"&gt;a ring&lt;/a&gt; from the wrecked ship SW from his position. Agree. Collect the ring and return it to him. Even if your Reaction is too low for him to ask for your help you can still bring the ring to him. It's cursed so don't wear it or keep it.\nThe Surgeon.\nAsk &lt;a href=\"the%20Surgeon\"&gt;the Surgeon&lt;/a&gt; (2888, 2079) who he is and he will give you a potion and start healing injured party members. He can be pickpocketed, but if pickpocketing fails he will become hostile and attack the party with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; spells. If you kill him after he goes hostile, you receive 975XP for no reputation loss, and he drops the items which could be pickpocketed from him.\nMod content.\nIn the mod (EET) this area is named Rocky Coast."}
{"id": "12698", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12698", "title": "Shistal", "text": "Shistal was a former monk of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; who was killed at some point by one of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;'s lackeys so a &lt;a href=\"Doppelganger\"&gt;Doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; could take his form and infiltrate Candlekeep.\nBefore you see Shistal, &lt;a href=\"Bendalis\"&gt;Bendalis&lt;/a&gt; will warn you that Shistal has not been acting like his usual self. When you speak with him he will act as if he never knew you. If you keep confronting him about his lack of knowledge about his past life or how he knows that you have been to &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood\"&gt;Cloakwood&lt;/a&gt;, he will turn into a &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Doppelganger\"&gt;Greater Doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; and attack.\nYou must wait until his transformation is complete to attack him. If you do not, any monk in the vicinity will attack you as well and accidentally killing one will result in 10 &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss."}
{"id": "42543", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42543", "title": "Shlimes and Oozshes", "text": "Schlimes and Oozshes is a side quest that takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Splurging%20Sturgeon\"&gt;Splurging Sturgeon&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nEnter the Splurging Sturgeon and locate &lt;a href=\"Lusselyn\"&gt;Lusselyn&lt;/a&gt;, the drunkard. After exhausting his dialogue 3 times, he will make a bet that your team can't kill the \"schlimes and oozshes\" located within the tavern. Talking like a drunkard back will activate the quest, while speaking clearly and insulting him will refuse.\nWalk-through.\nThere's really no in-depth\u00a0walk-through needed for this one. Just head up to the second floor, and up in the Northwestern corner room you'll find a lonely Mustard Jelly.\u00a0Once the Mustard Jelly is destroyed, you can return to the first floor and talk to Lusselyn again to close the quest for 100 gold.\u00a0No experience for closing the quest, just the gold, but the jelly itself is worth 2,000 experience\u00a0so for how short it is, it's not a terrible quest to donate 2 minutes to.\nIf you're not up to it you can also pay \"him\" for protection:"}
{"id": "7601", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7601", "title": "Shoal the Nereid", "text": "Shoal the Nereid is a slave of the &lt;a href=\"ogre%20mage\"&gt;ogre mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Droth\"&gt;Droth&lt;/a&gt;, in the &lt;a href=\"Shipwreck%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Shipwreck's Coast&lt;/a&gt; area west of &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge\"&gt;High Hedge&lt;/a&gt;. When talked to for the first time, she will kiss the character she is talking to, no matter their decision.\nAt this point, Shoal will become hostile and attack the party, but will surrender*, and will revive the slain party member with 1\u00a0hp if her plea for help is considered, after which the party will be confronted by Droth (with little chance to re-equip and heal, so it is best to have her kill and revive a ranged fighter, or the party member that you can best leave standing idly by). Alternatively, the party can choose to kill Shoal without reputation loss. \nCompleting Shoal's mini-quest awards 750 &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;. Killing her instead awards 5000 XP without incurring reputation loss.\nIf Shoal is attacked quickly enough after completing her mini-quest, then she can be slain for the additional 5000 XP without incurring reputation loss.\nDialog.\nFirst Encounter.\n\"Please to help me, will you? I am alone on this desolate dry-land and who knows what lurks in these woods.\"\nSo, whichever response you choose, it leads to a deadly kiss from the Nereid, which you can accept or attempt to decline:\nShe then turns hostile, but take care not to kill her too fast, or she won't be able to resurrect your teammate, nor will her master Droth appear.\nAfter Fighting.\n\"No! This is no longer fun! I cannot die for this! They are my actions, but not my intent! I can but do as I am bid by the master!\"\nTake care not to kill Shoal when she attacks, or she won't be able to raise your teammate, nor will her master Droth appear. Use your weakest combatant to attack with and she'll throw in the towel soon enough.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Droth\"&gt;Droth&lt;/a&gt; is teleporting in\nYou can kill her for the 5000 XP and &lt;a href=\"Droth\"&gt;Droth&lt;/a&gt; will complain saying \" Die, manlings! You killed my favorite toy!\"\nIf you're quick and evil you can kill her after the encounter for the 750 XP for the quest, and 5000 XP and her pearl for her death, with no repercussions."}
{"id": "4997", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4997", "title": "Shocking Grasp", "text": "Shocking Grasp allows the wizard to deliver physical and electrical damage by grasping/punching/touching a creature.\nGameplay.\nThe caster applies this spell to themself only.\nUpon completion of the spell a 3D graphic effect renders upon the caster's sprite, and a sound effect is audibled.\nThe spell creates an item that supplants the caster's main-hand weapon, replacing it with an item, which is SGRASP01.itm - SGRASP20.itm, depending on the caster's mage level.\nThe weapon has a range of 1-foot and has an assigned +6 &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; value for the purposes of what the weapon can hit.\nThe mage may attack in melee combat with this weapon but must roll to hit with it. The Enhanced Edition confers a hidden 4-point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to touch attack spell weapons.\nShould the caster successfully hit the target, then the victim suffers 1d2 &lt;a href=\"Stunning%20damage\"&gt;nonlethal damage&lt;/a&gt; (modified to hit and damage by the &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute), and variable &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electricity damage&lt;/a&gt; based on the caster's mage experience level.\nThe caster gets one shot at attacking the target, and if the attack roll is missed or if the attack successfully strikes, the magically created weapon then disappears afterwards.\nThe shocking grasp's electricity damage bypasses &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; - yet can be absorbed by any &lt;a href=\"Spell%20protections%20type\"&gt;Spell protections type&lt;/a&gt; defense such as a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, and the damage can be bounced back at the attacker with a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; will negate the electricity.\nWhen the spell expires, the shocking grasp weapon disappears, and a sound effect audibles as a reminder.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Shocking Grasp\" won't disappear until the caster discharges the electrical jolt by successfully touching a target, or the spell expires - it won't disappear if the caster misses the target. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, changing its effects, and school. See below for description:\nShocking Grasp\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Special\nWhen the wizard touches a creature while this spell is in effect, an electrical charge will deal 1d6 points of damage and stun the target for 1 round. If the target makes a successful saving throw vs. spell, he is not stunned. For every two extra experience levels of the caster, the creature will suffer an additional 1d6 points of damage and roll their saving throw at an increased -1 penalty (to a maximum of 5d6 damage and a -4 saving throw penalty at 9th level). The spell expires once the caster makes a successful melee attack or after 1 turn has passed. The wizard gains a +4 bonus to hit the target."}
