{"id": "36828", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36828", "title": "Shop (southeast Baldur's Gate)", "text": "Being one of two &lt;a href=\"General%20Store\"&gt;General Store&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;southeast&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;the Gate&lt;/a&gt;, both open around the clock, this one to the north and next to &lt;a href=\"Nemphre%27s%20Home\"&gt;Nemphre's Home&lt;/a&gt; is marked as Shop on the \"\" map and sells standard &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, while it's &lt;a href=\"%23shared\"&gt;more of&lt;/a&gt; a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop%23Buy%20and%20Sell\"&gt;potion shop&lt;/a&gt; in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBackground.\nThe small &lt;a href=\"General%20Store\"&gt;General Store&lt;/a&gt; is visited frequently by &lt;a href=\"commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt;s from the early dawn into late dusk, with good chances to hear some &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;rumors&lt;/a&gt; between eight in the morning and seven in the evening. When all have left, the &lt;a href=\"Storekeep%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;storekeep&lt;/a&gt; still has an eye on his unlocked shelves that are full of wares, though taking the &lt;a href=\"bullet\"&gt;bullet&lt;/a&gt;s and the &lt;a href=\"dart\"&gt;dart&lt;/a&gt;s from the bag in the side room might go unnoticed. If not done by somebody &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;invisible&lt;/a&gt; or by a &lt;a href=\"shadowdancer\"&gt;shadowdancer&lt;/a&gt; using their &lt;a href=\"Shadowstep\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt;, even taking a look at the other &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s \u2013 including &lt;a href=\"potions\"&gt;potions&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fire%20Breath\"&gt;fire breath&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 or the &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; provokes the storekeep to call the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;authorities&lt;/a&gt; to arrest the alleged &lt;a href=\"Party\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe Shop is a single-floor building with a separate ancillary room, like several other &lt;a href=\"stores\"&gt;stores&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;. Besides some shelves, many empty crates and barrels are lined up along the walls or placed in the corners. The &lt;a href=\"Storekeep%20%28southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;storekeep&lt;/a&gt; stays behind his counter, opposite a single door that opens to the north of &lt;a href=\"southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, while the customers are roaming.\nInvolvement.\nThe Shop offers a wide range of standard &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 with nothing specific of note, however. Accessories and jewelry can be sold, as well, with both purchase and disposal for average rates; see &lt;a href=\"%23STO1320\"&gt;below&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed list of what can be divested at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of only five percent.\nAll &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt;s can be &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;identified&lt;/a&gt; for the usual rate of one hundred\u202f&lt;a href=\"gp\"&gt;gp&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Rogues\"&gt;Rogues&lt;/a&gt; can try to steal from the shop, with a &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;skill&lt;/a&gt; of ten usually being sufficient; if that fails, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcer&lt;/a&gt; with two &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMEN2\"&gt;comrades&lt;/a&gt; will try to arrest the thief and the other members of the party.\nBuy and Sell.\n&lt;onlyinclude&gt;\n&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;"}
{"id": "5650", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5650", "title": "Shop of Silence", "text": "The Shop of Silence is a , run by &lt;a href=\"Silence%20%28NPC%29\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; in the city of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". The store is found in the district of &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; at the eastern wall, just south of the &lt;a href=\"Generic%20Tavern%20and%20Inn%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Tavern and Inn&lt;/a&gt; near the front gate.\nSilence sells equipment mainly intended for &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;thieves&lt;/a&gt;, but most of the items can be used by other &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; as well. In the \"\", Silence is a fence and will buy stolen goods. In the \"Sanctuary\", as the shop is called, Silence also offers rooms for resting but only the peasant type.\nAccess.\nWhether or not &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is welcomed here strongly depends on the &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; from Silence.\nOnly a party Silence reacts friendly too (reaction &gt;14) has full access to the store without further restrictions.\nIf the party is seen as hostile by Silence (reaction &lt;8), she will demand that they leave and eventually will turn hostile and attack if you continue proddin' her.\nAll parties that are reacted to neutrally (reaction between 9 &amp; 13) have to pledge to get access to Silence's wares and room.\nThis is a one time check, and the outcome determines Silence's future reactions. The neutral seen party always has to pay the , while with the friendly reaction they are welcome every time.\nLoot.\nItems that are found on the shelves of the store:&lt;br&gt;\nContainer 1 - &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Bolt\"&gt;Bolt&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Bullet\"&gt;Bullet&lt;/a&gt; \nContainer 2 - &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shortbow\"&gt;Shortbow&lt;/a&gt; \nContainer 3 - &lt;a href=\"Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Leather Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; "}
