{"id": "2736", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2736", "title": "Short Sword", "text": "Short Swords are one-handed swords with a short blade which deal piercing damage. They are often used by thieves and assassins, as they are easy to conceal. The base Short Sword deals 1d6 &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing damage&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Speed%20Factor\"&gt;Speed Factor&lt;/a&gt; of 3. In classic &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; this weapon falls under the Small Swords proficiency; in all other games, it falls under the Short Sword proficiency. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , and . It can be bought from most weapon stores.\nThe Short Sword is also used as a standard weapon by &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"xvart\"&gt;xvart&lt;/a&gt;s.\nAs Short Swords deal piercing rather than slashing damage, they are the only type of sword that is unable to damage enemies \u2014 for example, \u2014 that are immune to piercing damage."}
{"id": "3824", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3824", "title": "Short Sword +1", "text": "Short Sword +1 is a magical enchanted weapon but, like the &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Long Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, a rather common one. When compared with a normal &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;short sword&lt;/a&gt;, this weapon deals +1 more damage, has +1 THAC0\u00a0bonus, and is faster (has a lower speed factor). Both have the same weight though. This item appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", ', \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" and '. Only in the original Baldur's Gate this weapon belongs to the small swords proficiency; otherwise, it has the short sword proficiency."}
{"id": "7639", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7639", "title": "Short Sword +2", "text": "A Short Sword +2 is a magical and enchanted weapon which deals 1d6+2 points of piercing damage, has a -2 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, a speed factor of 1 and weighs 2 lbs. Unlike most weapons, there are two versions of this sword, which vary only in appearance, price and description."}
{"id": "15585", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15585", "title": "Short Sword +3", "text": "A Short Sword +3 is an enchanted weapon which deals 1d6+3 points of piercing damage, has a -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, a speed factor of 0 and weighs 2 lbs."}
{"id": "20039", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20039", "title": "Short Sword of Backstabbing", "text": ""}
{"id": "7522", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7522", "title": "Short Sword of Mask", "text": "The Short Sword of Mask +4 is an &lt;a href=\"short%20sword\"&gt;short sword&lt;/a&gt; which inflicts 1d6+4 points of piercing damage, has a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of 4, a speed factor of 0 and weighs 2 lbs. There is a 15% chance that a hit with this weapon can entangle (movement speed set to 0, +2 penalty to AC) a target for 24 seconds (or four rounds), and no save can be made against this effect, but it can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item appears in ' and '. It's sold at &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Sister%20Garlena\"&gt;Sister Garlena&lt;/a&gt; on the top of the tower. It can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; into an empowered + 5 version, which requires the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Heart of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; and some gold as well.\nUpgraded.\nThe Short Sword of Mask +5 deals 1d6+5 points of piercing damage, has a THAC0 bonus of 5, and there is a 15% chance that a hit with this weapon can entangle (movement speed set to 0, +2 penalty to AC) a target for 24 seconds (or four rounds). It also has a 15% chance to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; the target for 1 level (no save, nonmagical effect, that, therefore, bypasses magic resistance and can't be dispelled).\nGameplay.\nThe entangling effect featured in both forms of this sword has several noteworthy characteristics:\n-It stacks with itself, making it so the enemy's AC can be made progressively worse, beyond the initial +2 penalty\n-It stacks with other entangling effects, such as &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; (spell) and &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt;s #11 and #69\n-It affects creatures immune to other forms of entangling, such as Dragons. The vine-like overlay effect won't be displayed on them, but they'll still receive the AC penalty and their movement speed will be set to 0 (so they receive the full effect). In fact, the only protection against this weapon's entangling effect (besides magic resistance) is protection against AC-lowering itself (extremely rare) or against movement speed modifications (not as rare, but uncommon)."}
