{"id": "7524", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7524", "title": "Shuruppak's Plate", "text": "Shuruppak's Plate is an enchanted full plate armor +3.\nEquipped Abilities:\nThis armor set includes unlisted penalties of +1 THAC0 and -2 movement rating in the non-enhanced edition games.\nIt also weights 55 lb. less than the standard full plate.\nAcquisition.\nThis item appears in and . It is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura&lt;/a&gt; when he is killed in the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Siege Camp&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Saradush\"&gt;Saradush&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nBeing one of the few items that increase Dexterity, it is best utilized by characters with Dexterity score between 14 and 17 in order to grant them 1 additional point bonus to AC. &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Korgan%20Bloodaxe\"&gt;Korgan Bloodaxe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok Anchev&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; will thus receive the greatest benefits of using this armor."}
