{"id": "47443", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47443", "title": "Silver Apple", "text": "The Silver Apple is a consumable item that can be found during &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quest &lt;a href=\"Dorn%27s%20bloody%20path\"&gt;Dorn's bloody path&lt;/a&gt;, available in . \nThe apple has different effects based on the &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; of the character who consumes it. It restores 25% of the user's &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit Points&lt;/a&gt; and provides a +2 bonus to all &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;attributes&lt;/a&gt; for 6 rounds - for &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Neutral&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Good&lt;/a&gt; characters only. &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Evil&lt;/a&gt; characters suffer 25% loss of their maximum &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit Points&lt;/a&gt; and receieve a -2 penalty to all &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;attributes&lt;/a&gt; for one day (resting removes the effect). "}
{"id": "11505", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11505", "title": "Silver Blade", "text": "This is a part of the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sword\"&gt;Silver Sword&lt;/a&gt;. The blade is introduced during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;.\nAquisition.\nThere are several ways this blade will or can be obtained by the party.\nThe first way is to kill or pickpocket &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; as part of the &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Escaping the asylum&lt;/a&gt; questline in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Basement\"&gt;Spellhold Basement&lt;/a&gt;, or even later in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;Spellhold Main Floor&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; will also insist that the party takes the blade as a reward if the party participated in the &lt;a href=\"Leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;Leaving the island&lt;/a&gt; questline, as a prize for helping him steal the Pirate Lord &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik's&lt;/a&gt; personal vessel. \nThis method is probably best as it allows the party a chance to take part in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt; questline. If the party opts to take the portal in the Spellhold Basement - they will miss out on that entire quest and adventuring area and hundreds of thousands of XP and treasure.\nIf you pickpocket the blade, oddly enough Saemon will still give you another duplicate blade if you choose to leave Brynnlaw by ship. \nUnlike other scripts where it is removed from his inventory and transferred to yours, a second blade is created (which is a coding oversite - not intended for plot purposes). \nHaving a second blade allows some actions that are probably not what was planned by the developers - but in the end the party can still make only one &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sword\"&gt;Silver Sword&lt;/a&gt; if both components are brought to &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt;.\nHaving an extra silver blade allows the party to be kinder to the githyanki who are hunting their blade in chapter 6. The party can return it and avoid bloodshed if they desire (and then of course, still be able to get the Silver Sword reforged, if the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Hilt\"&gt;Silver Hilt&lt;/a&gt; is pickpocketed from &lt;a href=\"Kruin\"&gt;Kruin&lt;/a&gt; the githyanki). Roleplay this as you will."}
