{"id": "38674", "revid": "44766191", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38674", "title": "Silver Dragon", "text": "Silver Dragons are the second most powerful of the \"Metallic\" family of dragons, a collection of dragons characterized by their metal-based scale coloration and their affinity for goodness, although the different species span the Lawful-Chaotic axis. The Silver Dragons are best described as the \"Knights Errant\" of the Metallic Dragon family, with a strong interest in actively crusading against the forces of evil. Despite this, or perhaps because of it, they are also deeply fascinated by humanoids, and often form close allegiance with humans and demihumans, or even walk amongst them in secret.\nEncounters.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; encounters a Silver Dragon during when they venture into the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; during their misadventures in the region of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;, as covered by and that portion of . Whilst exploring the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, Gorion's Ward encounters &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt;, a female silver dragon who is simultaneously expecting a clutch of hatchlings and also devoted to warding &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; excursions away from the surface. When Gorion's Ward encounters her, the drow have abducted her eggs and are holding them to ransom to force her into allowing them to launch an invasion of the surface, and she turns to the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; for assistance in reclaiming her children.\nIn the player may encounter two more during the quest &lt;a href=\"Dorn%27s%20bloody%20path\"&gt;Dorn's Bloody Path&lt;/a&gt; in the realm of Lunia. They are labeled as \"Silver Dragon\" but in dialogue their names are &lt;a href=\"Dolrassa\"&gt;Dolrassa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ixthezzys\"&gt;Ixthezzys&lt;/a&gt;. They may be negotiated with to avoid combat or killed for &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scales\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scales&lt;/a&gt; to take to &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; to make the extremely useful low-AC cold-resistant &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;, though the armor cannot be worn by Good characters."}
{"id": "51537", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51537", "title": "Silver Dragon Cone of Cold", "text": "Silver Dragon Cone of Cold is an innate ability available to Silver Dragons in the game saga. This innate ability is initiated via internal creature scripting during combat. The purpose of the spell is to apply a &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; effect to the target and any in the Area of Effect, particularly the dragon's enemies.\nEffects.\nThe ability is uninterruptible and takes almost no time to deploy. The scripted targeting will fire over a selected single target, which is typically a enemy within the creature's sight detection range. The target and all creatures in the area of effect are subject to the effects. This projectile will impact and spread in a limited burst hit animation of silvery colored magic. \nWhen a dragon deploys this breath weapon, a blast area exposes all within the AoE who are then subjected to a 24d10 &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold damage&lt;/a&gt; effect. A quick reaction &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs Breath will apply, and a successful save will half the damage. Perhaps the target was able to dive aside, roll away from the burst, or raise a shield up to deflect some of the breath weapon. "}
{"id": "51536", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51536", "title": "Silver Dragon Paralyzation", "text": "Silver Dragon Paralyzation is an innate ability available to Silver Dragons in the game saga. This innate ability is initiated via internal creature scripting during combat. The purpose of the spell is to apply a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect to the target and any in the Area of Effect to the dragon's enemies.\nEffects.\nThe ability is uninterruptible and takes almost no time to deploy. The scripted targeting will fire over a selected single target, which is typically a enemy within the creature's sight detection range. The target and all creatures in the area of effect are subject to the effects. Rather than a cone of cold spreading forth from the dragon, this projectile will burst and spread in a limited impact hit animation of silvery colored magic. \nWhen a dragon deploys this breath weapon, a blast explodes upon enemies within the AoE who are then subjected to a Stun effect. A quick reaction &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs Breath will apply, and a successful save will negate the Stun. Perhaps the target was able to dive aside, roll away from the burst, or raise a shield up to deflect some of the breath mist. "}
{"id": "28836", "revid": "282905", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28836", "title": "Silver Dragon Scale", "text": "A Silver Dragon Scale can be made by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; with a &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scales\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scales&lt;/a&gt; and 5,000 gold. Similar as full armor plate +3 but have same AC against slashing as full armor plate +2 and worth against piercing/missile.\nTwo silver dragons, &lt;a href=\"Dolrassa\"&gt;Dolrassa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ixthezzys\"&gt;Ixthezzys&lt;/a&gt;, are found in &lt;a href=\"Lunia\"&gt;Lunia&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quest. Another silver dragon, &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt;, is found before, in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, but does not drop any scales.\nSince silver dragons are good creatures, good characters cannot wear it. Additionally, the wearer will suffer a -2 penalty\u00a0to &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt;.\nAbilities that deal 1 damage in quick succession will heal the wearer over time. The wearer will take 1 damage and be heal for 2 hp. Some examples of these abilities include &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Insects\"&gt;Summon Insect&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Weapon\"&gt;Poison Weapon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "28833", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28833", "title": "Silver Dragon Scales", "text": "Silver Dragon Scales\u00a0can be used by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to make\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scale&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for 5000 gold. While technically a &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor\"&gt;Full Plate Armor&lt;/a&gt; at +3, it does not have an enhancement level assigned and the strength requirement is considerably lower.\nLocation.\nTwo can be found if you kill the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;silver dragons&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dolrassa\"&gt;Dolrassa&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ixthezzys\"&gt;Ixthezzys&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Lunia\"&gt;Lunia&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; is also a silver dragon, but if you kill her you do not get her scales, but her &lt;a href=\"Blood%20of%20a%20Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;. The blood can also be used for some eclectic &lt;a href=\"Human%20Flesh\"&gt;evil deeds&lt;/a&gt;."}
