{"id": "11508", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11508", "title": "Silver Hilt", "text": "The Silver Hilt is one of two components necessary to reforge the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Sword\"&gt;Silver Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nAquisition.\nIf the party is in possession of the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt; (carried within a party member inventory or container), then the first time the party returns to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; a script is triggered. This can occur outdoors in all city districts and during day or nighttime. It may take several rounds of time before launching.\nThe script spawns a &lt;a href=\"githyanki\"&gt;githyanki&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Kruin\"&gt;Kruin&lt;/a&gt;. He will demand that you hand over the\u00a0Silver Blade. You can either give it to him or decide to fight him and his friends. Apart from other loot, he drops the Silver Hilt.\nGameplay.\nif the party gives up the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt; to the gith, then Kruin will depart in peace. If the party dispatches the githyanki blade seekers, the Silver Blade and hilt can be used by &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt; to reforge the Silver Sword."}
{"id": "13370", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13370", "title": "Silver Horn of Valhalla", "text": "Silver Horn of Valhalla is an item in \"\" that can be used to summon an allied fighter.\nLocation.\nInside the chest that lies at the foot of the bed, on the 2nd floor of the &lt;a href=\"Horn%20House\"&gt;Horn House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe horn can be used once per day to summon a 5th level &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20Warrior\"&gt;Berserk Warrior&lt;/a&gt; who will remain for 1 turn or until slain. The fighter is permanently under a &lt;a href=\"berserk\"&gt;berserk&lt;/a&gt; effect, which means he will become uncontrollable during combat and may attack allies.\nUses.\nFor and a &lt;a href=\"diamond\"&gt;diamond&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Maheer\"&gt;Maheer&lt;/a&gt; the Storekeep in the &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; can upgrade the Silver Horn into a &lt;a href=\"Bronze%20Horn%20of%20Valhalla\"&gt;Bronze Horn of Valhalla&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7638", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7638", "title": "Silver Ioun Stone", "text": "Silver Ioun Stone gives the wearer a bonus to &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; of 1 point. It can be obtained exclusively from Zakee's Tavern in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis item allows a 24 &lt;a href=\"Wisdom\"&gt;Wisdom&lt;/a&gt; Cleric (something achievable by the end of the Shadows of Amn part of BG2/BG2EE) to reach 25 Wisdom in the Throne of Bhaal part of BG2/BG2EE, which provides them with an extra level 7 spell slot.\nFor some players, it might not seem like a good enough reason to equip this on one's head slot, as it doesn't provide protection against critical hits; however, one must remember that, after the spell occupying the extra level 7 slot (the rightmost one in the Enhanced Edition) is already cast, the item need not stay on during combat and can be freely switched to a helmet for critical hit protection and other potential bonuses."}
