{"id": "6694", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6694", "title": "Silver Pantaloons", "text": "The Silver Pantaloons are one of three sets of metallic pantaloons scattered throughout the Baldur's Gate trilogy. They serve as easter eggs, but if a player collects all three sets - the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Pantaloons\"&gt;Golden Pantaloons&lt;/a&gt; in , followed by the Silver Pantaloons in and the &lt;a href=\"Bronze%20Pantalettes\"&gt;Bronze Pantalettes&lt;/a&gt; from , and then takes all of them to &lt;a href=\"Kerrick%20the%20Smith\"&gt;Kerrick the Smith&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Amkethran\"&gt;Amkethran&lt;/a&gt;, he will turn them into the &lt;a href=\"Big%20Metal%20Unit\"&gt;Big Metal Unit&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquisition.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Find%20the%20kidnappers%20who%20buried%20Tirdir\"&gt;Find the kidnappers who buried Tirdir&lt;/a&gt; quest in , the party will visit the &lt;a href=\"Kidnappers%27%20House\"&gt;Kidnappers' House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. There, on the second floor the party will meet a noblewoman named &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Elgea\"&gt;Lady Elgea&lt;/a&gt; who is being held captive by &lt;a href=\"Am-Si\"&gt;Am-Si&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Camitis\"&gt;Camitis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Reti\"&gt;Reti&lt;/a&gt;. Upon seeing the party she will initiate dialogue and demand to be set free, but do not do it otherwise the pantaloons will be unobtainable. Instead, tell her that you are undecided, end dialogue, grab the &lt;a href=\"Ransom%20Note\"&gt;Ransom Note&lt;/a&gt; from the nearby cabinet and go to the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt; by nightfall to meet &lt;a href=\"Welther\"&gt;Welther&lt;/a&gt; in front of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;. Either show him the note and he'll hand the pantaloons to you at the cost of losing 2 &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;, or directly pickpocket him."}
{"id": "11361", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11361", "title": "Silver Ring", "text": "Silver Rings are common loot found throughout &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and will likely be found most often on low-level enemies. They are worth very little and are generally not suitable for collecting to be sold."}
{"id": "32247", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32247", "title": "Silver Scepter", "text": "A Silver Scepter is a that can be found in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThree can be found in &lt;a href=\"Repository%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Repository of Undeath&lt;/a&gt;. One on a table in the laboratory, one in the room south of the scrying pool, and the last is in a cabinet, behind a hidden door with a large horde of undead.\nFunction.\nEach time the scrying pool is interacted with while possessing a scepter, one more is placed in the pool. After all three are placed, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may choose one of three visions, which will show someone they know and grant each character in the party . Two additional visions may be unlocked by finding the two &lt;a href=\"Essence%20of%20Clarity\"&gt;Essences of Clarity&lt;/a&gt; on the level and again interacting with the pool."}
{"id": "32896", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32896", "title": "Silver Star", "text": "Silver Star is a . Originally created by Davide Carter, it was adopted by Paula and modified to work with the ' and the '. It is hosted by &lt;a href=\"https%3A//baldursextendedworld.com/\"&gt;Roxanne&lt;/a&gt;.\nSilver Star is a &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"elven\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"assassin\"&gt;assassin&lt;/a&gt; who may &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;join&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor more information, see the link."}
{"id": "11502", "revid": "274208", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11502", "title": "Silver Sword", "text": "The Silver Sword +3 is an enchanted two-handed sword. \nAquisition.\nThis sword is available in and . It is gained by bringing the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Hilt\"&gt;Silver Hilt&lt;/a&gt; and paying 7500 gold to the master smith &lt;a href=\"Cromwell\"&gt;Cromwell&lt;/a&gt; located in his home/workshop in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;. \nYou obtain the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; in return for helping him steal a new ship as part of the &lt;a href=\"Leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;Leaving the island&lt;/a&gt; side quest. It may also be obtained from a successful pickpocketing attempt. \nWith the blade in the party's possession, upon returning to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; and go to one of the major locations in the city (&lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; is most likely), an encounter is triggered with &lt;a href=\"githyanki\"&gt;githyanki&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Kruin\"&gt;Kruin&lt;/a&gt;. He demands that you surrender the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Silver%20Blade\"&gt;Silver Blade&lt;/a&gt;. This blade is considered sacred by the githyanki.\nYou can either give it to him or decide to refuse, leading to a fight with he and his accompanying githyanki warriors. The &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Hilt\"&gt;Silver Hilt&lt;/a&gt; can be taken from Kruin's corpse. Now in possession of both components, if the party wishes they may visit Cromwell to commission the reforging of the two pieces into the Silver Sword.\nGameplay.\nThis two-handed sword is flagged as silver and also a +3 enchanted item. It has a relatively slow weapon speed factor, like most blades of this size.\nOn any successful hit upon a target, it inflicts 1d10 +3 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; damage. There is a 25% probability that the target creature is exposed to a vorpal effect - see the &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; status effect for more details. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Death, with a -2 penalty can negate the instant death effect. If the creature fails the save, and isn't immune to the effect, then a string reference and combat log message displays \"Vorpal Hit\". Additionally, the death type inflicted is the \"Chunked\" death type, which renders the target into bits and pieces - precluding resurrection.\nNote.\nThis item is flagged as a \"critical item\" and is unsellable."}
