{"id": "50323", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50323", "title": "Simbja", "text": "Simbja is a goblin warrior who is a member of an &lt;a href=\"Adventuring%20Party%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;adventuring party&lt;/a&gt; that is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; near the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSimbja will seek to engage in missile combat with his shortbow and arrows. If forced into melee combat he will stab with his dagger.\nBugs.\nIn the original Shadows of Amn goblins are classified by race as either &lt;a href=\"hobgoblin\"&gt;hobgoblin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt; and classified by class as either hobgoblin or &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;. This is not fixed in the Enhanced Edition of either game. However, it is fixed in the where goblins are now properly classified as race: Goblin and class: Fighter.\nFor the sake of proper classification within this wiki and to follow the correct D&amp;D classification, goblins are classified using the Siege of Dragonspear classifications. In Simbja's case the developers gave him a race and class of hobgoblin, but since the developers used goblin animation for him, it must be surmised that he is a goblin and not a hobgoblin. Thief is chosen over Fighter for class since he is equipped with armor and weapons usable by a thief and he is given a special ability of 100 points in the move silently skill. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to this creature. The original weapon proficiencies are removed. Shortbow proficiency is changed to 4 pips, and dagger to 2 pips. Thus, the bow fire will have a slightly faster APR, damage and to hit chance. An SCS default AI script is assigned for better tactical response and behavior."}
{"id": "6337", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6337", "title": "Sime", "text": "Sime is a female &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thief&lt;/a&gt; who works under &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIn , if you sided with the Shadow Thieves, Sime will accompany you to &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; and help you get into &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the party has opted to enter the Asylum by way of obtaining the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Wardstone for Asylum&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth the Adept&lt;/a&gt;, then at some point Sime will be waiting adjacent to the transition point on the North part of Brynnlaw. \nHer last words to party will be \"\"Then get going. I've got to send my report back to the mainland. It's remotely possible that we might be able to get more help, now that the way is clear\".\" \nShe will not be seen again, without modded content.\nMod content.\nSime can become a permanent &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; with the installation of a by &lt;a href=\"Sime%20%28mod%29\"&gt;the same name&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod installation adds a Miscellaneous Enhancement where Sime now has a proper fate, providing closure where none was present originally. (Previously she would go for help and never be mentioned again.)"}
