{"id": "13561", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13561", "title": "Sion", "text": "Sion is a powerful male &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; who is first encountered on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"Guarded%20Compound\"&gt;Guarded Compound&lt;/a&gt; building in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nSion and &lt;a href=\"Ketta\"&gt;Ketta&lt;/a&gt; will greet you upon entering the building:\nThe party may apologize and leave, or not. Either way, Sion will teleport both of them upstairs.\nIf the party intrudes further and attempts to explore the upstairs, Sion, Ketta and the rest of the group, including &lt;a href=\"Maferan\"&gt;Maferan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stalman\"&gt;Stalman&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Olaf%20Rassmusen\"&gt;Olaf Rassmusen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Koshi\"&gt;Koshi&lt;/a&gt;, will attack, providing the party with quite a tough battle.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Sion: he is now a level 22 specialist mage (randomly determined by SCS install), with more memorized spells, and better saving throws. A &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; is prepared for instant uses. Sion has two memorized mage HLA's &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, use depends on the game difficulty setting. Sion will probably try and cast a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt; spell. He is a dangerous caster and should be a priority to disrupt or kill. He has several useful defensive spells to make it hard to hit him with spells or weapons. An SCS random treasure is placed in Sion's inventory.\nWith the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, all of Sion's memorized spells will be the SR version."}
{"id": "48869", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48869", "title": "Sir Beverus", "text": "Sir Beverus is a human &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the retribution squad from the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; that has been sent to administer justice upon the party for the killing of five knights in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area during the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest. The squad is composed of two more paladins, a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"fighter/cleric\"&gt;fighter/cleric&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey will randomly appear in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt; districts, or &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; at any time of the day or night to attack the party for the party's horrific act of murder. All of this can be avoided if the party takes up &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of temporary sanctuary inside his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; following the battle with the knights. After some conversation inside the cabin, Windspear will set off to try to clear the party's name with the Radiant Heart by contacting some of his former friends within the Order. A task in which he is ultimately successful in accomplishing.\nThere is a second reason why the party may encounter the Radiant Heart enforcer group (including Sir Beverus) in Athkatla - and that occurs if the party's reputation falls to the \"Despised\" ranking.\nThe Radiant Heart enforcers group will attack the party on sight, with little or no warning. See the Gallery further below.\nGameplay.\nThe paladin will engage the closest enemy he can detect in melee combat. Despite the paladin kit, his creature file includes no paladin bonuses or innate abilities. No priest spells are provided. He behaves as a fighter.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; a fighter tactical AI script is assigned for better combat behavior. Weapon proficiencies are given with 2 pips in Scimitar and Sword and Shield Fighting style. Three random SCS potions are furnished allowing an initial potion to be quaffed/applied, and others for healing purposes. These will be used."}
{"id": "48871", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48871", "title": "Sir Branet Al-Thon", "text": "Sir Branet Al-Thon is a human &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the retribution squad from the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; that has been sent to administer justice upon the party for the killing of five knights in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area during the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest. The squad is composed of two more paladins, a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"fighter/cleric\"&gt;fighter/cleric&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey will randomly appear in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt; districts, or &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; at any time of the day or night to attack the party for the party's horrific act of murder. All of this can be avoided if the party takes up &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of temporary sanctuary inside his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; following the battle with the knights. After some conversation inside the cabin, Windspear will set off to try to clear the party's name with the Radiant Heart by contacting some of his former friends within the Order. A task in which he is ultimately successful in accomplishing.\nThere is a second reason why the party may encounter the Radiant Heart enforcer group (including Sir Branet Al-Thon) in Athkatla - and that occurs if the party's reputation falls to the \"Despised\" ranking.\nThe Radiant Heart enforcers group will attack the party on sight, with little or no warning. See the Gallery further below.\nGameplay.\nThe paladin will engage the closest enemy he can detect in melee combat. Despite the paladin kit, his creature file includes no paladin bonuses or innate abilities. No priest spells are provided. He behaves as a fighter.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; a fighter tactical AI script is assigned for better combat behavior. Weapon proficiencies are given with 2 pips in Axe and Sword and Shield Fighting style. Three random SCS potions are furnished allowing an initial potion to be quaffed/applied, and others for healing purposes. These will be used."}
{"id": "48984", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48984", "title": "Sir Cadril", "text": "Sir Cadril is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt; during the campaign. He can be found outside of the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nSir Cadril is standing by while &lt;a href=\"Garrick\"&gt;Garrick&lt;/a&gt; tries, miserably, to woo the &lt;a href=\"Lady%20Irlana\"&gt;Lady Irlana&lt;/a&gt; with lines fed to him by the nearby gnome, &lt;a href=\"Cyrando\"&gt;Cyrando&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf spoken to, Cadril seems quite amused at Garricks antics.\"It is quite amusing to watch Garrick perform these endeavors in his efforts to win the Lady's heart. I cannot wait to see what he does, next.\"\"The foolishness of this Garrick fellow...does he think the Lady Irlana does not see through his ruse?\"After the scene, Sir Cadril and the others eventually wander off, presumably out of the game for good.\nTrivia.\nThe scene referred to with Cyrando, a Gnome (presumably having a Big Gnomish Nose) who is enlisted by his \"would-be\" Bard friend to woo a Lady, is most likely an homage to the movie, ."}
