{"id": "48873", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48873", "title": "Sir Jolus", "text": "Sir Jolus is a human &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the retribution group from the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; that is sent to administer justice upon the party for the killing of five knights in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area during the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest or, aside from that, if the party's reputation is lower than 4 and &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; is above level 13. The group is composed of two more paladins, a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"fighter/cleric\"&gt;fighter/cleric&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey will randomly appear in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt; districts, or &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; at any time of the day or night to attack the party for the party's horrific act of murder. All of this can be avoided if the party increases their reputation, if that's the cause, or takes up &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of temporary sanctuary inside his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; following the battle with the knights. After some conversation inside the cabin, Windspear will set off to try to clear the party's name with the Radiant Heart by contacting some of his former friends within the Order. A task in which he is ultimately successful in accomplishing.\nThere is a second reason why the party may encounter the Radiant Heart enforcer group (including Sir Beverus) in Athkatla - and that occurs if the party's reputation falls to the \"Despised\" ranking.\nThe Radiant Heart enforcers group will attack the party on sight, with little or no warning. See the Gallery further below.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; a fighter tactical AI script is assigned for better combat behavior. Weapon proficiencies are given with 2 pips in Short Sword and Sword and Shield Fighting style. Three random SCS potions are furnished allowing an initial potion to be quaffed/applied, and others for healing purposes. These will be used."}
{"id": "48875", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48875", "title": "Sir Laren", "text": "Sir Laren is a human &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the retribution squad from the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; that has been sent to administer justice upon the party for the killing of five knights in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area during the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest. The squad is composed of three &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"fighter/cleric\"&gt;fighter/cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;, and the cleric.\nThey will randomly appear in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt; districts, or &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; at any time of the day or night to attack the party for the party's horrific act of murder. All of this can be avoided if the party takes up &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of temporary sanctuary inside his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; following the battle with the knights. After some conversation inside the cabin, Windspear will set off to try to clear the party's name with the Radiant Heart by contacting some of his former friends within the Order. A task in which he is ultimately successful in accomplishing.\nThere is a second reason why the party may encounter the Radiant Heart enforcer group (including Sir Laren) in Athkatla - and that occurs if the party's reputation falls to the \"Despised\" ranking.\nThe Radiant Heart enforcers group will attack the party on sight, with little or no warning. See the Gallery further below.\nGameplay.\nThe cleric will engage the closest enemy he can detect in melee combat. Despite the cleric class, his creature file includes no priest spell use. He behaves as a fighter.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; a fighter tactical AI script is assigned for better combat behavior. Weapon proficiencies are given with 1 pip in Mace and single weapon fighting style. A random SCS potion is furnished allowing use. A Clerical scroll is readied in the quick use slot for use by the script."}
