{"id": "48878", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48878", "title": "Sir Paritin", "text": "Sir Paritin is a human &lt;a href=\"fighter/cleric\"&gt;fighter/cleric&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the retribution squad from the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt; that has been sent to administer justice upon the party for the killing of five knights in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; area during the &lt;a href=\"Journey%20to%20the%20Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Journey to the Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt; side quest. The squad is composed of three &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;, and the fighter/cleric.\nThey will randomly appear in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums&lt;/a&gt; districts, or &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; at any time of the day or night to attack the party for the party's horrific act of murder. All of this can be avoided if the party takes up &lt;a href=\"Garren%20Windspear\"&gt;Garren Windspear&lt;/a&gt;'s offer of temporary sanctuary inside his &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Cabin\"&gt;cabin&lt;/a&gt; following the battle with the knights. After some conversation inside the cabin, Windspear will set off to try to clear the party's name with the Radiant Heart by contacting some of his former friends within the Order. A task in which he is ultimately successful in accomplishing.\nThere is a second reason why the party may encounter the Radiant Heart enforcer group (including Sir Paitin) in Athkatla - and that occurs if the party's reputation falls to the \"Despised\" ranking.\nThe Radiant Heart enforcers group will attack the party on sight, with little or no warning. See the Gallery further below.\nGameplay.\nThe fighter/cleric will engage the closest enemy he can detect in melee combat. Despite the cleric levels, his script includes no priest spell usage. He behaves as a fighter.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed; a fighter tactical AI script is assigned for better combat behavior. Weapon proficiencies are given with 2 pips in Scimitar and Sword and Shield Fighting style. Three random SCS potions are furnished allowing an initial potion to be quaffed/applied, and others for healing purposes. These will be used."}
{"id": "11454", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11454", "title": "Sir Sarles", "text": "Sir Sarles is an extremely talented (though very arrogant) sculptor visiting &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; at the time &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party arrives in the city.\nInvolvement.\nDuring his stay in Athkatla, Sir Sarles resides in the &lt;a href=\"Jysstev%20Estate\"&gt;Jysstev Estate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Government%20District\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGain the Services of Sir Sarles for the Temple.\nThe temples of &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lathander\"&gt;Lathander&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Helm%20%28Athkatla%29\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Talos\"&gt;Talos&lt;/a&gt; are all eager to commission Sir Sarles to create a sculpture to honor their patron deity, but the arrogant sculptor finds the priests tedious and is reluctant to work. To this end, he has demanded he be given the very rare medium of &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;illithium ore&lt;/a&gt; to work with, and he will only work for the temple that can provide him with the requisite material.\nYou can aid Sir Sarles' &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;efforts on behalf of the temple&lt;/a&gt; of your choosing. Depending on your actions, he will either create a sculpture for the temple or be offended by offering him the &lt;a href=\"Chunk%20of%20Illithium%20Alloy\"&gt;illithium alloy&lt;/a&gt; instead of the raw ore and leave Athkatla; however, the head &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; of the temple will mistake the molded mass of illithium alloy for a doctrine-compatible sculpture and happily display it instead."}
{"id": "48819", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48819", "title": "Sir William Reirrac", "text": "Sir William Reirrac is an NPC during the \"\" campaign, and especially the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt;.\nPresumably, the same person, also a Paladin and member of the Most Noble of the Radiant Heart is referred to by &lt;a href=\"Prelate%20Wessalen\"&gt;Prelate Wessalen&lt;/a&gt; in chapter 6. Depending on whether the party sided with Bodhi earlier, and if prompted through dialogue in Chapter 6, the Prelate will have a brief dialogue regarding sending help to fight Bodhi. Gorion's Ward is told:\nGameplay.\nThe Sir William Reirrac encounter is discussed in the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt; article. As combat is unlikely to occur with this NPC, no details are provided about what would happen if attacked.\nThe second version will be in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; along with Paladin &lt;a href=\"Eric%20Vanstraaten\"&gt;Eric Vanstraaten&lt;/a&gt;. Their script actions are similar, and both have dialogue. The paladin actions are centered around combat outcomes with &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt; vampires while the party is present in the same area.\nThe paladin warriors are not configured with any of the Paladin passive resistances or use of innate abilities such &lt;a href=\"Lay%20on%20Hands%20%28paladin%29\"&gt;Lay on Hands (paladin)&lt;/a&gt;, nor do they have use of any cleric spells.\nMore information about this encounter is covered in the &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; quest page.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a revised fighter style AI script to the paladin in Chapter 6. It allows for application of three SCS potions readied for quaffing during hostilities. Additionally, 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style are added to the creature's weapon proficiency."}
