{"id": "28900", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28900", "title": "Sirine (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "The Sirines in \"Shadows of Amn\" are subjects of the Fairy Queen &lt;a href=\"Vaelasa\"&gt;Vaelasa&lt;/a&gt;, whose realm is located in the &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt;. They will only appear if you attack Vaelasa or if you killed the dryads on the first level of &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%201st%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; which will cause Vaelasa to become hostile when you first meet her. \nGameplay.\nThe only notable difference between the \"Shadows of Amn\" sirines and the sirines found in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, is their &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt;: because they are classified as &lt;a href=\"basilisks\"&gt;basilisks&lt;/a&gt; rather than &lt;a href=\"fairies\"&gt;fairies&lt;/a&gt;, certain &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"spells\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt; with specific abilities related to basilisks will not behave the same as in other fights against sirines."}
{"id": "9547", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9547", "title": "Sirine Queen", "text": "The sirine queen is the head of the &lt;a href=\"sirines\"&gt;sirines&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20North\"&gt;northern Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt; in \"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nIf the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; has accepted &lt;a href=\"Evalt\"&gt;Evalt&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Evalt%27s%20Missing%20Brother\"&gt;search for his brother&lt;/a&gt;, she will stop them when they are taking the sandy path around the northwestern lagoon.\nBiography.\nLike many &lt;a href=\"Sirines\"&gt;of her kin&lt;/a&gt;, the sirine queen does not think much of land-dwellers and their ability to understand a sirine's nature, yet she too \"needs\" &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; males for mating.\nAt the time, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; reaches the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;, it actually \"was\" the sirine queen's time to mate, and she did what she always does in this case: luring a man to her by singing her song. Usually both parties benefit from the exchange and most males are happy to oblige, but this time the lured &lt;a href=\"Evan\"&gt;fisherman&lt;/a&gt; attacked the queen and tried to force himself upon her.\nCombat.\nThe queen's stats make her very distinguishable from common &lt;a href=\"sirines\"&gt;sirines&lt;/a&gt; and truly a queen, only on a par with &lt;a href=\"Meiala\"&gt;Meiala&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;:\nIt should also be mentioned that her is not \"&lt;a href=\"Monsters\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;\", but \"&lt;a href=\"Humanoids\"&gt;humanoid&lt;/a&gt;\" instead. So, any &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; with specific abilities related to these types will behave different depending on whether a sirine or their queen is affected."}
{"id": "28896", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28896", "title": "Sirine queen", "text": ""}
{"id": "8954", "revid": "263642", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8954", "title": "Sirines", "text": "Sirines are playful, fun-loving &lt;a href=\"http%3A//forgottenrealms.wikia.com/wiki/Fey\"&gt;fey&lt;/a&gt; creatures who love to sing and dance. They bear the appearance of human women but posses an unearthly beauty though they are not nearly as beautiful as &lt;a href=\"Nymph\"&gt;Nymph&lt;/a&gt;s. All Sirines are female and their skin tones vary from tan to light blue. Like &lt;a href=\"Nymph\"&gt;Nymph&lt;/a&gt;s, Sirines cannot abide captivity and will die if kept from the sea for too long. \nSirines fight with bows as well as magic. They are less magically powerful than &lt;a href=\"Nymph\"&gt;Nymph&lt;/a&gt;s but are still formidable. They attack with charm spells and can paralyze their foes. They are also able to make themselves invisible if they are cornered. \nThey are very protective of their waters and frequently accost travelers with deadly force sometimes killing them with a kiss. Though more violent than their &lt;a href=\"Dryad\"&gt;Dryad&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Nymph\"&gt;Nymph&lt;/a&gt; cousins they are not evil \"per se\". They are found frequently as enemies along the sword coast and occasionally as allies of a sort. Their actions mirror the sea; sometimes violent and treacherous, sometimes generous and life-giving.\nNotable Sirines.\nBaldur's Gate.\nLarriaz.\n&lt;a href=\"Larriaz\"&gt;Larriaz&lt;/a&gt; is a Sirine in a house on the far southeast side of &lt;a href=\"south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;south Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. She was abducted by fishermen and dies soon after the player finds her.\nMeilala.\nOn the third level of the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, you will find five statues of failed adventurers, one of who is a Sirine named Meiala. Clicking on her statue will cause her to come to life and join your side for a limited time before turning hostile and trying to kill you.\nSil.\nHostile sirines can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Lighthouse\"&gt;Lighthouse&lt;/a&gt; area. &lt;a href=\"Sil\"&gt;Sil&lt;/a&gt; and two others guard the entrance to Black Alaric's cave. Three others are on the beach on the bay near the center of the map.\nSirine Queen.\nThere is also the &lt;a href=\"Sirine%20Queen\"&gt;Sirine Queen&lt;/a&gt; on the northern part of the Isle of Balduran. You will be asked by &lt;a href=\"Evalt\"&gt;Evalt&lt;/a&gt; to rescue his brother &lt;a href=\"Evan\"&gt;Evan&lt;/a&gt;. You can collect the body of &lt;a href=\"Evan\"&gt;Evan&lt;/a&gt; off of the &lt;a href=\"Sirine%20Queen\"&gt;Sirine Queen's&lt;/a&gt; dead body.\nOther.\nThere are four Sirines with &lt;a href=\"Kelddath%20Ormlyr\"&gt;Kelddath Ormlyr&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Song%20of%20the%20Morning%20Temple\"&gt;Song of the Morning Temple&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple\"&gt;Temple&lt;/a&gt; area. No dancing, but each stands on a disk at the four cardinal points, singing. They can be pickpocketed for one &lt;a href=\"Pearl\"&gt;Pearl&lt;/a&gt; each. If you attack Kelddath, they will immediately fight to defend him. \nAnother three sirines are found in the south-western corner (&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;1000.3400&lt;/a&gt;) of the &lt;a href=\"Shipwreck%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Shipwreck's Coast&lt;/a&gt; area west of &lt;a href=\"High%20Hedge\"&gt;High Hedge&lt;/a&gt;.\nCombat.\nWith &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Invisibility\"&gt;Improved Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, sirines are formidable foes unless you can run them out of spells. Keep your melee fighters at a safe distance and use spells like &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20I\"&gt;Monster Summoning I&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt; to occupy their attention if you can, otherwise send in a single high-hp fighter. Spells such as &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Insects\"&gt;Summon Insects&lt;/a&gt; will help disrupt their casting. &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; will remove a &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt; spell, and the charm ability of &lt;a href=\"Algernon%27s%20Cloak\"&gt;Algernon's Cloak&lt;/a&gt; will (often) counter it, as will (perhaps) the spells &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person%20or%20Mammal\"&gt;Charm Person or Mammal&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; is immune to charm spells whle using his &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Berserk&lt;/a&gt; ability, as is anyone wielding the &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword%2C%20Cursed%20Berserking%20%2B3\"&gt;Two-handed Sword, Cursed Berserking +3&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Brage\"&gt;Brage&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Archaeological%20Site\"&gt;Archaeological Site&lt;/a&gt; area to the south. Again, send Minsc or the berserk sword wielder in alone so that they will not attack other party members.\nHaving a powerful melee character quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Clarity\"&gt;Potion of Clarity&lt;/a&gt; is also very effective."}
{"id": "29604", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29604", "title": "Sister Farielle", "text": ""}
{"id": "8161", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8161", "title": "Sister Garlena", "text": "Sister Garlena is a &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20the%20Vigil\"&gt;Knight of the Vigil&lt;/a&gt; whose task, along with the other knights, was to keep the 'Imprisoned One' trapped in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen you arrive at Watcher's Keep, Sister Garlena will be waiting below the looming structure. The player must initiate dialogue, and it should be their leader &lt;a href=\"Odren\"&gt;Odren&lt;/a&gt;. Once dialogue is underway, at some point he'll ask you to perform a ritual to fortify the seals that hold the Imprisoned One beneath the keep. If the party agrees, the knights will then escort you to the top of the fortress (in a cutscene move).\nSister Garlena has a few interjections during any conversations with Odren. If the player accepts the quest to assist the Knights with their needs to reinforce the wards within Watcher's Keep, She'll offer the party an invitation to peruse her goods for sale, and trade. \nBe aware that she will leave once the Watcher's Keep quest has been completed, so make any trades and purchases before than occurs.\nIf the party ends up in combat with Garlena she'll have access to both Cleric and some Druidic spells, as outlined in the InfoBox's scripted spell use.\nGarlena is unarmed and won't engage in melee combat.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes some revisions to Sister Garlena. \nShe is provided with a new memorized repertoire of Divine spells (No Druid spells included). A smarter Priest AI is assigned. Her initial buffs include: &lt;a href=\"Regeneration%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Regeneration (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Barrier\"&gt;Blade Barrier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Resistance%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Magic Resistance (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Fire%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Protection From Fire (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Physical%20Mirror\"&gt;Physical Mirror&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chaotic%20Commands\"&gt;Chaotic Commands&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough she isn't armed, Sister Garlena preps with a Spiritual hammer spell, so she'll be able to wield that.\nA ready to use potion is scripted for use to boost abilities.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed, those spells will be the SR versions.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; mod has a \"Unique Containers Colors and Names\" option (Miloch), which fixes issues with containers and stores. Garlena's Potion Case and Gem Bag are updated with their \"gold\" version. See an image &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/gallery/image/504-unique-containers-miloch/Tweaks\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;."}
