{"id": "15984", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15984", "title": "Skeleton Warrior", "text": "Skeleton Warriors are serious combat versions of &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s. They come with a greater amount of hit points and inflict greater damage with the +1 two-handed sword they wield. A second version carries a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt; and a two-handed sword. Plus they drop some high-value treasure unlike normal skeletons which drop no treasure. They also have up to 90% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and all the normal undead immunities. To prevent critical hits they wear a helmet as well.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes SKELWA01 so that it gets a new default SCS AI script. It is protected from &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt; effects. The creature is also assigned 3 pips in Two-handed sword proficiency and 2 pips in Two-handed weapon fighting style. Its adjusted THAC0 is now 4 instead of 7. \nSkeleton Archer SKELAR01 has a new default SCS AI script. They also have 2 pips Longbow proficiency and 2 points in single weapon fighting style (for their melee attack). Their base THAC0 is improved to 1. "}
