{"id": "5018", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5018", "title": "Skull Trap", "text": "When Skull Trap is cast, a magical skull launches itself to the center of the target area and floats there until detonated.\nGameplay.\nThe caster designates a point on the area map to which the \"Skull Trap\" projectile will travel to, use the targeting cursor to designate the point.\nOnce a Skull Trap is cast the projectile speeds to the designated point and remains \"hovering\" there on the area map until detonated by proximity to a creature.\nAll creatures in the explosive radius are exposed to variable &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;, as determined by the spell caster's mage level.\nExposed victims are allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells to halve the damage.\nThe skull trap's explosive magic damage effect is potentially blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreatures protected with &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; will not be affected.\nCreatures with the spell &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magic%20Energy\"&gt;Protection From Magic Energy&lt;/a&gt; will take no damage from this spell.\nAdditionally, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Necromancy&lt;/a&gt; will negate the spell's effects, as will the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe spell description isn't accurate in terms of the actual in-game explosive damage radius, it is closer to 20' radius rather than a 30'. Using it in gameplay a few times will give the player a better appreciation of the true Area of Effect.\nNotes.\nAbout one fifth smaller blast range than &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, but scales up to level 20 instead of 10, and produces magical damage, not the more commonly resisted fire type. If a high-level mage stocks up three Skull Traps in one &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, the damage potential is 3 x 20 x 1d6 (max damage = 360). Do notice the delay before the explosion though and place the traps accordingly.\nWhere to obtain its scroll.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nTreasure\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Skulltrap\" (note D&amp;D spelling) has several differences than the game's implementation of the spell. In the Pen and Paper version, the spell is actually a ward, and not an offensive damage spell - it is placed on an actual skeletal skull and is triggered when touched by living matter - it doesn't have an area proximity triggering ability. A saving throw vs. Breath weapon allows a reduced damage potential. The spell implies that a creature associated with the Negative Energy plane, like undead, would be immune. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, scaling, and saving throw. See below for description:\nSkull Trap\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Necromancy\nRange: Medium\nDuration: Special\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Breath half\nUpon casting this spell, a skull is thrown by the caster at the target area. The skull floats in the area until a creature comes within 15 feet of it. When this happens, the skull is triggered and explodes, damaging everyone within a 20 foot radius. The explosion deals 1d6 points of magic damage per level of the caster (up to a maximum of 10d6), with a save vs. breath at -2 allowed for half damage. When casting this spell, it is wise to set it far away from the party, lest they set it off accidentally. Undead creatures are not affected by this spell."}
{"id": "56602", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56602", "title": "Skull Trap (Skull Explode)", "text": "This spell is titled Skull Trap but actually explodes in a \"White Fireball\" in an area of effect.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Skull\"&gt;Flaming Skull&lt;/a&gt; creature is the user of this spell - it is some kind of death throe phenomena. \nInternal AI scripting text labelling identifies this spell as \"Skull Explode\". \nGameplay.\nWhen a Flaming Skull creature is killed, this spell triggers and explodes in an Area of Effect centered on the destroyed creature.\nThe innate spell effect is an instantly cast offensive damage spell. \nAll creatures in the area of effect are exposed to the effects. \nThe explosion inflicts 20d6 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;, however if the victim makes a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spell, then the damage is halved. \nThe Explosion can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and has 3 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, and thus can be blocked by a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; as well.\nMod content.\nBoth the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mods change this spell so that it cannot affect the Undead."}
