{"id": "57086", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57086", "title": "Slave", "text": "A Slave is a subjugated creature in dire straits. These human slaves are encountered on &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%202\"&gt;Level 2&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mine%20level%203\"&gt;Level 3&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt;. Their dialogue is short and there is nothing to be gleaned from talking with them except for the fact that they're down-beaten and cowered individuals.\nDialogue.\n\"Charmed response\".\nThe Slaves in the dining room are beyond help as they have nothing at all to say."}
{"id": "57097", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57097", "title": "Slave (bailey)", "text": "This particular Slave is encountered at the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; inside the bailey just west of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Shed\"&gt;Shed&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party are automatically transported to the surface of the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; after flooding the mine. His &lt;a href=\"Flooding%20the%20Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; depends on whether the &lt;a href=\"Slave\"&gt;Slave&lt;/a&gt;s within the mine were rescued or not before the mine was flooded. Upon conclusion of the dialogue, the slave disappears.\nDialogue.\n\"Slaves rescued\".\n\"You saved us! The rest of us have fled to the north toward Baldur's Gate, but I elected to stay so as to thank all of you. Without your heroics, who knows how long we'd be working that horrible mine. I'm just glad we didn't end up in the watery grave down there like the rest of the Iron Throne mercenaries.\"\n\"Slaves parish\".\n\"You bastards! You left everyone down there to rot! I barely escaped those chill waters. All my friends drowned. May all of you rot in the Nine Hells for what you've done!\""}
{"id": "57098", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=57098", "title": "Slave (lift)", "text": "This Slave is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Shed%23The%20Lift\"&gt;Lift&lt;/a&gt; that's located below the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines%20Shed\"&gt;Shed&lt;/a&gt; if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; attempts to reenter the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mine&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Flooding%20the%20Cloakwood%20Mine\"&gt;flooding&lt;/a&gt; it to close out &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Four\"&gt;Chapter Four&lt;/a&gt;. His reaction depends on whether the &lt;a href=\"Slave\"&gt;Slave&lt;/a&gt;s within the mine were rescued or not before the mine was flooded. Upon conclusion of the dialogue, the slave disappears.\nDialogue.\n\"Slaves rescued\".\n\"You can't get down into the mine anymore, friend. The water level's risen so high that the whole mine's filled. I'm just waiting here to see if anything interesting floats to the top of the elevator shaft. Doubt it will though. I have to thank you for saving my life, and everyone else for that matter.\"\n\"Slaves parish\".\n\"Get away from me, you bastard! I lost a lot of good friends to the mine 'cause of your lack of forethought. If you've come back to loot bodies, then you're out of luck. The mine's flooded all the way up to the topmost level. I'm just hoping that someone might surface... you never know.\""}
{"id": "51493", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51493", "title": "Slave Leader", "text": "Slave Leader is a fighter class male human whom the party may speak with if they wish. He and other women and children humans are caged in ornate pens on the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; Slave Pen Platform. This man is caged by himself.\nGameplay.\nThis thin, but still fit looking human has the bearing of a warrior. He is the default leader of a number of other humans who were taken captive on a drow hunting expedition on the surface. He will speak if spoken to. This man does not look cowed, but his sad eyes show the sorrow and concern on his mind.\nMore information and a potential Side Quest/encounter can be pursued here. Visit the &lt;a href=\"Free%20the%20Human%20Slaves\"&gt;Free the Human Slaves&lt;/a&gt; page for additional information, if desired."}
{"id": "52080", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52080", "title": "Slave Leader (Illithids)", "text": "Slave Leader is a speaking NPC that interacts with the party in the &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayers%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Mind Flayers in Underdark&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nWhen the player finds the &lt;a href=\"Illithid%20Serum\"&gt;Illithid Serum&lt;/a&gt; and then visits a strange chamber with machinery and unmoving humans with tubes attached to their bodies you see a series of screen text information displays:\nAssuming the player does use the serum and pour it into the tube, a text displays:\nThe humans, who are currently slaves of the illithids awaken from some kind of drug induced psycho state, for what purpose is unknown.\nAfterwards the Slave leader will speak in grateful appreciation for saving the group from a horrible state of nightmares and hallucinations during their \"sleep\". Through some dialogue and questions the party learns that these surfacers from Myratma were somehow captured while adventuring in the Underdark. The Leader, who tells you his name is Camaris Highcastle, informs you of what he knows to be going on:\nWith this knowledge in hand, it is possible that perhaps some of these &lt;a href=\"Control%20Circlet\"&gt;Control Circlet&lt;/a&gt; items could be produced by the party - using the illithids own machine to do so. The circlets may prove to be a valuable tool while in this horrid place.\nThe Slave leader will wish you luck and says that the slaves can fend for themselves while you try and find a way out of this psionic hell hole.\nNotes.\nIf the party succeeds in its mission and finds the &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Brain%20Blood\"&gt;Elder Brain Blood&lt;/a&gt;, the Slave Leader and his group will speak with the party again before departing the illithid complex."}
