{"id": "40161", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40161", "title": "Slave Wraith", "text": "The Slave Wraith creatures are a unique one-of-a-kind opponent encountered alongside the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Wraith\"&gt;Demon Wraith&lt;/a&gt; in a specific chamber on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nCalled forth by the demon, - these creatures appear nearby their skeletal corpses laying on the floor. The Slave Wraith beings are controlled against their will by the demon and are hostile.\nThe creatures will generate text dialogue on the combat screen, such \"\"Run, fools!\" and \"We cannot control ourselves!\"\".\nThe creatures have a number of immunities and resistances, as shown on the InfoBox.\nThey can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nTheir combat behavior is guided by the tried and true but simplistic WTASIGHT.bcs script. Each slave that detects an opponent will move toward the nearest one and engage in melee attacks.\nFor details of the effects caused by their melee attack - see their &lt;a href=\"TELSLAV.ITM\"&gt;Weapon&lt;/a&gt; description page.\nIf the Demon Wraith is destroyed, any surviving Slave Wraith creature will utter \"Thank you for releasing us! Thank you!\" and provide . A death animation will then manifest over the creature's sprite - signifying their release from undead servitude. However, destroying a slave in combat provides , and doesn't grant the spirit's release.\nIf the player has set their game difficulty below \"Normal\" - then the creatures are gimped by a &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; spell and a double &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt; - making them almost no threat at all."}
