{"id": "27872", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27872", "title": "Slime Library Note", "text": "The Slime Library Note is found in \"\" on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;second floor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in the Slime Library. The note details one of the four tactics to defeating the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt;.\nJust as importantly, it outlines the methods needed to overcome the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Golem%20%28Guardian%20of%20Ice%29\"&gt;Guardian of Ice&lt;/a&gt; and its supporting &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Mist\"&gt;Ice Mist&lt;/a&gt; allies, so the player can obtain the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Scepter\"&gt;Ice Scepter&lt;/a&gt;. Without that scepter, the party will never be able to confront the Chromatic Demon."}
{"id": "27848", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27848", "title": "Slime Scepter", "text": "The Slime Scepter can be found in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Elemental Level&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in ' and '.\nGameplay.\nDefeat the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Snake%20%28Guardian%20of%20Slime%29\"&gt;Guardian of Slime&lt;/a&gt; to obtain this scepter from the creature's corpse.\nThe item is flagged as \"Critical\" and can't be sold.\nThe Slime scepter acts as a key that can one gate on this dungeon level:\nIt is one of four \"keys\" needed to free the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt; from the special magical cage."}
{"id": "42383", "revid": "273271", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42383", "title": "Slime Sickness", "text": "Slime Sickness is a side quest in that can be found by going to the southernmost part of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, west of the Corrupted Druid Grove.\nAcquiring.\nBy exploring the Underground River, will encounter a number of soldiers from the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; who &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20Crusader\"&gt;have been infected&lt;/a&gt; by some fungus that is dissolving them into jelly. They will plead for assistance, pointing them towards the mad druid &lt;a href=\"Ferrusk\"&gt;Ferrusk&lt;/a&gt; whose corrupted grove lies just to the east.\nWalkthrough.\nIf spoken to, Ferrusk will reveal he can cure the slime sickness, but he will require a &lt;a href=\"Myconid%20Bloom-Sac\"&gt;Myconid Bloom-Sac&lt;/a&gt; and, depending on the chosen dialog options, no payment or payment in the form of either 2000 gold pieces or the murder of his former druidic cabal, who can be found &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;just above the Underground River&lt;/a&gt;. Once presented with either the coins or the heads of &lt;a href=\"Jamven\"&gt;Jamven&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chorster\"&gt;Chorster&lt;/a&gt;, he will take the Bloom-Sac from the party's inventory and give them the cure. Cooperating with him is not the only way to help these sick crusaders though, as he can also be attacked in order to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"BDPOTN06\"&gt;Slime Sickness Curative&lt;/a&gt; from his dead body. The curative should also be able to be pickpocketed from him.\nUpon returning to the soldiers, all but one of them will be revived by the cure, rewarding the party with 6,000 EXP for completing the quest; one soldier succumbs to the slime sickness and instead transforms into a &lt;a href=\"Mustard%20Jelly\"&gt;Mustard Jelly&lt;/a&gt;, which is worth 2,000 EXP when defeated. The leader of the sick soldiers will also reward with a &lt;a href=\"Seal%20of%20Caelar\"&gt;Seal of Caelar&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhilst this marks the official completion of the quest, the party can also speak to &lt;a href=\"Ladle\"&gt;Ladle&lt;/a&gt; and inform him of having found and cured the sick crusaders, as the leader of the (formerly) sick soldiers suggests. He will express his gratitude for this:\nRefuse to Help.\nIf the player declares that they will not help the sick crusaders, they all instantly succumb to their disease and transform into a collection of &lt;a href=\"Mustard%20Jelly\"&gt;Mustard Jellies&lt;/a&gt;, which immediately attack the party.\nIn newer game versions, it is no longer possible to refuse to help (confirmed for v. 2.6.6.0), the journal entry will always be the same, regardless of the chosen dialog options, and the crusaders will transform after a while."}
{"id": "33001", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33001", "title": "Slime Sickness Curative", "text": "The Slime Sickness Curative is in the possession of &lt;a href=\"Ferrusk\"&gt;Ferrusk&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt; in . Ferrusk will trade the curative in change for the &lt;a href=\"Myconid%20Bloom-Sac\"&gt;Myconid Bloom-Sac&lt;/a&gt; and 2,000 &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; or just the bloom-sac; alternatively, you can kill him. This potion is needed to heal the &lt;a href=\"Poisoned%20Crusader\"&gt;Poisoned Crusader&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Slime%20Sickness\"&gt;Slime Sickness&lt;/a&gt; quest. In exchange for the cure, the crusaders will reward you with the &lt;a href=\"Seal%20of%20Caelar\"&gt;Seal of Caelar&lt;/a&gt;."}
