{"id": "7911", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7911", "title": "Sling of Arvoreen", "text": "The Sling of Arvoreen is a sling +4 in terms of enchantment. Unlike the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20of%20Arvoreen\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bow%20of%20Arvoreen\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Arvoreen\"&gt;Arvoreen&lt;/a&gt;, this weapon is usable by all races. It has +4 bonus to damage, -4 bonus to THAC0\u00a0and a speed factor of 2.\nThis weapon also has the ability to stun a target for three rounds (18 seconds real-time) if they don't save vs. spells. It stuns all enemies in a 60 ft. radius of the target. This ability is magical, but it nonetheless ignores magical resistance and its stun effect can't be dispelled/cured (whether by dispel magic or spells that cure stun like Remove Paralysis).\nThis item only appears in and the where it can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Beholder%20Cave%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;in the beholders' area&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; ."}
