{"id": "7075", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7075", "title": "Sling of Unerring Accuracy", "text": "The Sling of Unerring Accuracy (Sling of Unerring Accuracy +1 in-game) is a sling weapon added in .\nCompared to a normal &lt;a href=\"sling%20%2B1\"&gt;sling +1&lt;/a&gt;, it has a +2 THAC0 bonus instead of a +1, but loses the +1 bonus to damage and speed factor. As a result, it is more like a sidegrade than an upgrade to the cheaper and more common sling +1, and it is best reserved for either characters with low base THAC0 to improve their accuracy, or high base damage as the difference in damage would be negligible.\nTwo copies of this weapon can be found in the game; one in a locked chest on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Splurging%20Sturgeon\"&gt;Splurging Sturgeon&lt;/a&gt;, and the other up for purchase from &lt;a href=\"Black%20Lily\"&gt;Black Lily&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;."}
