{"id": "5005", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5005", "title": "Slow", "text": "A Slow spell causes hostile creatures to move and attack at half of their normal rates through the &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow status effect&lt;/a&gt;, while also inflicting heavy &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"AC\"&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt; penalties.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a point on the map to aim the spell's target point towards, with a range of 25 feet.\nWhen the spell is finished a fast-moving projectile travels to the selected point and affects all non-party creatures in the 15-ft. radius of the point.\nEach creature must roll a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell with a -4 penalty to negate the effects.\nIf the saving throw is missed the victim is affected by a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a 4 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; penalty.\nA slowed creature basically takes twice as long to perform an action as compared to normal - some examples include; movement is halved, attacks per round are halved, casting time is doubled, regeneration rate is halved, initiative is worsened etc.\nA creature that fails the saving throw will be identified in the combat log with a text reading \"Slowed\", as well as a lighting effect and a color glow rendered on their sprite. A sound effect is audibled upon the start and at the expiration of the spell.\nA player character affected by this spell will show a \"Slow\" icon (No. 41) on their portrait.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell, as well as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity Alteration&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;, such as from an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; spell will negate this effect.\nA &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect can also remove the spell.\nThis spell will not \"stack\" or be additive to other forms of slow magic, for example from the &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish&lt;/a&gt; spell, or &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Slow\"&gt;Golem Slow&lt;/a&gt;, or even another Wizard Slow spell.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Wizard spell \"Slow\" also negates a victim's Dexterity bonuses, in addition to other penalties. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects and saving throw. See below for description:\nSlow\nLevel: 3\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 3\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Polymorph negates\nA Slow spell causes creatures to move and attack at half of their normal rates unless a save vs. polymorph at -2 is made. Slowed creatures also suffer a -2 penalty to attack rolls, AC, and saves vs. breath. Spellcasting time is doubled, though spell effects are not affected. Furthermore, the rate at which these creatures regenerate or suffer damage from poison is halved. At the instant the spell is completed, all hostile creatures in 30-foot radius of a point selected by the caster will be affected (thus, creatures leaving the area are still subject to the spell\u2019s effect; those entering the area after the casting is completed are not). It negates the effects of a Haste spell but does not otherwise affect magically speeded or slowed creatures. This spell is not cumulative with itself or with other similar magic."}
{"id": "6994", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6994", "title": "Moon Dog Figurine", "text": "The Moon Dog Figurine can be used once per day to summon\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Cerebus\"&gt;Cerebus&lt;/a&gt;, a moon dog, lasting for up to 300 seconds/5-turns. \nGameplay.\nA character places the figurine in a quick item slot (like a wand is used) and selects the item to cast a spell. The spell requires the player to select a location on the map where the creature will enter the map, using a targeting cursor. There is a 20 feet distance limit from the caster.\nThe creature appears on the map with a summoning graphic, and Cerberus is now a controllable creature to command, including utilizing its special spells.\nCerebus can attack enemies for the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; and has several innate spell abilities. See the creature's article page for details.\nIf Cerebus is slain, the moon dog figurine will be added to the inventory of the character who has the item in the inventory slots. In case the inventory is full, the item will be dropped on the ground when the figurine is ready to be used again.\nThis item is a reward from the spirit of the lands in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;, given to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the stronghold quest &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Ranger-Protector of the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;.\nThough a \"fallen\" &lt;a href=\"ranger\"&gt;ranger&lt;/a&gt; qualifies for the &lt;a href=\"stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ranger-Protector%20of%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, they can't use this figurine.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Aranthis\"&gt;Aranthis&lt;/a&gt; the Astral war dog based on the \"Moon dog\", summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Tiefling%20%28Mage%29\"&gt;Tiefling (Mage)&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55936", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55936", "title": "Moon Dog Howl (SPIN891)", "text": "Moon Dog Howl (SPIN891) is an innate ability available to &lt;a href=\"Cerebus\"&gt;Cerebus&lt;/a&gt;. The ability is initiated via script by the AI, or by the player when controlling the creature. \nEffects.\nThe effect is directed at the caster only. \nThe ability is cast with a speed of 2 or by other means by script (such as \"ApplySpell\", \"ForceCast\" or \"ReallyForceCast\"). \nThe magic behaves as a typical Wizard's &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Protection From Evil (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; arcane spell on the caster and any party members in the area of effect.\nAdditionally, the caster and party members in the AoE are cured of &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt;/Fear effects, as well as morale break, and also protected from further exposure as if they had a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Fear\"&gt;Remove Fear&lt;/a&gt; spell upon them.\nEnemy creatures with an Evil &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt; that are located in the Area of effect of the Howl are potentially affected in a couple of ways.\nFirst, evil creatures are exposed to 5 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; initially when the spell manifests, which can be negated with a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Spells with a -2 penalty. It also can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. After a delay of 6 and 12 seconds later the same exposure occurs, with the same saving throw to negate.\nSecondly, evil creatures are also exposed to a Moral Break effect that lasts 60 seconds, which can be prevented with a save vs. spells with a -2 penalty or blocked by magic resistance. Creatures immune to morale changes are not affected, such as most &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; or Fiends.\nThe innate spell is &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 6 and can be dispelled.\nBugs.\nThis spell has been identified as needed some work to get it to behave correctly. The spell uses an indiscriminate projectile, it can also hit non-enemy creatures if they're evil. The Projectile it uses for damage and fear effects should be changed from 94 to 159. There are some other coding issues that are planned to revise as well with this spell, and it is listed for updating in the upcoming EEFP - \"Enhanced Edition Fix Pack\"."}
