{"id": "3759", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3759", "title": "Moonblade (Nashkel Mines)", "text": "This Moonblade (Moonblade +3 in \"\") is a powerful magical sword. \nGameplay.\nWhen unsheathed, the blade will be engulfed in blue flames, very similar to &lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Earth\"&gt;The Burning Earth&lt;/a&gt;. It can only be used by &lt;a href=\"Xan\"&gt;Xan&lt;/a&gt;, who was chosen by the sword itself to wield it.\nIt falls under the \"Small Sword\" &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;proficiency&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"Dagger\" in the \"\".\nThe blade offers a bonus to the &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 1, a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of 3 and +50% &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance to the wielder. It can inflict 1d8+3 &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and has a speed factor of 2.\nIt's found in &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt;'s chest in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;, on the fourth level.\u00a0Xan is held prisoner nearby.\nBackground.\nMoonblades generally are longswords which &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s, as &lt;a href=\"Xan\"&gt;Xan&lt;/a&gt;, in the underlying \"Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons 2nd edition\" ruleset usually can't wield. To circumvent this and make Xan a valid wielder of his weapon, the item was changed to be a &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; in terms of . As a result some remnants of a common &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword\"&gt;Long Sword&lt;/a&gt; still can be found in the item file, such as the false description of the weapon's speed factor in the non-\"Enhanced Edition\" of the game (see the Bugs section below) or the (never appearing) description of the item if it was &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;unidentified&lt;/a&gt;, which isn't the case."}
{"id": "30082", "revid": "282079", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30082", "title": "Moonblade (Suldanesselar)", "text": "The \"Moonblade\" is an artifact required as part of the &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20Palace%20in%20Suldenessellar\"&gt;Getting inside the Palace in Suldenessellar&lt;/a&gt; questline during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThree artifacts must be placed on the altar inside the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Temple of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt;. These are the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Goblet%20of%20Life\"&gt;Golden Goblet of Life&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Talisman%20of%20Rillifane\"&gt;Talisman of Rillifane&lt;/a&gt;, and the Moonblade.\nAcquisition.\nAfter a cut scene \"Moonblade Fight\" in &lt;a href=\"The%20House%20of%20the%20Moon\"&gt;The House of the Moon&lt;/a&gt; between an &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Warrior%20%28Suldanessellar%29\"&gt;Elven Warrior (Suldanessellar)&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Balor\"&gt;Balor&lt;/a&gt; - both combatants will be killed, the elf sacrificing himself so that the moonblade can destroy the fiend. Searching the dead elf's heroic corpse reveals the Moonblade."}
