{"id": "7476", "revid": "275612", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7476", "title": "Mordaine", "text": "Mordaine is one of the temporary companions you get during combat training in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"storage%20cellars\"&gt;storage cellars&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4890", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4890", "title": "Mordenkainen's Sword", "text": "The Mordenkainen's Sword spell invokes a levitating controlled sword to fight alongside the party. The Swords is immune to all forms of physical and elemental damage, except for magical energy damage.\nGameplay.\nThe Wizard doesn't have to aim this spell, but simply casts it, and the summoned sword will appear in an elaborate animation lasting several seconds adjacent to the caster, maybe to the side, rear, or front depending on the space available on the map, and if other creatures and objects are occupying the space.\nOnce the sword appears it can be given orders to float (move) in a direction or to target another creature.\nThe sword counts toward the total summoned creature limit.\nThe sword cannot open doors or interact with objects/containers.\nThe sword cannot dispel the fog of war, nor can the sword detect/attack invisible/hidden creatures.\nIf the sword isn't given any orders, it will behave according to its default AI script, which frankly is limited and very basic.\nThe sword has a host of immunities to status effects and is mostly immune to damage.\nHowever, it can still be destroyed by &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt;, excessive &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;, ability score drain (except &lt;a href=\"Intelligence\"&gt;Intelligence&lt;/a&gt;), disintegrate, imprisonment, and all insta-kill effects.\nThe sword will disappear from the map when the spell's duration elapses, and a text display will read \"Unsummoned\".\nTriva.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Mordenkainen's Sword\" differs considerably in its implementation compared to the BG game's version. For instance, the spellcaster is able to mentally wield this weapon (to the exclusion of all activities other than movement), causing it to move and strike as if it were being used by a fighter. It hits any Armor Class on a roll of 19 or 20. it can be removed with a Dispel Magic. See the External links for further reading.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, and description. See below:\nMordenkainen\u2019s Sword\nLevel: 7\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 round/level\nCasting Time: 7\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, the wizard brings into being a shimmering, swordlike plane of force. Once the spell is cast, the sword will float in the air completely under the control of the caster, until the spell duration expires, or the sword is dispelled. The sword acts as a +4 weapon in all respects and attacks on its own once each round, inflicting 5d4 damage when it hits a target. It has 100% resistance to almost all forms of damage (acid, cold, fire, electricity, poison, etc.), and 95% resistance to physical damage, but it\u2019s vulnerable to pure magic damage. The sword is immune to mind affecting spells, has 36 hit points, AC 5, and THAC0 2. Note that this spell does not prevent the caster from performing any other actions while the spell is in effect.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, enemy mages often employ these summoned swords, and sometimes more than one at a time in a battle. Most level 13+ SCS mages can recognize summoned creatures via the AI and are also scripted to destroy them with &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "47349", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47349", "title": "Mordenkainen's Sword (creature)", "text": "Mordenkainen's Sword is a floating sword that can take instructions and fight on the side of its owner. It is summoned by the level 7 Wizard spell &lt;a href=\"Mordenkainen%27s%20Sword\"&gt;Mordenkainen's Sword&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce summoned, its in-game creature name is Magical Sword.\nThis belongs in the comments, but, I can't seem to leave a comment. This spell doesn't have a long duration, but, it makes an incredible tank. It also does decent damage to boot."}
{"id": "50534", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50534", "title": "Moreno", "text": "Moreno is a so called \"squatter\" gathered in Imnesvale, along with &lt;a href=\"Pardo\"&gt;Pardo&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Brunson\"&gt;Brunson&lt;/a&gt;. All three are assembled outside the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Baron%20Metrich\"&gt;Baron Metrich&lt;/a&gt; does not want you to speak with these individuals and has labelled them as illegal 'squatters\" on his land and wants them removed. If you do speak with Moreno, then you will gain additional information, that could very well refute what the Baron has stated. He'll be found as part of a specific task as part of the &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Stronghold%20Duties\"&gt;Paladin Stronghold Duties&lt;/a&gt; quest line.\nMoreno is also a fighter with some skills and weapons and armor. It appears that the developers assigned this fighter with erroneous THAC0 and saving throws (that of a level 1 Fighter).\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default SCS Fighter script for smarter tactical behavior. The mod also revises battle axe weapon proficiency to 4 pips and 2 pips in sword and shield fighting style. Appropriate THAC0 and saving throws are also corrected. Finally, SCS random treasures are added to the inventory."}
{"id": "23745", "revid": "284609", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23745", "title": "Morentherene", "text": "Morentherene is an adult green dragon, though rather young and small by dragon standards. She is an optional boss in chapter 9 of . The party finds her asleep next to her hoard and eggs in the &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%20Cave\"&gt;Wyrm Cave&lt;/a&gt; as they seek the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; where they hope to find a priest of &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; who stole &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;the means&lt;/a&gt; to enter &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe dragon can be either killed, or tiptoed around by sticking to the southernmost part of the cave, where the only two entrances/exits are located. Approaching Morentherene, her eggs, her treasure, using any spell, ability or &lt;a href=\"Bard%23Bard%20Song\"&gt;bard song&lt;/a&gt; will wake her up and battle will break out immediately, but It is possible to get close to her without waking her up with a &lt;a href=\"Stealth\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt; of at least 100 or a &lt;a href=\"silence\"&gt;silence&lt;/a&gt;d character.\nIn core rules difficulty, this battle will attract two &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Wyvern\"&gt;Greater Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s which may join the fight on the side of the wyrm. In hard difficulty, another Greater Wyvern and a &lt;a href=\"Young%20Green%20Dragon\"&gt;Young Green Dragon&lt;/a&gt; will enter the area as well. In insane difficulty, the total will grow to five Greater Wyverns and two Young Green Dragons. But Morentherene can also be killed in her sleep with a single &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger\"&gt;Throwing Dagger&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=\"Throwing%20Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Throwing Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt; does not work \u2013 provided whoever has thrown it still has at least one equipped when the first one hits its target. &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Scales\"&gt;Dragon Scales&lt;/a&gt; can be collected from her corpse."}
