{"id": "42600", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42600", "title": "Moving Crates", "text": "Moving Crates is an optional side quest that can be undertaken in . Upon entering the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, this quest can be gained by speaking to &lt;a href=\"Ladle\"&gt;Ladle&lt;/a&gt;, the overseer of the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;rs currently stationed at the opening. He will request that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; transfer the contents of one nearby crate - approximately twenty bags of grain - to a second crate which sits near the river, just south of the bridge leading over the river.\nOnce this task is done, Ladle will instruct Gorion's Ward to transfer all of the bags of grain back to their original starting point.\nOnce \"that\" has been done, Ladle will admit his surprise and confess that the whole quest was simple busywork that he came up with on the spot, although he's very impressed that Gorion's Ward completed it so quickly. The quest will be completed and the party will gain 12,000 EXP for this quest and two potions."}
{"id": "6798", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6798", "title": "Mr. Colquetle", "text": "Mr. Colquetle is a townsperson who may be encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" or \"\".\nLocation.\nHe lives in a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Beregost%29%23AR3331\"&gt;generic home&lt;/a&gt; in the town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. It's the first house north of &lt;a href=\"Firebead%27s%20Home\"&gt;Firebead Elvenhair's Home&lt;/a&gt;, across the road from &lt;a href=\"Feldepost%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Feldepost's Inn&lt;/a&gt;. The house faces towards the obelisk in the center of town.\nEncounters.\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nIf you have a &lt;a href=\"Bloodstone%20Amulet\"&gt;Bloodstone Amulet&lt;/a&gt; in your bags, he will say that it belonged to his son. You may return it to him, if you like, but there is no reward.\n\"Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition\".\nHe doesn't give you any journal quest record, but if you have found &lt;a href=\"Colquetle%27s%20Family%20Amulet\"&gt;Colquetle's Family Amulet&lt;/a&gt;, you can return it to him for 250 xp and +1 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;. If you ask for a reward or refuse to give him the amulet: -1 Reputation, 250 xp."}
{"id": "8423", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8423", "title": "Mr. Shade", "text": "Mr. Shade is a person who will ask the player character if they have \"them\" without ever identifying what he wants. If the player character bluffs for long enough before admitting ignorance of what he is talking about, Mr. Shade will admit that he forgot what he was supposed to take. If you do continue the bluff, and have the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Pantaloons\"&gt;Golden Pantaloons&lt;/a&gt; in your inventory, he will steal them. You can kill him without losing reputation.\nDialog.\nMr. Shade: \"Do you have them?\"\nGorion's Ward: \"Eh... of course. Do you have the trade?\"\nMr. Shade: \"Aye, that and more. Best we say no more lest the night be blown.\"\nGorion's Ward: \"I suppose? To actions then?\"\nMr. Shade: \"As well we should. The place is ready?\"\nGorion's Ward: \"Will it ever be ready?\"\nMr. Shade: \"And I would know this? What of your job?\"\nGorion's Ward: \" It goes as planned.\"\nMr. Shade: \"So it's agreed then?\"\nGorion's Ward: \"Uh... sure!\"\nMr. Shade: \"All right then.\"\nMr. Shade: \"Um...\"\nMr. Shade: \"You have no idea what we were talking about, do you?\"\nGorion's Ward: \"Eh, no, I was just playing along.\"\nMr. Shade: \"I see... so you bluffed your way through this entire conversation without a clue what was going on?\"\nGorion's Ward: \"Um, yes. What was the point of all this?\"\nMr. Shade: \"I, uh... I forgot. Um, goodbye.\""}
{"id": "41855", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41855", "title": "Mrs. Cragmoon", "text": "Mrs. Cragmoon is a potion vendor who conducts business from the street. She can be located beside the &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20House\"&gt;Derelict House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;\nQuest involvement.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Solve%20the%20%22skinner%22%20murders%20in%20the%20Bridge%20District\"&gt;Solve the \"skinner\" murders in the Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; quest, the child beggar &lt;a href=\"Faraji\"&gt;Faraji&lt;/a&gt; will suggest that Mrs. Cragmoon is a witch and is behind the murders. If you confront her about it and then notify the authorities that she is operating as an unlicensed magic user, she will disappear permanently from the game. You will also be attacked at some future point by a hit squad of friends of Mrs. Cragmoon. The hit squad consists of &lt;a href=\"Strachan%20Fireblade\"&gt;Strachan Fireblade&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dunbar%20the%20Fifth\"&gt;Dunbar the Fifth&lt;/a&gt; and four unnamed Adventurers.\nOpening times.\nMrs. Cragmoon is available for business at the following hours:\nMod Content.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Tweaks%20Anthology\"&gt;The Tweaks Anthology&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Case\"&gt;Potion Case&lt;/a&gt; to Mrs. Cragmoon's inventory, available to buy. In the unmodified game you could buy one from the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; merchant, and that would be the only one in the game until \"Throne of Bhaal\". With this mod component installed, there is another potion case available from &lt;a href=\"Roger%20the%20Fence\"&gt;Roger the Fence&lt;/a&gt; as well."}
{"id": "13806", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13806", "title": "Mrs. Harrold", "text": "A resident of &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;, Mrs. Harrold is a citizen who came to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; to see the circus in the &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Promenade&lt;/a&gt; together with her apparent husband, &lt;a href=\"Harrold\"&gt;Harrold&lt;/a&gt;. This journey was in vain, however, as the circus was closed due to &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20circus%20tent\"&gt;mysterious problems&lt;/a&gt; inside."}
