{"id": "49007", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49007", "title": "Mugger", "text": "A Mugger is a general term for anyone who attacks to rob or \"to beat up...to strike the face\" (i.e., the mug, in pugilism and perhaps influenced by Thieves' Cant \"a dupe, fool, or sucker\"). Muggers may be found in any number of places during the \"\" campaign.\nGameplay.\nThese muggers are dual-classed Fighter/Thieves, protected by &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor\"&gt;Studded Leather&lt;/a&gt; and a good &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; (-2 AC bonus). They can either melee with a &lt;a href=\"Short%20Sword\"&gt;Short Sword&lt;/a&gt; or attack at range with a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow\"&gt;Light Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; and mundane &lt;a href=\"Bolts\"&gt;Bolts&lt;/a&gt; . He is worth and can be looted for &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average random treasure&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49187", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49187", "title": "Mugger (Bridge District)", "text": "This particular Mugger is an &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Thief\"&gt;Thief&lt;/a&gt; that only appears at night (19:30-5:29) on the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Athkatla Bridge&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Horn%20House\"&gt;Horn House&lt;/a&gt;.Reply \"I have no money\" or \"you're about to be the one regretting it\" results in combat, and he calls in help from three more &lt;a href=\"Mugger\"&gt;Muggers&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf you reply, \"Alright, alright...here you go...\" he will divest the party of up to before he tries to flee.\nHe is protected by Studded Leather Armor, a &lt;a href=\"Small%20Shield\"&gt;Small Shield&lt;/a&gt; and a high Dexterity (-3 AC bonus). He can only melee with a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword\"&gt;Bastard Sword&lt;/a&gt;, since he has no ranged weapons. He is worth only and can be looted for and &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Poor%20treasure\"&gt;poor random treasure&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis fellow muggers are Human Fighter/Thieves worth each, who drop &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23Average%20treasure\"&gt;average random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and mundane arms and armor.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes minor revisions to the Mugger. An SCS Thief script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior and backstabbing. The Weapon proficiencies are changed to 1 pip in long sword and 1 in sword and shield fighting style. A long sword replaces the bastard sword as the quick weapon. Random SCS random treasures are placed in his inventory.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Innershade\"&gt;Innershade&lt;/a&gt; mod places a map in this mugger's inventory, for use with the quest in the modification."}
{"id": "4179", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4179", "title": "Mulahey", "text": "Mulahey is a cleric of &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; in the employment of &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;, and the boss of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt; in the story-line. He is found at the lowest level of the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. He has somehow convinced the &lt;a href=\"kobold\"&gt;kobold&lt;/a&gt;s who work for him that he is one of their deities. This is the first hint that worshipers of Cyric are involved in the iron shortage plot. Remembering this can prove useful in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; later on.\nHis paranoia is typical for organizations ruled by fear, as evident by his greeting:\nGameplay.\nHe will summon 6 kobolds and 4 &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s; focus on attacking him or try and group them all together and use AoE spells. It is entirely possible to kill him before he gets a chance to summon his minions, though for a party at this level it requires a bit of luck in the critical hit department. He is not wearing a helmet however, so your critical hit will hit for full damage.\nWhen his hit points get low, Mulahey will pretend to surrender, but will use the distraction to summon more kobolds and skeletons and heal himself up before renewing the fight.\nHe has to be killed and the party can retrieve his letters of correspondence from the chest or his corpse .\nExploit.\nMulahey is scripted not to turn hostile before he can initiate dialogue, so casting &lt;a href=\"Silence%2C%2015%27%20Radius\"&gt;Silence&lt;/a&gt; on him from out of vision is basically his kryptonite. Since he can't speak, he won't turn hostile if attacked, and will stand passively until the silence wears off or he dies. Using the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Monster%20Summoning\"&gt;Wand of Monster Summoning&lt;/a&gt;, this exploit works well on Legacy of Bhaal difficulty. "}
{"id": "10912", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10912", "title": "Mulahey's Holy Symbol", "text": "Mulahey's Holy Symbol is an item dropped by &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt; after the player kills him in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;. It is the symbol of the evil god &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;, who took over as the lord of the dead after &lt;a href=\"Myrkul\"&gt;Myrkul's&lt;/a&gt; demise.\n&lt;a href=\"Berrun%20Ghastkill\"&gt;Berrun Ghastkill&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; would like to see this as part of his &lt;a href=\"Troubles%20in%20the%20Region\"&gt;task&lt;/a&gt;."}
