{"id": "30255", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30255", "title": "Multi-class", "text": ""}
{"id": "24175", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24175", "title": "Mummy", "text": "The Mummy is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; creature that retains some of its living heritage, memories and intelligence. They inhabit forlorn and hidden tombs, crypts, and similar places far from the light of day. They are aligned with evil; corrupted and embittered by the process of transitioning to undeath, whether willingly or unwillingly.\nA mummy may be found in several areas throughout the saga. They may be present with others of their kind and grouped with other undead creatures as well. They can be encountered in some areas by random spawning based on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;'s experience level and or a location difficulty selection. Some examples include in &lt;a href=\"Ghoul%20Town\"&gt;Ghoul Town&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;.\nGame Play.\nA mummy needs to engage in close quarters melee combat in order to be effective with its attack, which deals crushing damage and is modified by its formidable strength. A save vs. death is needed to negate a disease effect that may be contracted with a successful attack. Only magical weapons can strike a mummy during melee combat.\nIf a cleric were to cast the level 7 spell &lt;a href=\"Resurrection\"&gt;Resurrection&lt;/a&gt; on a mummy, the mummy is resurrected back to a &lt;a href=\"commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt;, who will say \"\"Wha\u2014?! Where am I? What has happened?\" and then wander off.\nMod Content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a default AI script to all mummy creatures. This script will improve the tactical behavior and conduct threat assessments as well as selective targeting of vulnerable opponents. In addition, the \"Missile Damage\" resistance is raised to 80%."}
{"id": "53720", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53720", "title": "Mummy (Siege of Dragonspear)", "text": "The Mummy is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; creature that retains some of its living heritage, memories and intelligence. They inhabit forlorn and hidden tombs, crypts, and similar places far from the light of day. They are aligned with evil; corrupted and embittered by the process of transitioning to undeath, whether willingly or unwillingly.\nThis particular mummy is encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Dig%20Site\"&gt;Dwarven Dig Site&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Korlasz%20Family%20Tomb%20Second%20Floor\"&gt;Korlasz Family Tomb Second Floor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Repository%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;Repository of Undeath&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "53719", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53719", "title": "Mummy (Watcher's Keep)", "text": "The Mummy is an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; creature that retains some of its living heritage, memories and intelligence. They inhabit forlorn and hidden tombs, crypts, and similar places far from the light of day. They are aligned with evil; corrupted and embittered by the process of transitioning to undeath, whether willingly or unwillingly.\nThis mummy is encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Adventure%20Level%20%28Spirit%20Warrior%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Adventure Level (Spirit Warrior)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nThe three creature codes referenced in the InfoBox relate to an \"appearance\" of different versions of a Mummy that might be encountered by the player's &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; avatar, the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Warrior\"&gt;Spirit Warrior&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe mummy version encountered is determine by the script, and factors in certain actions taken previously by the Spirit Warrior on the Adventure Level.\nThere are three possible Mummy versions the Spirit Warrior can face, and they have different &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hit%20point\"&gt;Hit point&lt;/a&gt; levels, the only relevant creature stats in this encounter. \nThe mummy's actions are controlled by cutscene scripts, and these creatures are not traditional enemies found in other places in the game.\nAs the contact with this creature only occurs by the scripted Spirit Warrior actions, the Mummy isn't actually \"real\" as related to the player's corporeal party characters."}
