{"id": "11068", "revid": "45084420", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11068", "title": "Murky potions", "text": "Murky potions are fake or otherwise dangerous versions of real potions. They have the same name as the potion they mimic, but look different and are generally described as appearing murky or seeming 'off' in the item description.They have a wide range of effects but consistently do not work as advertised."}
{"id": "43088", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43088", "title": "Murs", "text": "Murs is a female &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; who is part of a small tribe that dwells in a concealed camp in the center-east portion of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; map in \"\". She is the mate of the tribe's chief, an &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Slug\"&gt;Slug&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nWhen the party enters the camp, talking to Murs can initiate the quest &lt;a href=\"Murs%20and%20the%20Brigands\"&gt;Murs and the Brigands&lt;/a&gt;. If completed, she then gives the player the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Dungeon%20Slug\"&gt;The Dungeon Slug&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has managed to become the chief of the tribe, upon telling her that you need to get past the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusade&lt;/a&gt; and into the tunnels beneath &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, she may also update your journal for the quests &lt;a href=\"Blind%20Albino%20Wyrmlings\"&gt;Blind Albino Wyrmlings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Lost\"&gt;The Lost&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Accessing%20the%20Warrens\"&gt;Accessing the Warrens&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Druid%20Circle\"&gt;Dark Druid Circle&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchivements.\nReuniting Murs with her mate Slug, and asking them to join against the crusade, is required to get the following:\nTrivia.\n and are the two members comprising the American hip hop duo ."}
{"id": "43113", "revid": "261190", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43113", "title": "Murs and the Brigands", "text": "Murs and the Brigands is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nThis quest can be started after walking near an &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; bandit camp in the central-eastern portion of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River%20Entrance\"&gt;Underground River Entrance&lt;/a&gt; map during .\nWalkthrough.\nWhen arrives, two ogres, &lt;a href=\"Arbinge\"&gt;Arbinge&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cheski\"&gt;Cheski&lt;/a&gt;, are arguing about which of them should become the tribe's new leader now that their old leader, &lt;a href=\"Slug\"&gt;Slug&lt;/a&gt;, has been kidnapped by the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt;. Slug's mate &lt;a href=\"Murs\"&gt;Murs&lt;/a&gt; protests that they should rescue Slug instead, but she is told to shut up and stay out of it; as a female, she is not allowed to participate in such discussions.\nSpotting the party, they will include them in the conversation. The party can simply attack the ogres, or leave, or they can offer to fight Arbinge and Cheski - either to claim leadership over the ogres themselves, or as champion of Murs.\nIf takes part in the fight for leadership, regardless of if they do it for themselves or for Murs, the rules are made clear: they must fight the two challengers alone and without the use of offensive magic*, although healing and bolstering spells like &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; are permissible. This can be accomplished by moving other party members far away from the fight or by turning off the party &lt;a href=\"AI\"&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf successful, Murs will offer the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Dungeon%20Slug\"&gt;The Dungeon Slug&lt;/a&gt;, promising that the ogres will fight on the side of the Alliance when they attack &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt; if the party brings back her mate.\nAchievements.\nThis quest is required to begin The Dungeon Slug, which is required for the achievement &lt;a href=\"All%20the%20Allies\"&gt;All the Allies&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11161", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11161", "title": "Mustard Jelly", "text": "Mustard Jellies are one of the more dangerous varieties of &lt;a href=\"Slimes\"&gt;slime&lt;/a&gt;. They are immune to normal weapons, electricity, piercing damage and many other forms of attacks, especially missiles, cold and magic. They are also immune to backstab with any weapon. They are most vulnerable to fire, acid, and slashing damage. They have the ability to &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;slow&lt;/a&gt; their enemies.\nShapeshift Mustard Jelly.\nIt is possible to change into a \"Mustard Jelly\", through &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20Self\"&gt;Polymorph Self&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Sewers\"&gt;Cloak of the Sewers&lt;/a&gt;. The polymorphed character obtains the following stats:\nThis list is to be added to pre-existing immunities, such as those coming from equipment for instance.\nThe 100% magic resistance granted by this form translates to immunity to &lt;a href=\"Beholder\"&gt;Beholder&lt;/a&gt; rays, but not \"Devour Brain\" of &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt;s.\nMod content.\nWhile the Mustard Jelly form provided by the Cloak of the Sewers and the Spell form is immune to almost all Gauth and Beholder eye blasts/rays, with &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; and the \"Smarter Beholders\" component that is not completely true. The three &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Mother\"&gt;Hive Mother&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game files are able to fire a unique Cause Serious Wounds ray that bypasses magic resistance, saving throws and spell level protections. Testing indicates at least one blast every other round is generated, dealing an average of 22 &lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; each time. In addition, the Hive Mother's anti-magic ray will drain charges in all equipped items and quick slot items, even in Jelly Form. If soloing the Hive Mother as a Jelly, the creature will deal more damage to you faster than you are able to deal to the Hive Mother. It is also likely that the creature will protect itself from magical weapons as well, and the polymorph duration will wear off before you can kill it with a Mustard Jelly attack weapon."}
