{"id": "13734", "revid": "246282", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13734", "title": "Myrkul", "text": "Myrkul, also known as the Lord of the Dead or the Lord of Bones, is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; dead &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of the dead.\u00a0He is part of the Dead Three alongside &lt;a href=\"Bhaal\"&gt;Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Murder,\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Bane\"&gt;Bane&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Tyranny.\nLong ago Myrkul was a powerful adventuring &lt;a href=\"necromancer\"&gt;necromancer&lt;/a&gt; in his mortal years, traveling with Bane and Bhaal, dedicated each to a quest to attain divinity for themselves. They traveled to the citadel of &lt;a href=\"Jergal\"&gt;Jergal&lt;/a&gt; who, tired of his position, gave up his portfolios willingly. Breaking off his skeletal knucklebones after an argument over which of the three would rule over the other two, they were each thrown by the mortals to determine which of Jergal's portfolios they would receive. The end result was Myrkul gaining the portfolio of the Dead and Jergal became his\u00a0seneschal.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;, which Myrkul and Bane were the cause of, he was slain by &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt; inherited his portfolio as god of the dead thereafter. Unlike with the worshippers of Bane\u00a0and Bhaal, the transition went smoothly and without any notable tension, for they did not seem to care whose name they were invoking in prayer."}
{"id": "7929", "revid": "36786428", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7929", "title": "Mystra", "text": "Mystra, also known as the Lady of Mysteries, is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20good\"&gt;neutral good&lt;/a&gt; greater &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; of magic.\nShe was slain during the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;, but rose again shortly after through the mortal wizard Midnight. A large statue of her can be found on the ground floor in the &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50319", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50319", "title": "N'ashtar", "text": "N'ashtar is one of the &lt;a href=\"Adventuring%20Party%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Adventuring Party (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt; members encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nIf given enough time the Conjurer will self-buff and then begin casting offensive oriented spells at enemies. \nThis mage will be hostile whenever attacked or if you are in his range of detection. Note that the AI script for this creature is pretty well configured compared to many simple ones found in the basic game.\nAll the spells scripted for use are annotated in the InfoBox. Spells in memory but not scripted are omitted. \nHe'll most likely be able to apply a \"Tatoo of Power\" at the outset of battle and get up several protective spells before he can be struck - and they are not interruptible by damage. A &lt;a href=\"Mislead\"&gt;Mislead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;SI Evocation&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; are instantly cast. \nAfter that expect a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; spell cast upon the closest detected party member.\n&lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; will be attempted if hostile summoned creatures are detected.\nIf N'ashtar detects a mage class party member, then a &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Stun\"&gt;Power Word, Stun&lt;/a&gt; is scripted.\nThe mage has a couple of other contingency spell chains to use for protection such as &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe longer he survives the better chance he'll have to start casting offensive damage dealing spells such as Melf's Acid Arrow, Flame Arrow, Magic Missile and such.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes this mage. The Mage may be an Enchanter (randomly determined upon mod installation). Some new memorized spells are added, but no level 8 spells are provided. A minor sequencer and spell sequencer is prepared for instant use and are available to deploy via the SCS \"Improved Mages\" component. N'ashtar is granted one pip in quarterstaff weapon proficiency. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory. \nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, this creature's memorized spells and casts will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "51934", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51934", "title": "NISHRUU.ITM", "text": "NISHRUU.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by the &lt;a href=\"Nishruu\"&gt;Nishruu&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nGameplay.\nIt is considered a non-magical and unenchanted item and deals no damage, with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 0.\nIf the weapon lands a successful hit upon a target it applies two effects:\nThe first effect is to drain item charges (using &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 243). The coding for this attack means that items matching the 'Item Type' value on the targeted creature(s) will have their charges drained. It is coded so that Magical items including weapons will be drained of their charges. One charge will be drained from each item, per hit. \nThis includes items equipped by the target, and in the quick item use slots (such as wands or similar items). Items just sitting in the backpack slots or within a container (like a &lt;a href=\"Gem%20Bag\"&gt;Gem Bag&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt; won't be touched).\nThe second effect is to drain Wizard spells from the target (using Opcode 244). Drains spells from a wizard's memory. This effect always drains the highest-level possible spell first and drains the number set by the Number to Drain parameter. The weapon is set to drain 1 spell per hit.\nThe item also has a passive power that protects the user from the 5th wizard level spell &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to the &lt;a href=\"Nishruu\"&gt;Nishruu&lt;/a&gt; creature summoned by the spell &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Nishruu\"&gt;Summon Nishruu&lt;/a&gt;. The mod also revises this weapon item used by the creature.\nIt is now a +3 enchanted item that provides a -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus to hit. Any hit on a target does the same as the unmodified weapon, plus it applies a 3 round &lt;a href=\"Feeblemindedness\"&gt;Feeblemindedness&lt;/a&gt; effect that can't be resisted or blocked, although a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. spells will negate.\nThe item also provides passive extra immunities to the Nishruu that were not provided to the original creature (some coding omissions probably). This weapon makes the Nishruu immune to both &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt;. It also provides complete immunity to &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe last change made is the item furnishes the creature with a passive &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Illusion\"&gt;Detect Illusion&lt;/a&gt; percentage, that is always on, with a 20% chance of working per round. Any illusions in range of detection will be destroyed with a 20% chance of success - checked once per round."}
{"id": "56681", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56681", "title": "NOCIRC.ITM", "text": "NOCIRC.ITM is an undroppable ring that can be equipped by a non-player character/creature in the game.\nThe purpose of the item is to ensure the creature's default selection circle is removed, which is essentially a graphic blocking &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis feature is employed when the game/plot wishes to ensure a creature placed on an area map remains invisible and is not targetable.\nOther items may also be included in the creature's file to compliment this item."}
{"id": "34773", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34773", "title": "Naaman", "text": "Naaman is one of six servants of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, all of whom are located on the fifth floor of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and are under orders from Sarevok to eliminate &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; permanently. He will most likely be encountered during the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Investigating the Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and will fight alongside &lt;a href=\"Zhalimar%20Cloudwulfe\"&gt;Zhalimar Cloudwulfe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Aasim\"&gt;Aasim&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Alai\"&gt;Alai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diyab\"&gt;Diyab&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gardush\"&gt;Gardush&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; (in the guise of &lt;a href=\"Emissary%20Tar\"&gt;Emissary Tar&lt;/a&gt;).\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt;, Naaman has nothing to say.\nGameplay.\nNaaman and his associate Alai have the following spells memorized:\nCompared with Alai, Namaan only lacks the ability to cast &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;.\nNamaan will open combat by casting Shadow Door to turn invisible, then will begin casting Confusion at the nearest party member. After this, he will cast Flame Arrow, Horror, Melf's Acid Arrow, Agannazar's Scorcher, and Magic Missile at the nearest party member, in that order. Finally he will cast Chromatic Orb at the nearest party member who is not already stunned. Failing all of that, he will move to engage in melee combat."}
{"id": "8710", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8710", "title": "Nabassu", "text": "A Nabassu is a demon that can be summoned by the arcane conjuration spell &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt;, or as a result of a &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Surge\"&gt;Wild Surge&lt;/a&gt;. It can be quite dangerous to low-level parties. The creature depicted in this article is for the gated or conjured variety available to the player if summoned by spell, or by opponent spell casts.\nNote that other Nabassu creatures in the game will be mostly similar, and not different enough to warrant their own InfoBox.\nAs a gated demon, it will ignore creatures under &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Evil\"&gt;Protection From Evil&lt;/a&gt; and disappear after 2 turns. It cannot be banished by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;.\nOtherwise, it can attack its summoner. Its claws and bites work as &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; weapons +4, dealing 3D4 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;. It can innately see the invisible and regenerates 1 HP every 12 hours (which is probably a coding error).\nNabassu immunities can vary slightly from one creature type to the next, but they all possess an &lt;a href=\"RINGDEMN.ITM\"&gt;undroppable item&lt;/a&gt; in their ring slot which provides the following protections:\nBesides physical melee attacks, it has the following abilities available:\nOne party member of the player's choice may fight a Nabassu from the lower planes in the second match available in the beast fighting pit in the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha%20Tavern\"&gt;Ust Natha Tavern&lt;/a&gt;. Speak with &lt;a href=\"Szordrin\"&gt;Szordrin&lt;/a&gt; in the tavern to participate, and battle to the death for gold and the glory of Lolth.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod, and the \"Improved Fiends\" component will Improve the Nabassu as follows:\nNabassus (cast at 12th level):&lt;br&gt;\nPowerful silence spell (-5 to saves) once per day&lt;br&gt;\n\"Death gaze\" (damaging gaze attack) automatically, once per round (in addition to other powers)&lt;br&gt;\nTeleport without Error, Paralysis and Vampiric Touch, all at will&lt;br&gt;\nDamage Resistance: Cold and Fire 50%, Electricity 100%&lt;br&gt;\nAdjusted THAC0: 7\nThe creature also gets a different color scheme and has a unique appearance to differentiate it from some other fiends using the same animation in the game. The mod version of the Nabassu's Silence innate spell will be launched at any mage, bard or cleric class (including sub varieties and dual and multi class) spell casters. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod replaces the &lt;a href=\"Cacofiend\"&gt;Cacofiend&lt;/a&gt; spell with a &lt;a href=\"https%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/arcane/level-7/summon-death-knight\"&gt;\"Summon Death Knight\"&lt;/a&gt; alternate, and thus, the Nabassu won't be available via summoned magic by the player or opponent mages. See the Cacofiend spell page for details.\nExternal links.\nSwitch immunity reference article from Demon to RINGDEMN.ITM"}
