{"id": "6158", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6158", "title": "Nalia abducted by Isaea Roenall", "text": "Nalia abducted by Isaea Roenall is &lt;a href=\"Nalia%20de%27Arnise\"&gt;Nalia's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest during the \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign.\nQuest Prerequisite.\nIn order for this quest to set up properly and eventually initiate it stems from part of the &lt;a href=\"The%20de%27Arnise%20Keep%20has%20been%20Invaded\"&gt;The de'Arnise Keep has been Invaded&lt;/a&gt; questline. Nalia must be in the party at the time when &lt;a href=\"TorGal\"&gt;TorGal&lt;/a&gt; is killed. It is optional for Nalia to have dialogue with TorGal, although there is much voice acting and content available if done. This sets the game file GLOBALs appropriately so that the Nalia abduction questline can initiate. It is not necessary to have Nalia in the party continuously after these files are set. She could be temporarily removed. and added back to the party later, if desired. But at some point, she must be added to the party again for the quest to proceed, and the messenger to spawn and deliver the letter. See the walkthrough below.\nWalkthrough.\nNalia has no other quests in the unmodified game. She can be removed from the party and added again later, over and over as desired."}
{"id": "4492", "revid": "277958", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4492", "title": "Nalia de'Arnise", "text": "Nalia de'Arnise is a chaotic good &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Dual-class\"&gt;dual-class&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; (level 4) \u2192 &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in \nNalia's family castle is under attack by &lt;a href=\"trolls\"&gt;trolls&lt;/a&gt; with a higher intelligence than average for their kind, and she needs a group of adventurers who can take back the castle and save family members who are possibly held captive.\nRecruitment.\nNalia\u00a0is available to recruit from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. She can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; inn in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe can be acquired as a level 9/4 Mage/Thief, with &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiencies&lt;/a&gt; in: Short Sword, Dagger, Quarter Staff, and Short Bow.\nIn the enhanced edition game, she can be acquired as a level 9/4 Mage/Thief, with &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiencies&lt;/a&gt; in: Dagger, Dart, Quarterstaff, Short Sword and Short Bow.\nGameplay.\nNalia is an immediate replacement for &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;, who is abducted as soon as the party escapes from the starting dungeon. She doesn't have &lt;a href=\"Imoen%23Gameplay\"&gt;special powers&lt;/a&gt; like Imoen (but these powers aren't unlocked until the last chapters of the game), and her thieving skills are slightly lower, but she makes up for it by being in the possession of a unique &lt;a href=\"de%27Arnise%20Signet%20Ring\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;, which grants 2 bonus points to her &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; and to all her &lt;a href=\"saving%20throw\"&gt;saving throw&lt;/a&gt;s, plus 50% resistance to fire, and can be worn together with other protection items. Nalia is also available very early in the game, with the potential to gain much more &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;XP&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile her thief skills aren't impressive, being a thief dual-class does allow her to equip the &lt;a href=\"Dak%27kon%27s%20Zerth%20Blade\"&gt;Dak'kon's Zerth Blade&lt;/a&gt;.\nPersonality.\nNalia was of a particularly charitable bent. She was appalled at the unfairness of the class system in her country and others like it, and consequently very preoccupied with helping the needy, to the point of criticizing charity that was too small. She insisted that she did not \"go slumming\", and thought she was really in touch with the people she was trying to help, but she had some difficulty shaking off the feeling of superiority she was raised with, and was seen as well-intentioned but not so good as she thought she was.\nBelow are excerpts of conversation taken from the game to help characterize Nalia:\nHer discontent with the current class system is also reflected by her aversion to Amn's various churches and what is done with the donations poor people give to them to better their lives. This is shown when visiting Keldorn's house, which is quite the Villa bought and paid for by the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt;. But no matter how much she hates the system, she loves her Aunty and can accept that her generation \"is set in their ways\"."}
