{"id": "34933", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34933", "title": "Naljier Skal", "text": "Naljier Skal is an unhinged &lt;a href=\"bard\"&gt;bard&lt;/a&gt; who can be found amongst the inmates at &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; during the course of Baldur's Gate II: Shadowns of Amn.\nHistory.\nNaljier Skal was apparently once a bard of some repute and a skilled mage who was known to conduct experiments into planar travel and divination. From what little is known, he attempted to work some magic to divine what lays \"beyond the gods\", and, according to &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;, something apparently didn't like him looking. He was struck by a magical malady that reduced him to the mental level of a child, but still possessing his full magical capabilities, a dangerous combination that saw him banished to Spellhold.\nHe is killed as part of the efforts by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their friends to defeat Jon Irenicus, falling in battle against the cursed elven archmage.\nGameplay.\nThe player can interact with Naljier Skal when they first arrive at the Main Floor for Spellhold. Either \"The Coordinator\" will introduce them to Naljier as he gives them a tour of the asylum's inmates, or they can encounter Naljier as they explore the common rooms once &lt;a href=\"Lonk\"&gt;Lonk&lt;/a&gt; lets them out of their cells.\nIf the player talks to Naljier during this stage, and brings up the topic of \"pretties\", he will give the player a random gemstone. This even can occur several times and is driven by dialogue and interest in his ramblings. After several gems are produced, he loses interest, and the free gemstones cease. No more pretties for the party.\nWhile in the cellblock, Naljier is equipped with a &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; to prevent death and for plot purposes. Once he's involved in the battle with Irenicus later in the adventure, he is vulnerable. Like all the other inmates who participate in that fight, their death is a scripted certainty. \nNaljier has no scripted use of mage spells in the unmodified game and carries no weaponry. When the bard goes into the battle against Irenicus with the other inmates and the party, Naljier can't contribute anything meaningful. He has no bard song use either.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes revisions to this bard so that it can contribute some spellcasting during the battle with Irenicus.\nNaljier is provided an AI script that allows an opening \"previously cast\" trigger that applies &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;. If able, he can cast &lt;a href=\"Glitterdust\"&gt;Glitterdust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; and \"Icelance\" (if the IWD spell component is also installed). A \"Soundburst\" spell will be attempted with the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed.\nTwp potions for quaffing are supplied and scripted for use during the battle. One for boosting protections and the other to heal damage. No melee weapon is given for fighting."}
{"id": "34729", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34729", "title": "Nalmissra", "text": "Nalmissra will spawn when the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20Key\"&gt;Heart Key&lt;/a&gt; is turned to unlock the western pedestal in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon.\nShe is a Succubus, wielding her enchantments and charms to beguile and control her enemies.\nGameplay.\nNalmissra can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe's also under a permanent &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Improved Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nLike many demons, she has several &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status effect&lt;/a&gt; immunities and a formidable &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nAfter she applies her two buffs when she first sees an enemy. she then \"ForceSpell\" launches a &lt;a href=\"Mass%20Charm%20Person%20%28SPIN553%29\"&gt;mass Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; spell at the nearest target to her, which may expose other party members in the 15' radius area of effect to a Dire Charm and a few other short-term effects. A saving throw with a penalty can negate this, as well as other potential protections, see the spell link for details. \nIt is unlikely she will be able to do this again, as there is a long delay between her ability to cast this spell a second time, but it is possible if the party doesn't put her down in for a few turns.\nHer only other threat to the party is her potent touch attack - although she is a fragile opponent in melee combat and can't take a beating.\nIf she is able to connect with her touch attack, then several bad outcomes can afflict the victim - See the on-hit effects in the InfoBox or the Touch weapon link.\nUpon death she drops a rare &lt;a href=\"Wish\"&gt;Wish scroll&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Diamond\"&gt;Diamond&lt;/a&gt; and two random treasures.\nBugs.\nNalmissra's regeneration ability timing mode is set as permanent, but that setting requires a duration to work, and it has no duration, and therefore it doesn't operate correctly. This is an issue throughout the game in several other creatures as well. This issue is included in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt; and is already identified to Beamdog for possible fixing in the future.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Nalmissra, and especially with the \"Improved Fiends and Celestials\" component.\nShe now will behave as a powerful succubus, and her abilities reflect this.\nA &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; is added to her initial buffs. The permanent Improved haste effect is removed, but a movement modifier bonus of +9 is added.\nThe Mass charm person spell is removed, and she instead can cast the powerful single-target &lt;a href=\"Succubus%20charm%20male\"&gt;Succubus charm male&lt;/a&gt; spell, and this can and will be done much more often and she has an endless supply. Despite its title it can work on Male or Female persons, but her AI mainly looks for male targets.\nShe can also heal herself with innate version of &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Critical%20Wounds\"&gt;Cure Critical Wounds&lt;/a&gt; at certain damage thresholds and can be imitated as required if the condition trigger is applicable.\n\"Teleport without error\" is also a used ability. It is often employed to escape from being pounded in melee, to jump across the map to a vulnerable foe, and other reasons.\nShe also gets the &lt;a href=\"Ethereal\"&gt;Ethereal&lt;/a&gt; power, triggered by wounds or spell failure. She'll regenerate, be invisible, and gain extra magic resistance. It is resistant to being destroyed by divination and can't be dispelled."}
{"id": "6792", "revid": "283088", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6792", "title": "Namarra", "text": "Namarra is an enchanted longsword +2, but unlike a &lt;a href=\"Long%20Sword%20%2B2\"&gt;Long Sword +2&lt;/a&gt;, it has +4 damage bonus instead of +2, but they have the same weight of 3 lbs, both a speed factor of 3 and -2 THAC0 bonus. This weapon can also be used to cast &lt;a href=\"Silence%2C%2015%27%20Radius\"&gt;Silence, 15' Radius&lt;/a&gt; three times every day, which makes it useful against spellcasters.\nThis item appears in and . It can be found in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt;. It is wielded by the &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20King\"&gt;Crypt King&lt;/a&gt; in the tomb next to the entrance of Bodhi's Lair, who drops it upon being slain."}
