{"id": "18589", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18589", "title": "Near Infinity", "text": "Near Infinity (NI for short) is an open source file browser and editor for resources of &lt;a href=\"Infinity%20Engine\"&gt;Infinity Engine&lt;/a&gt; games, such as &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt; or and their Enhanced Edition counterparts. It has been written in Java and can therefore be used on any platform supported by Java, which includes Windows, Mac OS X and Linux. The source code is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License."}
{"id": "6683", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6683", "title": "Neb", "text": "Neb is a &lt;a href=\"Gnome\"&gt;gnomish&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; serial killer who plays minor roles in both \"Baldur's Gate\" and \"Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn\".\n\"Baldur's Gate\".\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", Neb is a storyline-important NPC who the party encounters when they are thrown into the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; cells in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf repeatedly talked to, Neb boasts about how he was incarcerated for murdering street children, and reveals he has a hidden way to escape the cells. To proceed, the player must answer his riddle; his default riddle is a number's puzzle, asking how many children he has killed (correct answer is 33). If the player fails, he offers two other, easier ones.\nOnce the party is free, Neb escapes back into Baldur's Gate. As the second game reveals, he subsequently makes his bloody way to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nNeb cannot be killed; if attacked he automatically will give you the \"key\" and disappear.\n\"Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn\".\nIn \"\", Neb is a minor NPC who appears if the player agrees to undertake the &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Sarles the Sculptor&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nIf the player chooses to investigate the merchant &lt;a href=\"Unger%20Hilldark\"&gt;Unger Hilldark&lt;/a&gt; after speaking to &lt;a href=\"Jerlia\"&gt;Jerlia&lt;/a&gt;, he will, if approached nicely, explain that he was robbed by Neb, and directs the party to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Illithium%20Ore\"&gt;Illithium Ore&lt;/a&gt; from the malevolent gnome if they want it so badly.\nNeb dwells within his locked lair in a &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20House\"&gt;Derelict House&lt;/a&gt; that's located at the western end of the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen approached, Evil characters can agree to trade Neb's life for the Illithium, but if Minsc or Jaheira are present in the party, then they recognize Neb as a child murderer from Baldur's Gate and force a confrontation.\nIn battle, Neb is aided by a number of &lt;a href=\"Child%20Spirit\"&gt;Child Spirits&lt;/a&gt;, entities spawned from his victims. If the party kills Neb, each Child Spirit left alive is released to the Outer Planes, rewarding the party with and a &lt;a href=\"Pearl\"&gt;Pearl&lt;/a&gt; per surviving Child Spirit.\nNeb's corpse has his &lt;a href=\"Neb%27s%20Head\"&gt;head&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Neb%27s%20Nasty%20Cutter\"&gt;Neb's Nasty Cutter&lt;/a&gt; (a unique Dagger of Poison), and the Illithium Ore as loot. His head can be given to &lt;a href=\"Chief%20Inspector%20Brega\"&gt;Chief Inspector Brega&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Six%20Building\"&gt;Council of Six Building&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt;, for 2500 and a +1 increase to your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of the \"&lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG2\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" mod can add some extended and possibly restored content regarding Unger Hilldark and the &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple&lt;/a&gt; Illithium questline.\nTrivia.\nThe games are oddly inconsistent about of what &lt;a href=\"race\"&gt;race&lt;/a&gt; Neb actually is. The first game implies he is a gnome, but in the second game, he is alternately referred to as a gnome or as a &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt;. Unger Hilldark describes him as \"looking like a hill dwarf\", and his severed head is described as coming from \"Neb the dwarf\", but he uses a gnome sprite and voice clips, is considered a gnome by the game engine and is referred to as a gnome in the &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; and by the government officials to whom his head is delivered."}
{"id": "13503", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13503", "title": "Neb's Head", "text": "Neb's Head is a quest item in \"\". It can be turned in to &lt;a href=\"Chief%20Inspector%20Brega\"&gt;Chief Inspector Brega&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Council%20of%20Six%20Building\"&gt;Council of Six Building&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Government%20District\"&gt;Government District&lt;/a&gt; for 2500 gold and 1 &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocation.\nDropped by &lt;a href=\"Neb\"&gt;Neb&lt;/a&gt; in a &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20House\"&gt;Derelict House&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;.\nRelated quests.\n&lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nA renowned sculptor is visiting &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, and several local temples are vying to procure his services to increase their prestige."}
{"id": "6968", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6968", "title": "Neb's Nasty Cutter", "text": "Neb's Nasty Cutter is a Magical &lt;a href=\"dagger\"&gt;dagger&lt;/a&gt; +2 able to inflict a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt;effect (and, in the original edition of , a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt; as well) if the target doesn't &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs Death. The Nasty Cutter can only do this 10 times, after which it becomes nothing more than a normal &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B2\"&gt;Dagger +2&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item appears in and . This dagger is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Neb\"&gt;Neb&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20House\"&gt;Derelict House&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Gain%20the%20services%20of%20Sir%20Sarles%20for%20the%20temple\"&gt;Gain the services of Sir Sarles for the temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nWhile looking like a random made-up design, the weapon is actually modeled after an African weapon called the mambele. It was used as both a melee and thrown weapon, and varied greatly in shape and size."}
