{"id": "5468", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5468", "title": "Negative Plane Protection", "text": "Negative Plane Protection is a 4th level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It protects the target creature from any form of &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt does not protect against &lt;a href=\"Ability%20Scores\"&gt;Ability Scores&lt;/a&gt; drain such a &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Troll\"&gt;Spirit Troll&lt;/a&gt;'s, a &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Troll\"&gt;Spectral Troll&lt;/a&gt;'s or a &lt;a href=\"Shadow\"&gt;Shadow&lt;/a&gt;'s, which drain strength, or a &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;Mind Flayer&lt;/a&gt;'s, which drains intellect.\nSee also.\nOther necessary protection spells from Priests:\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this Divine spell, revising its duration, casting time, and description. See below:\nNegative Plane Protection\nLevel: 4\nSchool: Abjuration\nSphere: Necromantic, Protection\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen a Negative Plane Protection spell is cast, the recipient receives complete protection from negative energy attacks. This spell also affords the recipient partial protection from monsters with Negative Energy plane connections (such as vampires) and certain weapons and spells that drain levels. A protected creature is immune to any form of level draining for the duration of the spell, though they will still suffer normal hit point damage from the physical attacks, if applicable."}
