{"id": "8191", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8191", "title": "Nelleck", "text": "Nelleck is a village guard and a resident of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party travels to the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; area for the first time, perhaps because &lt;a href=\"Delon\"&gt;Delon&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Athkatla Government&lt;/a&gt; district has asked for help for the village of &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt;, Its likely that Nelleck will be observed in a public gathering and asking the Mayor about the current crisis.\nAfter the crowd disperses, the party can speak with Nelleck and ask some questions and perhaps get filled in on what's going on, what Nelleck thinks is the issue, and what he thinks is bunk.\nHe will tell you he believes wolves are responsible for the disappearances in the village.\nIf the party undertakes the &lt;a href=\"Idle%20hands%20in%20Imnesvale\"&gt;Idle hands in Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; side quest, Nelleck has some commentary at the conclusion of the quest if spoken to."}
