{"id": "43947", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43947", "title": "Nereid", "text": "Nereids are a race of water-dwelling fey, distantly related to &lt;a href=\"dryad\"&gt;dryad&lt;/a&gt;s and similar to &lt;a href=\"sirine\"&gt;sirine&lt;/a&gt;s. Like dryads, they are powerful spellcasters, combining an innate ability for &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; spells with an arsenal of combat spells.\nIn Baldur's Gate.\nA single nereid, &lt;a href=\"Shoal%20the%20Nereid\"&gt;Shoal&lt;/a&gt;, appears at the &lt;a href=\"Shipwreck%27s%20Coast\"&gt;Shipwreck's Coast&lt;/a&gt;, though she counts as a , rather than a .\nIn Siege of Dragonspear.\nAnother nereid can be encountered during the events of as part of the quest &lt;a href=\"Strunk%27s%20Elementals\"&gt;Strunk's Elementals&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "29204", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29204", "title": "Nereids", "text": ""}
{"id": "54939", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54939", "title": "Nerit", "text": "Nerit is an NPC during the \"\"saga and the enhanced edition.\nGameplay.\nNerit only appears during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; with three other paladins, including &lt;a href=\"Eric%20Vanstraaten\"&gt;Eric Vanstraaten&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sir%20William%20Reirrac\"&gt;William Reirrac&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Branet%20Al-Thon\"&gt;Branet Al-Thon&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe paladin's appearance only occurs if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; asked for assistance against the vampire coven when seeing &lt;a href=\"Prelate%20Wessalen\"&gt;Prelate Wessalen&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Most%20Noble%20Order%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart%20building\"&gt;Most Noble Order of the Radiant Heart building&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the Prelate agreed, then all the paladins will appear in the first chamber entered when the party descends into the catacombs.\nNerit is not controllable by the player, but the creature's script will follow the PC and engage in melee combat with red circled enemies when they are detected.\nThe paladin actions are centered around combat outcomes with &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt; vampires while the party is present in the same area. When those two are defeated, Erik Van Straaten will dismiss Nerit, William and Branet and they'll depart the area.\nThe paladin warriors are not configured with any of the Paladin passive resistances or use of innate abilities such &lt;a href=\"Lay%20on%20Hands%20%28paladin%29\"&gt;Lay on Hands (paladin)&lt;/a&gt;, nor do they have use of any cleric spells.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a revised fighter style AI script to the paladin in Chapter 6. It allows for application of three SCS potions readied for quaffing during hostilities. Additionally, 2 pips in single weapon fighting style are added to the creature's weapon proficiency."}
