{"id": "48497", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48497", "title": "Nishruu", "text": "Nishruu are extra-planar creatures sometimes called \"magic-eaters\" and are also related to a more vicious sub-race known as &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt;.\nNishruu can be summoned, either by the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt;, or by , using the 6th level &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; spell &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Nishruu\"&gt;Summon Nishruu&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe AI script for a Nishruu looks for spell casters in sight \u2013 first for all mage classes and mage multi-classes, then bards, then clerics, and finally druid classes. It has to get within melee range and connect with its attack in order to cause any magic draining effects.\nLiterally any spell cast on the Nishruu, even an area of effect spell, will cause a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Light%20Wounds%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Cure Light Wounds (spell)&lt;/a&gt; effect on the creature. A party-summoned Nishruu could be healed by the player by exposing it to a spell effect that would normally affect a companion or enemy.\nThe creature can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nNotes.\nItem Drains.\nRules for draining items aren't clear. For example:\nWands whose charges are depleted to 0 through this means will be destroyed. Magically conjured projectiles such as &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Minute%20Meteors\"&gt;Melf's Minute Meteors&lt;/a&gt; are not drained. Items stored in a &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt; are not drained.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, a Nishruu and &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; can be destroyed with three specific spells other than &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt;. Both can be slain by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28priest%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (priest)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Dispel Magic (wizard)&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Other forms of Dispel magic won't work, such as the &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt; Dispel magic innate ability.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod installed (with or without SCS) the Nishruu included in the game files is changed (and the &lt;a href=\"Hakeashar\"&gt;Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; is removed from the game, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; spell).\nNishruu (9 Hit Dice):\nSTR -, DEX 10, CON 16, INT 13, WIS 15, CHA 13; AL Chaotic Neutral\nHP 90, AC 10, THAC0 7, Saving Throws 8/8/8/8/8\n1 Attack Per Round, Drain Magic (Contact +3)\nCombat Abilities:\nDrain Magic:\nwizards lose one memorized spell, chosen at random from the highest spell level possible\nany creature touched must save vs. spell or suffer feeblemindedness for 3 rounds\nSpecial Qualities:\nAbsorb Magic: immune to magic, every spell cast against a Nishruu heals the creature by 1d8+1 hit points\nPhysical Resistance 50%"}
{"id": "8142", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8142", "title": "Nivek", "text": "Nivek can be found in one of the &lt;a href=\"Warehouses%20%28south%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1207\"&gt;warehouse&lt;/a&gt; buildings in the district of &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will warn &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; about a &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Basilisk\"&gt;basilisk&lt;/a&gt; on the loose inside the warehouse and run away."}
{"id": "6179", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6179", "title": "Nizidramanii'yt", "text": "Nizidramanii'yt is a black dragon that &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; persuaded to transport him and aid in the attack &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;. Under Irenicus' command, Nizidramanii'yt is now tasked with guarding the &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Goblet%20of%20Life\"&gt;Golden Goblet of Life&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20Clearing\"&gt;Forest Clearing&lt;/a&gt; to prevent anyone from reaching him whilst draining the &lt;a href=\"Tree%20of%20Life\"&gt;Tree of Life&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen the party moves into the clearing, a massive black dragon is eventually observed, which is neutral at the moment. When the beast has detected a party member (it can see invisible or hidden creatures) it will immediately challenge the intruders and begin with a rumbling remark that the party is viewed as a source of food. \nThis leads to a series of dialogue choices between the dragon and party spokesperson. As is usual for dragons, they have a sense of ego and self-worth that may be arrogant or display an air of confident superiority. It is obvious that Nizidramanii'yt is not entirely satisfied with his status as a hired soldier for Irenicus. \nThe party can explore this fact, and perhaps come to an agreement, or bargain if you will, to obtain the sought after &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Goblet%20of%20Life\"&gt;Golden Goblet of Life&lt;/a&gt; that the party seeks. \nTo bargain with it for the Goblet you have to have at least 30,000 gold and choose the correct dialogue options. If the party doesn't have sufficient funds, the dialogue option doesn't appear. Then all your gold and most inventory carried will be exchanged for the Goblet. Once the dialogue choice is made and the correct conditions are met, the game script will initiate the \"Blackdragon items\" global from 1, to 2, and execute the \"Destroy All Destructible Equipment\" code. However, the following items will not be taken from the party:\nThis bargain is really not a good deal, as the party by this stage of the saga isn't so weak that a lone dragon should dictate the party's actions and prevent their goals. If the party chooses to fight its way through, then there are obvious dialogue paths to accomplish this. Most likely if you can get the dragon to reply with:\n\"Then I will kill you as I should have done the moment I saw you. Mere cattle should not be bargained with.\"\nThe battle will now begin, and the dragon becomes a hostile creature.\nThe dragon opens with a burst of uninterruptible force cast spells including &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; on self and a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; on the nearest opponent within range (also possibly exposing other party members in the AoE).\nIt will shortly afterwards radiate a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Fear\"&gt;Dragon Fear&lt;/a&gt; aura and spew a full-throated &lt;a href=\"Black%20Dragon%20Breath\"&gt;Black Dragon Breath&lt;/a&gt; at the nearest party member, followed by a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnyone in the party in melee range will be a target for the beast's claw attacks, and with the Haste effect on (if not dispelled earlier) it will be 4 &lt;a href=\"attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; plus 2 off-hand slashing attacks. Both types count as +5 weapons.\nEvery three rounds the dragon will blast another acidic dragon breath attack on a timed interval.\nIf the dragon's original Hit Point total decreases to 50%, then an automatic contingency will deploy that will cast a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell on itself.\nIf the dragon is still alive and functioning after several rounds, it will deploy two other innate abilities, beginning with &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Insects%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Summon Insects (innate)&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe insect swarm will spread to most party members on the map.\nA long time into the battle, perhaps never occurring if the beast is slain in less than a turn, will be an attempted &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt; innate ability - sort of like a powerful &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; effect. The party may never face this ability since it is only used after a long period of time from the start of hostilities.\nThe cycle of dragon breath attacks and additional wing buffets will continue, and there is a 35% chance the dragon will attempt a &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Person\"&gt;Charm Person&lt;/a&gt; spell as well.\nThat is the gist of the scripted abilities of this dragon. Be wary of its potent acid breath attack, as protection from acid is difficult in the game, without being a Mage, or having access to the green &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Acid%20%28protection%20scroll%29\"&gt;Protection From Acid (protection scroll)&lt;/a&gt;. Oddly enough, the dragon is not scripted to do anything special against summoned creatures - it has no &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or banishment ability.\nDefeating the dragon will give access to the creature's carried hoard, and the required &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Goblet%20of%20Life\"&gt;artifact&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchievements.\nBlack Dragon Slayer Achievement icon BG2EE.jpg|\nBlack Dragon Slayer.\nSlew the black dragon, Nizidramanii'yt.\nMod Content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Nizidramanii'yt in several ways. Especially if you install the \"Smarter Dragons\" component (which is responsive to the game difficulty selection). His SCS AI improves targeting and recognition of opponent's protections, which means he will fight smarter and not waste attacks on someone he cannot hit or damage. It will also influence his tactical options and attack methods. First, some mention of the dragon's stats and abilities. In most cases, all of the unmodded ones are still applicable:\nImmunities in addition to the unmodified dragon version:\nThe dragon follows the unmodified game script closely, however depending on the game difficulty selection, will perform breath attacks more frequently (every two rounds). Additionally, the dragon is able to cast &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt; twice each. Instead of charm person it can cast &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Charm\"&gt;Dire Charm&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf any cloud type spells are cast at the dragon, including &lt;a href=\"Incendiary%20Cloud\"&gt;Incendiary Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, then the script will initiate a Wing Buffet to clear it from the map.\nWith SCS, dragon breath weapons are not assigned to any school of magic and have no secondary type - so the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; has no effect, nor will &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Shield\"&gt;Spell Shield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; and similar protections have any interaction.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod adds \"The Manual of Golem Building Vol. 5\" to the dragon's carried loot. Party mage can now build a variety of &lt;a href=\"Adamantite%20Golem\"&gt;Adamantite Golem&lt;/a&gt; golems with the correct components and XP levels."}
