{"id": "45725", "revid": "283209", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45725", "title": "N\u00fcber", "text": "N\u00fcber is a character in \"\". After many repeated dialog conversations, he will eventually remember that he left his boot in his house. You will earn for your perserverance. With force-talk and the space key, you can rapidly progress through his conversations and move on without too much annoyance. \nAlternatively, if you kill the man before he has finished his set of talks, he will rise again as an undead, and continue talking to you. If you kill him again (before being rewarded with the aforementioned 1,000 XP for your patience), he will rise once more, still capable of speech. As the sum-total of all three N\u00fcbers is worth only 250 XP, it is more lucrative to just listen to him to the end. Killing him is therefore for pleasure, not profit. \nTrivia.\nHe is likely a homage to &lt;a href=\"Noober\"&gt;Noober&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Neeber\"&gt;Neeber&lt;/a&gt; from previous released games. "}
{"id": "49426", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49426", "title": "OGRE1.ITM", "text": "OGRE1.ITM is an undroppable weapon used by Summoned Ogres (typically in the Weapon 1 slot).\nEffects.\nIt is considered a &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; Morning Star of &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchantment&lt;/a&gt; level 1, and deals 1d10 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; bonus ), with a range of one foot, and speed factor of 3."}
{"id": "53073", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53073", "title": "OHRGEM01.ITM", "text": ""}
{"id": "53895", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53895", "title": "OTYUGH.ITM", "text": "OTYUGH.ITM is an undroppable melee weapon used by various &lt;a href=\"Otyugh\"&gt;Otyugh&lt;/a&gt; creatures. It is placed in one of the creature's \"Quick Weapon\" slots.\nIt is considered a magical and +3 enchanted item and deals 1d8 damage (adjusted by &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; modifier), with a range of two feet, and speed factor of 1.\nIn addition to the crushing damage, each hit inflicts a &lt;a href=\"Disease\"&gt;Disease&lt;/a&gt;, that offers no &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; nor is it blocked by magic resistance or spell protections. The effect last for 90 seconds (15 rounds).\nThe disease causes 1 damage every round (this is &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt;). It also infects the target with a &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;. \nMultiple strikes from an otyugh's attack will cumulatively apply the poison damage and refresh the duration of the &lt;a href=\"slow%20effect\"&gt;slow effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nRemoving the disease before it runs its course can be achieved with a &lt;a href=\"Cure%20Disease\"&gt;Cure Disease&lt;/a&gt; spell or item which applies a cure disease effect. \nA target that is successfully struck by this weapon will have two icons assigned to the creature's portrait (No. 7) \"Nauseated\" and (No. 41) \"Slow\". If the target is explicitly immune to disease effects then these icons are blocked.\nCoding of the weapon also provides immunity to certain creatures that are not affected by disease or poison damage, for better scripting behavior."}
