{"id": "19608", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19608", "title": "Odamaron", "text": "Odamaron is a &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Sendai's Enclave&lt;/a&gt; and specifically this area &lt;a href=\"Sendai%27s%20Lair%E2%80%94Odamaron\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. If attacked Odamaron will have no mercy upon your party, and your intrusion shall not go unpunished. This lich will open up hostilities with defensive magics, followed by offensive magical attacks of the highest order. Additionally, Odamaron is not particularly subservient to Sendai, and even states that he \"tolerates\" her, and will reevaluate the relationship after he destroys you, the intruding Bhaalspawn. \nAbilities.\nAll liches, including Odamaron, are naturally immune to non-magical weapons and &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; effects between 1 through 5.\nOdamaron can see hidden and invisible creatures by script.\nThis lich is equipped with three undroppable items which bestow the creature's immunities and protections, and its melee touch attack. These are:&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"RING95.ITM\"&gt;RING95.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for the general Undead protections. See the item link for specifics.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"LICH.ITM\"&gt;LICH.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for lich specific protections. See the item link for specifics.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"LICH02.ITM\"&gt;LICH02.ITM&lt;/a&gt; for the touch attack melee weapon. See the item link for specifics.&lt;br&gt; \nThere is some overlap in immunities with two of the items worn together. \nGameplay.\nAfter a cut scene plays out when the party enters the Lich's abode, Odamaron will have eventually decided that he has had enough of the party's pathetic dialogue, it will rasp:\n\"Come, my servants... wake and taste fresh blood.\"\nOdamaron will then instantly force cast a group of defensive buffs to include, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;. A few tics later, a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; will be applied, and then a &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the Time Stop, the lich will release a spell trigger with &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; to remove illusions, &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; to banish summoned creatures.\nIf the lich takes any damage, it will reapply another Stoneskin and a Protection from magical Weapons. It can also use a &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Red%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Red)&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt some point in the battle not too far after casting some Symbol spells it will apply a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Door\"&gt;Shadow Door&lt;/a&gt; and perhaps a &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Efreeti\"&gt;Summon Efreeti&lt;/a&gt;.\nVarious damage dealing and disabling type spells will be attempted, as shown in the InfoBox.\nAll of the memorized spells listed in the InfoBox are scripted for use.\nOdamaron't AI script is not coded to recognize party protections or vulnerabilities, it just attempts cast spells from memory at mainly the nearest detected target. The party can use this to their advantage by protecting one party member very well, and the other members attacking from afar.\nIn his possession is the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Heart of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Eye%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Eye of Tyr&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod will change the lich's spellbook to the SR versions. This Mod is compatible and designed to work with SCS."}
{"id": "4559", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4559", "title": "Odd-looking Key", "text": "The Odd-looking Key, also known as Odd Looking Key in , can be found within the 1st level of the dungeon in &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. It is necessary for opening a warded chest on the same level. Inside the chest are several items of treasure and some gold, along with the &lt;a href=\"Switch%20for%20an%20Engine\"&gt;Switch for an Engine&lt;/a&gt;, which is needed to activate the nearby steam engine.\nPlayers should be careful not to put the key into the warded chest, or the chest will be locked along with all items inside without any means except console to open it.\nGallery.\nBulder's Gate TOSC images"}
