{"id": "56593", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56593", "title": "AURSTAF.ITM", "text": "The AURSTAF.ITM is a unfroppable quarterstaff provided to &lt;a href=\"Aurumach%20Rilmani\"&gt;Aurumach Rilmani&lt;/a&gt; as the creatures melee weapon\nIt is similar to a &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20the%20Ram\"&gt;Staff of the Ram&lt;/a&gt; but has some differences as well.\nGameplay.\nThe weapon is a +3 enchanted quarterstaff with a reach of 2 feet, and a weapon speed factor of 1.\nEach successful hit can inflict 1d6+3 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and the weapon provides a 3 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus.\nAny successful hit exposes the target to a potential &lt;a href=\"Slow%20effect\"&gt;Slow effect&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell with a -2 penalty is required to negate it.\nIf the save is missed, the victim is slowed for 3 rounds - the effect can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, but the effect is a 0 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, so no spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; will provide any defense.\nAt the same time, the target is subjected to a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt;, or \"knockback\" effect - moving the victim away from the attacker up to 20 feet distance.\nIt takes 2 seconds for the knockback effect to finish, and the victim is also rendered &lt;a href=\"Unconscious\"&gt;Unconscious&lt;/a&gt; for 3 seconds.\nOnly immunity to the unconscious status effect can block this.\nA party member slowed by this staff will display a \"Slow\" status effect icon on their portrait for the duration.\nEquipping this staff provides some passive defenses, including protection from level 1-4 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; spells/effects, and immunity to 6 ammunition projectiles fired from missile weapons or thrown, such as Arrow, Throwing Axe, Bolt, Bullet, Throwing Dagger, and Dart."}
