{"id": "29782", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29782", "title": "A Corpse for Arkion", "text": "A Corpse for Arkion is a &lt;a href=\"Side%20Quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; given by &lt;a href=\"Arkion\"&gt;Arkion&lt;/a&gt; in his house in &lt;a href=\"east%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;east Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He will only give this quest to the party if a character with a low reaction / charisma speaks to him, otherwise he will view the speaker with suspicion.\nObjective.\n&lt;a href=\"Arkion\"&gt;Arkion&lt;/a&gt; asks the player to bring him a corpse. Arkion will accept as many corpses as you can bring him; however, he will only increase the reward for delivering more than one body, regardless of whether you bring him two or seven.\nWalkthrough.\nExit &lt;a href=\"Arkion%27s%20Home\"&gt;Arkion's Home&lt;/a&gt; then travel north-west toward &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;, behind the shop you will find &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20Sewers%20East\"&gt;Baldur's Gate Sewers East&lt;/a&gt; entrance. Be careful when descending into the sewer because an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage%23Baldur.27s%2520Gate\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt; as well as several &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Crawler\"&gt;Carrion Crawlers&lt;/a&gt; may be present. Directly west of the ladder will be four corpse shaped containers each with a &lt;a href=\"Male%20Body\"&gt;Male Body&lt;/a&gt; or a &lt;a href=\"Female%20Body\"&gt;Female Body&lt;/a&gt;. Bring one corpse to Arkion to complete the side quest earning and , or bring him at least two corpses to earn 1800 XP and .\nThe Ogre Mage and Carrion Crawlers, as well as the item &lt;a href=\"Sashenstar%27s%20Ruby%20Ring\"&gt;Sashenstar's Ruby Ring&lt;/a&gt; found with one of the corpses, are part of the &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;Quest&lt;/a&gt; : &lt;a href=\"Missing%20Citizens\"&gt;Missing Citizens&lt;/a&gt;. A cluster of Carrion Crawlers may spawn in this area whether you have completed &lt;a href=\"Missing%20Citizens\"&gt;Missing Citizens&lt;/a&gt; or not."}
