{"id": "5961", "revid": "272153", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5961", "title": "A Mage's Proposal", "text": "This is a side quest available in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. You have just freed &lt;a href=\"Vithal\"&gt;Vithal&lt;/a&gt; in the previous &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%20Imprisoned%3F\"&gt;A Mage Imprisoned?&lt;/a&gt; quest and given a bit of experience. But the mage came here with a purpose...\nGameplay.\n In the original Shadow of Amn (SoA),\u00a0the XP cap was set to 2.95 million. As a result, it was impossible to reach a level that would allow any\u00a0player\u00a0character to pick\u00a0or memorize\u00a0level 9 spells.\u00a0 The only way to access\u00a0level 9 spells, such as Time Stop, was to find\u00a0a scroll.\u00a0 Such\u00a0scrolls were extremely rare.\u00a0 Vithal\u00a0was well known among experienced players for holding the very first &lt;a href=\"Time%20Stop\"&gt;Time Stop&lt;/a&gt; scroll that a player could get hands on through normal gameplay.\n As of BG2EE v.2.5.16.6, all the \"treasures\"\u00a0in Vithal's inventory can be pickpocketed, including a total of five\u00a0level 8 or 9 scrolls.\u00a0If killed the mage will additionally drop the ritual book that you gave him and a plain quarterstaff.\u00a0\u00a0Even if provoked, however, he is not interested in fighting the player\u00a0and will teleport away once the quest is over, with only a few brief moments before disappearing from the game for good.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Quest%20Pack\"&gt;Quest Pack&lt;/a&gt; Mod adds a \"Reward Negotiation\" component. The player will be able to select specifically what items constitute their share of the loot during the division of Vithal's spoils from the Underdark portals. Some dialogue will be added, and reactions from Vithal will differ from the regular game. \nWith this mod, he can be made hostile, and he'll not attempt to flee but instead defend himself and all his treasures. Also, a failed pickpocket attempt with this mod may lead to a provoked battle.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; increases the elemental guardians at each Portal. The &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod alongside SCS bestows special abilities to the Greater Elementals."}
{"id": "39964", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39964", "title": "A Mage Imprisoned?", "text": "Obtaining the side quest.\nThe party will eventually come across a group of duergar merchants on the south central area of the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. Speaking with all of them is possible, and a good way to gain some insight and information.\nOne of the three, a merchant by the name of &lt;a href=\"Uder%20Mordin\"&gt;Uder Mordin&lt;/a&gt; has the most information for you. Engage in as much conversation as possible with this one, and ask any questions you wish in the dialogue choices. Paraphrased below are some of the replies and information he shares:\nGameplay.\nIt should become apparent that there is a mage that was defeated in battle nearby, who has been affected by the dreaded &lt;a href=\"Imprisonment\"&gt;Imprisonment&lt;/a&gt; spell effect. Based on the information available from Uder, it is likely the mage was pursuing some kind of artifact hunt before being unceremoniously trapped in a confined area below the surface.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt; is a party member he'll have an interjection and show keen interest in these alleged artifacts.\nUder Mordin says this imprisonment event occurred just north of their location. After this dialogue, the party will receive a Journal Update officially marking the side quest.\nYou will note that &lt;a href=\"Carlig\"&gt;Carlig&lt;/a&gt; who is the storekeeper for the duergar has a &lt;a href=\"Freedom\"&gt;Freedom&lt;/a&gt; scroll available. Perhaps this could be put to use, and possibly free this trapped mage?\nShould the party cast the freedom spell in the duergar's area (perhaps a bit north of them), then your suspicions are proven correct. Indeed, a mage was trapped by Imprisonment, and use of the Freedom spell by the party will summon the captive back to the exact location he was - before being spirited away to eternal stasis.\nThe mage, named &lt;a href=\"Vithal\"&gt;Vithal&lt;/a&gt;, will of course speak with the party and be thankful. He will also provide a chance to undertake another task, so he can finish his original exploration and hunt for artifacts. This is covered in the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; page. \nReward.\nFor releasing Vithal from Imprisonment: "}
{"id": "50977", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50977", "title": "A Mod for the Orderly", "text": "A Mod for the Orderly is a modification hosted by the Gibberlings 3 for Baldur's Gate II, Throne of Bhaal (classical and EE games), Baldur's Gate Trilogy and EET\nOverview.\nThis mod adds a keyring to help manage the avalanche of keys you acquire in your journey across Faerun. \nCompatibility.\nThis mod is designed to work on the following Infinity Engine games: The original Baldur's Gate II (BG2 or just SoA) with the Throne of Bhaal (ToB) expansion, Baldur's Gate II: Enhanced Edition (BG2:EE), the conversion projects Baldur's Gate Trilogy (BGT) and Enhanced Edition Trilogy (EET).\nThis is a WeiDU mod, and therefore should be compatible with all WeiDU mods. If you encounter any bugs, please report them on the forum!\nComponents.\nThe installer includes one or two components, and you select which one you want to install.\nFor more information see the links."}
