{"id": "2324", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2324", "title": "A Rogue Ogre", "text": "A Rogue Ogre, also known as Unshey's Girdle of Piercing and Unshey's Belt, is a &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", available from &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt; on.\nWalkthrough.\nOnly with a &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; of eight or higher will &lt;a href=\"Unshey\"&gt;Unshey&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;The Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt;'s second floor, tell an interested &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; how she had to \"bargain [her] new &lt;a href=\"Elves%27%20Bane\"&gt;girdle of piercing&lt;/a&gt; for [her] life\" out of an encounter with \"&lt;a href=\"Ogre%20%28A%20Rogue%20Ogre%29\"&gt;a rogue ogre&lt;/a&gt; with a fetish\", and that she'd \"be &lt;a href=\"%23Rewards\"&gt;mighty grateful&lt;/a&gt;\" if they returned the girdle to her. At a lower reaction, she will simply feel bothered by the party's smell and not be interested in any cooperation.\nIn the eastern wilderness of the southerly located &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way\"&gt;Coast Way&lt;/a&gt;, about half the way down and near the border of the map, an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20%28A%20Rogue%20Ogre%29\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; will attack the party. After being slain, two can be found on him: &lt;a href=\"Elves%27%20Bane\"&gt;Elves' Bane&lt;/a&gt; (Unshey's \"girdle of piercing\") and the &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Masculinity/Femininity\"&gt;Girdle of Masculinity/Femininity&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpeaking to Unshey again while being in possession of the former girdle, \"whether the task was requested by her or not\", will let her show some gratefulness, the amount of which depends on her reaction again. In any case, the party will gain &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;, but lose a unique and useful girdle. Unshey can be killed afterwards and the Girdle of Piercing can be looted from her body, but doing so will result in reputation loss.\nRewards.\n&lt;a href=\"Unshey\"&gt;Unshey&lt;/a&gt;'s standards regarding people around her are even higher than before when it comes to showing her gratefulness: \"neutrality\" doesn't suffice anymore for the higher reward, she now has to &lt;a href=\"Reaction\"&gt;react&lt;/a&gt; \"friendly\" to the deliverer of &lt;a href=\"Elves%27%20Bane\"&gt;her girdle&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpeaking of \"gratefulness\", it remains to be considered if the given reward, even the higher one, compensates the loss of a &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Piercing\"&gt;Girdle of Piercing&lt;/a&gt;, with a base value of and only one among very few available at all, barely enough to equip a whole &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; during the original campaign."}
