{"id": "12010", "revid": "24349587", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12010", "title": "A Tour of Durlag's Tower", "text": "To begin this quest, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party must travel to the town of &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt;, where they will find &lt;a href=\"Ike%20Cascadion%20Vendar\"&gt;Ike&lt;/a&gt; standing in front of the &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt; offering tours of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. He charges the party to provide the tour. After accepting the payment, he heads towards the Inn and disappears.\nWhen the party arrives at Durlag's Tower, they'll find Ike waiting on a stone bridge that is located just past the first gate of the entrance way to the tower. Upon speaking to him, he will berate the party for being late and then head off towards the main entrance.\nSpeaking to him again will begin the tour. He'll start talking about the history of the tower and the enormous fortune located within before heading inside. Moving inside to the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Ground%20Floor%29\"&gt;ground floor&lt;/a&gt;, the party will find Ike along with several &lt;a href=\"Tourist\"&gt;tourists&lt;/a&gt; standing in the foyer.\nHe must then be spoken to four more times. Each time Ike will provide more insight into what caused the tower's eventual decline, the magical wards &lt;a href=\"Durlag%20Trollkiller\"&gt;Durlag&lt;/a&gt; installed within the tower to protect himself, and even a few sensational examples of the horror's to be found throughout the tower. After the fourth time, one of the tourists will wander off and trigger a silent &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt; trap and fry himself.\nThe final time Ike's spoken to, he will offer for what he claims to be is a true wardstone that will give the party access at least as far down as the &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Three%29\"&gt;third level&lt;/a&gt; of the dungeon. Whichever dialogue option you pick as a response, they will all end with the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Knight\"&gt;Demon Knight&lt;/a&gt; teleporting into the foyer and killing Ike and the tourist with fireballs. So you cannot lose any money as Ike will simply drop anything you gave him, including the wardstone if you did not purchase it. At this point the quest ends."}
