{"id": "8438", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8438", "title": "Aabir", "text": "Watchknight Aabir is a neutral aligned priest and missionary of &lt;a href=\"Helm\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt;. He appears only in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" on the streets of the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nIf the party initiates conversation with this cleric, they may find out more about the religion of Helm and the temple here in the city.\nThe cleric invites the party to enter the Temple of Helm and partake of its services.\nHe will answer some questions, including the subject of the \"Unseeing eye\".\nAttacking this neutral cleric will shut down quests and actions issued from Helm as well as Temple services."}
{"id": "34777", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34777", "title": "Aasim", "text": "Aasim is one of six servants of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, all of whom are located on the fifth floor of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and are under orders from Sarevok to eliminate &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; permanently. He will most likely be encountered during the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Investigating the Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and will fight alongside &lt;a href=\"Zhalimar%20Cloudwulfe\"&gt;Zhalimar Cloudwulfe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Alai\"&gt;Alai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diyab\"&gt;Diyab&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gardush\"&gt;Gardush&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Naaman\"&gt;Naaman&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; (in the guise of &lt;a href=\"Emissary%20Tar\"&gt;Emissary Tar&lt;/a&gt;).\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt;, Aasim has nothing to say.\nGameplay.\nAasim and his associate Diyab have the following spells memorized:\nAasim will open combat by using both of the Flame Strike spells on the nearest party member, followed by two attempts at casting Hold Person on the nearest (non-helpless) party member. He will then cast Draw Upon Holy Might and move in for melee combat."}
