{"id": "30106", "revid": "26182140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30106", "title": "Abela the Nymph (item)", "text": "Abela the Nymph is the unconscious body left behind after telling the nymph &lt;a href=\"Abela\"&gt;Abela&lt;/a&gt; you have struck a deal with &lt;a href=\"Ramazith\"&gt;Ramazith&lt;/a&gt;. Since she is to be kept captive, she has no will to live on, let alone move, and the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; is instructed to carry her.\nDialogue.\nAt this point Abela drops down on the floor and her body is placed in the inventory of the party member who talked to her. As indicated in the infobox, she has a weight of 90\u00a0lbs, so the character may become overloaded."}
