{"id": "32686", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32686", "title": "Acid damage", "text": "Acid damage is one of the 10 main &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;damage types&lt;/a&gt; of the game, typically inflicted by spells or on-hit effects caused by weapons like the &lt;a href=\"Flail%20of%20Ages\"&gt;Flail of Ages&lt;/a&gt;. A weapon would cause &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; provided it goes through &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt;, and then an additional effect could add elemental damage such as Acid.\nProtection from acid.\nThrough the use of certain spells, items or abilities, it is possible to reduce the amount of damage, afflicted by acid.\nSpells and Scrolls.\n&lt;a href=\"Spells\"&gt;Spells&lt;/a&gt; usually offer only temporary protection from acid, in varying degrees.\nEquipment.\nThese items will provide elemental acid resistance as long as they are equipped.\nAbilities.\nThere are a few that can offer temporary or constant protection from acid.\nDamage from acid.\nMany spells are based on acid, as well as some abilities, and items may deal bonus or even pure acid damage.\nSpells.\nDue to their purpose of healing and supporting, the arsenal of acid-based spells is much smaller for &lt;a href=\"priest\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt;s than for &lt;a href=\"wizard\"&gt;wizard&lt;/a&gt;s.\nItems.\n...incomplete!\nAbilities.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nCreatures, protected from acid.\nSome have a natural resistance against acid damage, some have special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s equipped that protect them.\n\u2026 incomplete!\nCreatures, dealing acid damage.\nThere's is a number of that always or by will are able to deal acid damage, either naturally, via spells or through special &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;s in their &lt;a href=\"Inventory\"&gt;equipment&lt;/a&gt;.\n\u2026 incomplete!"}
