{"id": "48530", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48530", "title": "Acton Balthis", "text": "Acton Balthis is Vice-Regent for the Council of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; and resides in &lt;a href=\"Balthis%20Estate\"&gt;Balthis Estate&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. \nAttempting to talk to Acton directly results only in him shouting, \"Brigands in my home, is it? Bah, where are the guards?! GAURDS!!\" Of course neither of the guards actually enter his bedroom, and leaving the bedroom finds the guards still neutral. \nKilling either Acton or his servant &lt;a href=\"Pip\"&gt;Pip&lt;/a&gt; result in the usual &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss associated with murdering an &lt;a href=\"innocent\"&gt;innocent&lt;/a&gt;. Furthermore, his &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Bodyguard\"&gt;Amnish Bodyguards&lt;/a&gt; will turn hostile, and call for backup from the military, which may include one or more of the following: \nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business II&lt;/a&gt; mod for Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn restores a quest, \"The Murder of Acton Balthis\", that was cut from the game according to &lt;a href=\"David%20Gaider\"&gt;David Gaider&lt;/a&gt; of Bioware. This quest is only for players who have taken &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt; as a companion, and who also, for some reason, have not already slain &lt;a href=\"Quataris\"&gt;Quataris&lt;/a&gt; the art dealer in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6340", "revid": "269044", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6340", "title": "Adalon", "text": "Adalon is a &lt;a href=\"http%3A//forgottenrealms.wikia.com/wiki/Silver_dragon\"&gt;silver dragon&lt;/a&gt; who attempted to keep peace between the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; and the surface elves by guarding the passageway between the surface and the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, often being successful. According to past lore, Adalon was married. She and her mate fought a powerful evil, but he perished in the attempt. After destroying it, she was granted a wish. At first, she attempted to resurrect her husband, but that was not possible. So instead, she wished for his spirit to fertilize some eggs.\nOverview.\nIn , Adalon will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party to retrieve &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Eggs\"&gt;her eggs&lt;/a&gt; after they were stolen by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;, as a way for the wizard to ensure that she wouldn't dare meddle in his schemes. She will ask the party to infiltrate the drow city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and retrieve her eggs disguised as drow. By doing this, the party will be able to return to the surface, so as to continue on their quest to defeat &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and Irenicus.\nIf the player retrieves her eggs intact, Adalon will facilitate a way to the surface, and give a reward from her hoard. If the eggs are destroyed, Adalon will fight the player. Her blood may be used to help complete the &lt;a href=\"Human%20Flesh\"&gt;Human Flesh&lt;/a&gt; armor. See the &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; quest page for details.\nGameplay.\nUpon first making way through the darkened staircase leading to Adalon' lair, the party will eventually observe the magnificent form of the Silver Dragon.\nAdalon will address the party. She will know if the party obtained the &lt;a href=\"Light%20Gem\"&gt;Light Gem&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Goldander%20Blackenrock\"&gt;Goldander Blackenrock&lt;/a&gt; by doing the good deed of destroying the &lt;a href=\"Balor%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Balor (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt;, and she'll also know if it was obtained in other fashion, such as being stolen. If it was obtained in an underhanded fashion, then the dragon will make known her displeasure and say:\n\"\"You have come here through trickery, without granting the wishes of Goldander Blackenrock. He and his people will fall to the balor they unearthed because of it.\"\nIf any murders of the Svirfneblin gnomes have occurred, she will also know this and likely say:\n\"You committed pointless murder in your travels, leaving Therndle with no son, and you used trickery to get here without helping Goldander Blackenrock. If they are not dead now, they soon will be. You are vile in many ways, but I have need of you. I also know that you have need of me.\" \nFurther dialogue will continue, as she explains her purpose, and may answer a question or two. She knows of Bhodi and Irenicus. but eventually will inform the party that she requires a task be performed. Adlaon explains:\nIf you agree to do the task, Adalon will give instructions, and explain how her powerful magic will make the party appear as drow. She also gives a plausible back story for you to adopt, instructing the party to pretend they are from the drow city of Ched Nasad. Gorion's Ward should use the common name \"Veldrin\". In this manner and using subterfuge, the party is to find her eggs, and safely return them to her. In return she shall assist in leaving the Underdark and give a worthy item from her hoard as an extra reward.\nIf the party refuses, then finding a way out of the Underdark can only be accomplished by other means. The party has no idea how to do that, if it is even possible, and must figure it out on their own. No clues are provided in the game about leaving the Underdark without Adalon's help.\nThe most optimal way of leaving the Underdark is to undertake the quest to retrieve Adalon's Dragon Eggs. Unless the party is granted an illusory disguise to \"appear\" as, \"speak\" as, and \"understand\" the drow language, then there is no really ideal method to leave the Underdark.\nIt will also be impossible to enter the city of Ust Natha unless the party is disguised to appear as drow. Even if the party has a drow party member such as &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt;, that won't be enough to allow entry. In practical terms, the game saga is designed to encourage the party pursue the Dragon Egg quest. There really is no good game playing reason to try and figure out a way to get out of it, as the rewards (especially Experience points) for the quest are substantial, plus there is more adventuring, and over all immersive play opportunity. \nHowever, there are two ways to avoid the Dragon Egg quest and to depart the Underdark, if the player is bent on doing that:\nIf the party has indeed managed to secure Adalon's eggs, and is ready to leave the Underdark, then return to her lair. A reward will be given, and then she'll eventually change to a more appropriate form as a humanoid and teleport the party and herself to an area close to the exit gate and the &lt;a href=\"Drow%20gate%20guardians\"&gt;Drow gate guardians&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Kuo%20Toa%20in%20Underdark\"&gt;Western Tunnels&lt;/a&gt;, assist with a spell cast, and then take her leave. As promised, she has broken the ward on the exit gate, but the party will still need to battle through the guardians, although she will cast a spell to weaken the defenders.\nIt's possible to kill Adalon before this occurs. Perhaps the party is interested in obtaining a &lt;a href=\"Blood%20of%20a%20Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;Blood of a Silver Dragon&lt;/a&gt;. This can be attempted in two ways. Try it in her humanoid form or do it in her Dragon form. In the human form, after she change shape and teleport you near the exit of Underdark. You should use spells like finger of death otherwise she could turn hostile and teleport. If killed this way you will get full experience for the kill, and you can freely loot her. This can is difficult to accomplish, due to timing restriction, as she will teleport away once made hostile. If the player isn't bothered by \"save scumming\", and just reloading until it is successful, well, then it can be accomplished at some point. This instant death attempt will not work with &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; installed.\nIt's also possible, though considerably more difficult, to complete the quest and still have Adalon be killed in dragon form. Through very precise timing (and some luck on saving throws), you can begin the conversation to return the eggs and reap the rewards, whilst simultaneously attacking her, perhaps with by an instant-kill spells (such as Finger of Death). This doesn't provide any other benefits to the method described above, and you do not get teleported to the exit of the Underdark. The instant death attempt will not work with &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; installed.\nCertainly, a full-on battle with the Silver Dragon may provide a way for an evil party to test their mettle.\nFighting Adalon.\nShould the party instigate an attack on Adalon, or if Adalon herself initiates hostilities the following actions will occur:\nIn between these events, Adalon will engage in physical combat with any party member in range using her melee attack.\nExpect that the closest party members will be exposed to Dragon Fear, Remove Magic, and dragon &lt;a href=\"Wing%20buffet\"&gt;Wing buffet&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll dragons have a specific type of breath attack, and the silver dragon is no exception. However, Adalon has two varieties of breath weapon, one which inflicts cold damage, and the other a paralyzing breath that actually applies a &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; effect. Saving throws will apply to these for half damage and to negate the status effects, but magic resistance and spell level immunity protection like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; offer no protection.\nDuring the battle she will attempt several offensive damage and or disabling spells depending on target opportunities, such as &lt;a href=\"Silence%2C%2015%27%20Radius\"&gt;Silence, 15' Radius&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Orb\"&gt;Chromatic Orb&lt;/a&gt; and a few others. \nParty reaction to fighting Adalon.\nSeveral good-aligned party members will take exception to siding with the Lesser Demon Lord in the final stages of the &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace Despana&lt;/a&gt;'s ritual. They will either become hostile to the PC or just leave the party forever.\nHowever, this is not the case if the party attacks Adalon (which seems like an oversight). For example, while &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn Firecam&lt;/a&gt; will fight the party if siding with the Lesser Demon Lord, he won't have a reaction if the party attacks Adalon, and will carry on as normal.\nThe only exception to this is &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad yn Bashir&lt;/a&gt;. He will leave the party permanently if Adalon is attacked, so plan accordingly.\nAchievements.\nSilver Dragon Slayer.\nSlew the silver dragon, Adalon.\nMod Content.\nWith &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed and the \"Smarter Dragons\" component, Adalon has some revisions which are responsive to the game difficulty settings. Adalon has all the immunities and powers of the unmodified dragon, with the following additional changes:\nImmunities in addition to the unmodified dragon version:\nAdalon has an opening Spell Sequencer that applies &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Fear\"&gt;Dragon Fear&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, which is uninterruptible and takes only 1 second to deploy. All party members in range not protected from fear must make a saving throw or possibly suffer &lt;a href=\"panic\"&gt;panic&lt;/a&gt;. Adalon also has &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; already applied without the need for casting it.\n&lt;a href=\"Adalon%27s%20Blood\"&gt;Adalon's Blood&lt;/a&gt; Mod is available to bargain with the Silver Dragon to get some of her blood. This blood can be used to resolve the &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; quest. Instead of trying to slay her for the blood, you can convince her to give you some of her own Silver Dragon's Blood voluntarily - if you do a task for her."}
{"id": "49486", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49486", "title": "Adalon's Blood", "text": "Adalon's Blood Modification enables the player to ask Adalon the Silver Dragon in the Underdark for some of her blood.\nMod summary.\nTo resolve the &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; questline, the player needs to obtain some blood of a Silver Dragon. \nThis mod provides a method that is mainly aimed at good-aligned characters who want to finish the quest in a non-evil fashion: to discover and terminate the clients of the skinner and cleanse the armor of any vile taint in a temple setting.\nThe mod provides an alternative to obtain the dragon's blood without having to try and kill her for it.\nNevertheless, evil characters with CHAR of 18 or higher may also attempt to convince Adalon to sacrifice some of her blood. There is a 25% chance of success for them in deceiving the silver dragon.\nThe modification is compatible with original BGII, BGT, BGII:EE and EET.\nFor more information see the link."}
