{"id": "44996", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44996", "title": "Adalon's Lair", "text": "Adalon's Lair is the den of the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;Silver Dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nThis map area is entered through a passage marked on the Underdark map as \"Dark Cave\". \nIf the party attempts to enter the cave a message will display \"An impenetrable darkness overwhelms you. You cannot pass this way without light.\"\nGameplay.\nThis area is impenetrable by the party unless they first acquire the &lt;a href=\"Light%20Gem\"&gt;Light Gem&lt;/a&gt; - needed to pierce the dragon's mystical darkness defense - a blackness so deep that even the drow cannot travel through it.\nShould the party ever make its way within the lair and encounter the silver dragon, they will be introduced to the &lt;a href=\"Recover%20the%20Silver%20Dragon%27s%20Eggs\"&gt;Recover the Silver Dragon's Eggs&lt;/a&gt; quest, unless Adalon is attacked by the party before the dialogue can progress. In that case, there will never be any exploration of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; and all adventures, quests, tasks, experience, treasure and challenges within the city will be unattainable by the player.\nAnother quest is possible with this creature, known as &lt;a href=\"Blood%20of%20a%20Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;Blood of a Silver Dragon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "38621", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38621", "title": "Adalon's Note", "text": "Adalon's Note is a scroll that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can acquire by killing &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon\"&gt;Silver Dragon&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;Chapter 5&lt;/a&gt; in the . It contains the necessary enchantments needed to break through the warding spells that the &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; are using to control passage through the tunnel connecting to the surface.\nGameplay.\nThe note can't be pickpocketed from Adalon in the Enhanced Edition. The dragon's sprite is too large for the reach of a rogue's pickpocket, and the item is flagged as \"Can't steal\". Repeated attempts when she is not hostile will trigger dialogue with her only. If she is hostile then no dialogue will occur, the pick pocket will just fail."}
{"id": "8993", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8993", "title": "Adamantine Dust", "text": "Adamantine Dust is the result of exposing any item made by the &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; to sunlight. Any Drow item turns into dust, whether it's worn at the moment or stored away in the &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bag of Holding&lt;/a&gt; or the inventory. The only probable way to protect your items is by entering the surface when its dark and storing the item in a safe container."}
