{"id": "33412", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33412", "title": "Adamantine items", "text": ""}
{"id": "8926", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8926", "title": "Adamantite Golem", "text": "Adamantite Golems are the most powerful &lt;a href=\"golems\"&gt;golems&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nAdamantite golems have 90% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt;. Only weapons of +3 or greater enchantment can strike them. \nThey are difficult to harm with most magic, having 100% Magic Resistance and 100% resistance to other &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; will actually heal the golem instead of harming it. They are immune to &lt;a href=\"paralyze\"&gt;paralyze&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Held\"&gt;hold&lt;/a&gt;, but not &lt;a href=\"stun\"&gt;stun&lt;/a&gt;. \nAdamantite golems are much larger than human size and are therefore unable to fit through many doorways. See Mod content below for exceptions.\nThese golems possess the innate ability to create a &lt;a href=\"Gas%20Cloud\"&gt;Gas Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, which causes poison damage. See the link for details.\nIn battle, these blundering constructs rush toward the nearest detected enemy and begin trying to smash it with their crushing fists. After a few rounds, the golem will discharge a gas cloud over itself. The golem can do this periodically as long as it is still functional.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the installation of the \"\"AI Enhancement's\" component improves many aspects of creatures encountered in the game. In regards to golems, the mod implements the following:\nImproved Golems (BG2, BG2EE, BGT/EET)&lt;br&gt;\nThis component doesn't really make golems smarter (they're supposed to be stupid) But it streamlines their scripts a bit, gives their weapons a sensible range, makes them immune to \"Lower Resistance\" and to poison, and tries to prevent situations where golems get stuck behind barricades. It also fixes an animation glitch in the Iron Golem animation - this hopefully makes Adamantite golems a bit prettier when they attack and blow clouds.\nAdamantite golems are immune to the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Resistance\"&gt;Lower Resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Magic\"&gt;Pierce Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pierce%20Shield\"&gt;Pierce Shield&lt;/a&gt; spells.&lt;br&gt;\nIf you damage an iron golem, and then decide to back away and rest somewhere, to continue the fight later, the golem will be restored to full health.&lt;br&gt;\nThe golem has a advanced script allowing better targeting and tactical behavior. It will also apply its Gas Cloud at least every three rounds of combat, and if it is dispersed by a &lt;a href=\"Zone%20of%20Sweet%20Air\"&gt;Zone of Sweet Air&lt;/a&gt; effect.&lt;br&gt;\nThe golem will do a better job of chasing down PC party members attacking from afar, as long as it can reach them via movement. It will follow and hunt down attackers.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; Mod adds a necessary lootable component to Adamantite golems, so that the player can start amassing enough material in order to build its own \"lesser Adamantite Golem\", \"Adamantite Golem\", \"Greater Adamantite Golem or \"Perfect Adamantite Golem\". \nThis mod also replaces the golem's &lt;a href=\"Gas%20Cloud\"&gt;Gas Cloud&lt;/a&gt; ability with a new mod-only ability called \"Trample\":\nTrample&lt;br&gt;\nRange: 0&lt;br&gt;\nDuration: Instant&lt;br&gt;\nArea of Effect: 1 creature&lt;br&gt;\nSaving Throw: Special&lt;br&gt;\nBecause of the golem's huge size and weight, it can literally run over opponents that are smaller than itself. The trample ability deals 8d10+30 points of crushing damage and stuns the target for one round. A successful Saving Throw vs. Death at -4 can reduce damage to half and prevent the stun effect. Huge creatures, like dragons or giants, are not affected."}
{"id": "47069", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47069", "title": "Addy", "text": "Addy is a noblewoman who can be found wandering about in front of &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR0707\"&gt;generic home 1&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. She will approach the party upon sight and, recognizing &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; by name, beseech the party to investigate the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; one more time. After which she will walk away and disappear.\nThe conversation also results in the following &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry in the quest section under the title \"Rising Tensions with Amn\"."}
