{"id": "10672", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10672", "title": "Adoy's Enclave", "text": "Adoy's Enclave is located south of the &lt;a href=\"Firewine%20Bridge\"&gt;Firewine Bridge&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. For this area to become available, &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; must be in the party to trigger her banter which will allow for her quest to begin.\nOnce you reach the area, you will have the choice of fighting all the &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20EE%29\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s in this area, or asking them for passage through their camp to the &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave%20%28Goblin%20Caves%29\"&gt;goblin cave&lt;/a&gt;, after which you may let those weak creatures live or wage an all out war on them. There is no penalty or reward either way.\nThe elven ranger &lt;a href=\"Magreb\"&gt;Magreb&lt;/a&gt; is also found here standing in front of his small house (with no front door). He'll fill you in on &lt;a href=\"Adoy\"&gt;Adoy's&lt;/a&gt; current predicament and his grief for the loss of his beloved &lt;a href=\"Rilsa\"&gt;Rilsa&lt;/a&gt;.\nMoose and Squirrel.\nThere are two &lt;a href=\"wild%20mage\"&gt;wild mage&lt;/a&gt;s polymorphed into animals to the north of the bridge, one is a squirrel and the other is a moose. They accidentally summon a monster and run away. The monster can be either a Gnoll (35XP) or an Ogre (270XP).\nTrivia.\nMoose and squirrel dialogue is a reference to \"\"."}
{"id": "47422", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47422", "title": "Adoy's Enclave (Goblin Caves)", "text": "The Goblin Caves are located in &lt;a href=\"Adoy%27s%20Enclave\"&gt;Adoy's Enclave&lt;/a&gt;. This is where were the imprisoned &lt;a href=\"Adoy\"&gt;Adoy&lt;/a&gt; and the remains of &lt;a href=\"Rilsa\"&gt;Rilsa&lt;/a&gt; are found.\nLayout.\nThe caves are comprised of three caverns with the first and second caverns being separated by a wooden foot bridge and the second and third caverns separated by a makeshift door fashioned out of small trees.\nThe first cavern is slightly kidney-shaped in appearance and is occupied by five &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20EE%29\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s. Four of them are equipped with &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow\"&gt;Composite Longbow&lt;/a&gt;s and a quiver of 60 &lt;a href=\"Arrow\"&gt;Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s. The fifth is equipped with an &lt;a href=\"axe\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;. A medium-sized pot near the fire pit contains a &lt;a href=\"Skull\"&gt;Skull&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe second cavern is the biggest of the three and it too is slightly kidney-shaped in appearance. The lower portion is where the remains of Rilsa are located. You have the option of either burying her body or leaving it where it is. The chest near her body is opened and contains the +2 leather armor called &lt;a href=\"Rugged%20Leathers\"&gt;Rugged Leathers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Fear\"&gt;Wand of Fear&lt;/a&gt; with 9 charges, three &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Healing\"&gt;potions of healing&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Genius\"&gt;potion of genius&lt;/a&gt;, an item of &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDTRE04\"&gt;wealthy random treasure&lt;/a&gt; (which could be a random amount of gold) and 600 .\nThe upper portion of the cavern is where &lt;a href=\"Rogdok\"&gt;Rogdok&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the goblins, is located along with four additional goblins. Two of the goblins are equipped with composite longbows and the other two carry axes. Rogdok is equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Bastard%20Sword%20%2B1\"&gt;Bastard Sword +1&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Shortbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Shortbow +1&lt;/a&gt; and 80 arrows. There are no containers in this portion of the cavern.\nThe third cavern is where the goblins have Adoy imprisoned. The area is roughly circular in appearance and is sparsely decorated. The only container is the empty table."}
{"id": "29649", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29649", "title": "Adratha", "text": ""}
{"id": "13304", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13304", "title": "Adratha's Cottage", "text": "Adratha's Cottage is a building in the &lt;a href=\"Druid%20Grove\"&gt;Druid Grove&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is home to the old witch &lt;a href=\"Adratha\"&gt;Adratha&lt;/a&gt; who sells a variety of potions to her visitors.\nGameplay.\nWithin the cottage is an older woman, and two men tending to the shop. The woman glances up at you as you enter and smiles, but remains quiet. Speak with her or the two shop hands if you wish. Perhaps there are goods to purchase than may assist your adventures.\nA chest can be looted within the area, containing &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Arrows of Fire&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Acid Arrows&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Biting\"&gt;Bolts of Biting&lt;/a&gt; , and &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Bolts of Lightning&lt;/a&gt; \nBuy and Sell.\n\"Oh good! I do so enjoy someone coming by to look at my mixes! The townsfolk always come, but none have come lately... the business with the animals, I suppose...\"\nThe shop is not accessible under certain &lt;a href=\"Ihtafeer%23Shop%20or%20Fight\"&gt;conditions&lt;/a&gt;. Furthermore, she only sells, and does not buy anything from the party, legitimate or stolen, with the notable exception of &lt;a href=\"Bag%20of%20Holding\"&gt;Bags of Holding&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gem%20Bag\"&gt;Gem Bags&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20Case\"&gt;Scroll Cases&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ammo%20Belt\"&gt;Ammo Belts&lt;/a&gt;. She also cannot Identify items, nor can you steal from her stock.\nMod Content.\nThe plot of &lt;a href=\"Afaaq%20the%20Djinni%20Companion\"&gt;Afaaq the Djinni Companion&lt;/a&gt; mod begins in Adratha's Cottage."}
