{"id": "50392", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50392", "title": "Adrian NPC walkthrough", "text": "The \"&lt;a href=\"Adrian%20NPC\"&gt;Adrian NPC&lt;/a&gt;\" mod by \"Rhaella\" adds Adrian, a &lt;a href=\"Alignment%23Lawful_Evil\"&gt;lawful evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;, to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;BG2&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;joinable NPC&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe has a small personal quest, and one extra encounter.&lt;br&gt;\nThis is a walkthrough for that quest content.&lt;br&gt;\nSPOILER WARNING!\nHow to get him to join.\nHe is being held captive by the &lt;a href=\"duergar\"&gt;duergar&lt;/a&gt; smiths in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon 2nd Floor&lt;/a&gt;. Kill them.&lt;br&gt;\nHe offers to join when you loot the key to his shackles from the duergar's bodies."}
{"id": "55038", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55038", "title": "Adsaan", "text": "Adsaan the &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; can be encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, and specifically within &lt;a href=\"Demin%27s%20House\"&gt;Demin's House&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe raksasha will deploy a couple of uninterruptible buffs, and then attempt to pollute the battlefield with a &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Lightning\"&gt;Chain Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt;. \nIf able, he'll fire off various offensive damage spells as shown in the InfoBox. \nRemember, the raksasha are immune to spells with a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; between 1 through 7, and thus he won't be touched by any of the AoE spells he will try.\nIn close quarters combat the creature will conduct melee attacks with his rapid APR longsword ability. His blows can pack a punch due the magical girdle he wears.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises this raksasha. A new \"Smarter Mage\" AI script is assigned. Adsaan's experience level is raised to 17. \nA new battery of memorized arcane spells are scripted for use. The creature will be able to launch a chain of protective buffs at the outset of hostilities, to include: &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Improved%20Haste\"&gt;Improved Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; (or \"Greater Spell Deflection\" with &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;SR)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;.\nA set of prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt; are scripted for instant deployment.\nA scripted potion is assigned for healing purposes.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod the creature's spell versions will be the SR variety. Expect being unable to break the mage's invisibility and illusions due to SR's Non-Detection. Peel away the protective layers first."}
{"id": "24611", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24611", "title": "Adventurer's Guide", "text": "The Baldur's Gate: Enhanced Edition Adventurer's Guide is the &lt;a href=\"Game%20guides\"&gt;manual&lt;/a&gt; and rulebook for &lt;a href=\"Beamdog\"&gt;Beamdog&lt;/a&gt;'s enhanced \"Baldur's Gate\" series.\nBackground.\nIt was published as part of the ' release and replaced the former ' manual \"&lt;a href=\"Mastering%20Melee%20%26amp%3B%20Magic%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Mastering Melee &amp; Magic&lt;/a&gt;\". It is publicly available for download on the games' official websites. A spiral-bound printed copy is part of the \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.beamdog.com/products/baldurs-gate-siege-of-dragonspear-collectors-edition\"&gt;Siege of Dragonspear Collector's Edition.&lt;/a&gt;\"\nContent.\nThe guide contains errors and omissions, many of which have been reported for years. If these will be fixed in a future release, is currently unknown."}
{"id": "12210", "revid": "6896023", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12210", "title": "Adventurer's Mart", "text": ""}
{"id": "3799", "revid": "26182140", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3799", "title": "Adventurer's Robe", "text": "Adventurers Robe is a magical robe to avoid crushing attacks and spells under petrification &amp; polymorph category. This robe can be gained as a drop from mages encountered in the game or as treasure.\nLocations.\n\"Baldur's Gate\" &amp; \"Tales of the Sword Coast\".\nDropped by.\nUnless otherwise specified, these mages wear the robe and therefore it cannot be &lt;a href=\"Pick%20Pockets\"&gt;stolen&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5823", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5823", "title": "Adventurer Mart", "text": "The Adventurer Mart is a store located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. This indoor market is owned by &lt;a href=\"Ribald%20Barterman\"&gt;Ribald Barterman&lt;/a&gt; and rents space to two other specialty merchants, who are independently buying and selling their own merchandise. Ribald buys and sells a variety of mundane and powerful gear, equipment, and other items for the adventurer. Also, in , he provides some special wares you can browse through if you pay each time. A notable thing about &lt;a href=\"Ribald%20Barterman%23Special%20Items%20Store\"&gt;that shop&lt;/a&gt; is that he pays 55% instead of the usual 30%. \nThe market employs its own full time security &lt;a href=\"Amnian%20Soldier%20%28Adventurer%20Mart%29\"&gt;guard&lt;/a&gt; to deter theft and other disruptive activity. Intuitively, this should imply that just picking up anything found on shelves or containers around the market would be seen as theft, but surprisingly, there are a large quantity of books that you may keep, read, or even sell back to another merchant (including Ribald). Books are a great way to get some background lore and history of the land of Faer\u00fbn. \nThe lady in the middle of the store (&lt;a href=\"Deidre\"&gt;Deidre&lt;/a&gt;) sells some unique items, which make a reference to the computer game &lt;a href=\"w%3Ac%3Atorment\"&gt;Planescape: Torment&lt;/a&gt; and a few items of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe woman in the market corner (&lt;a href=\"Lady%20Yuth\"&gt;Lady Yuth&lt;/a&gt;) near the bookshelves sells scrolls. She has bribed the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; in order to do this and she can tell you how you can gain a license to cast spells in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. Her store is named \"Pen and Parchment\", and sells mostly arcane spell scrolls, some of which are rare and of high level.\nMod Content.\nMods:.\nInstall the BG2EE compatible Lucy the Wyvern Mod from &lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.shsforums.net/files/file/635-lucy-the-wyvern/\"&gt;Spellhold Studios&lt;/a&gt;. This mod adds a twist to the encounter with Lucy, the wyvern in the Adventurer Mart. To access this encounter, simply talk to Lucy with your Player Character."}
{"id": "23310", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23310", "title": "Adventurers' Mart", "text": ""}
{"id": "50318", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50318", "title": "Adventuring Party (Underdark)", "text": "Adventuring Party (Underdark) is a potential encounter that is triggered by accepting an order from &lt;a href=\"Solaufein\"&gt;Solaufein&lt;/a&gt; that sets a global in the game. After your party leaves &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; from this point on - it will trigger a spawning script of the \"Adventuring Party\" which will be placed further south of the causeway connecting Ust Natha and the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. The opposing party will be made hostile if you are detected or they are attacked. Dialogue with the Adventuring party won't be available, as they don't care what you have to say. \nThis eventually hostile party appears to be a mixed creature group of Adventurers exploring the Underdark. The enemy party has the following members: \nThe Skeleton is a long duration summoned creature armed with a small shield and club. It is a 5-HD Skeleton, with all the usual undead immunities.\nThe War Dog is roughly equivalent to a &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Wolf\"&gt;Dire Wolf&lt;/a&gt;. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to these creatures. SCS AI scripts are added where appropriate, and spell casters have revised spells memorized including sequencers and or instant cast triggers to reflect the party being prepared and self-buffed. \nWeapon proficiencies and skills are assigned commensurate with the experience levels of the party for increased challenge. See the individual creature pages for more details."}
{"id": "7728", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7728", "title": "Aec'Letec", "text": "Aec'Letec is a &lt;a href=\"Nabassu\"&gt;Nabassu&lt;/a&gt;, a powerful type of &lt;a href=\"tanar%27ri\"&gt;tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; and the final boss of the quest &lt;a href=\"Recovering%20%22Soultaker%22\"&gt;Recovering \"Soultaker\"&lt;/a&gt;, following the completion of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. It has a unique ability that will cause the target to be turned into hostile &lt;a href=\"ghast\"&gt;ghast&lt;/a&gt;s, victims are dismembered, die permanently and cannot be raised. &lt;a href=\"Kirinhale\"&gt;Kirinhale&lt;/a&gt; also mentions \"Aec\" as her 'friend' and how Durlag and her came to a disagreement about how to 'treat' him and how she doesn't want to end up like him.\nLocation.\nAec'Letec can be found in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Shandalar%27s%20Home\"&gt;Shandalar's Home&lt;/a&gt; on the western side of &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard&lt;/a&gt; after the &lt;a href=\"Soultaker%20Dagger\"&gt;Soultaker Dagger&lt;/a&gt; has been stolen from the party by cultists.\nUpon entering the Inner Sanctum, an NPC named &lt;a href=\"Tracea%20Carol\"&gt;Tracea Carol&lt;/a&gt; will start talking to you. As soon as this dialogue is finished the fight will start. Aec'Letec will spawn in the center of the red circle, and there are a number of Cult Guard standing passively around the outside.\nAbilities.\nAs a denizen of the lower planes, Aec'Letec has a high Magic Resistance, making it difficult to harm it with spells. Aec'Letec is also immune to normal weapons, immune to fire, electricity, poison and resistant to cold. It is also immune to most mind-affecting spells and hold.\nAec'Letec can avoid death by taking over the bodies of its worshipers. If it is killed while any of the six &lt;a href=\"Cult%20Guard\"&gt;Cult Guard&lt;/a&gt;s are still alive, it will re-incarnate at full health from the body of a Cult Guard and the fight will continue until no Cult Guards are left alive. The priority therefore is to kill the cult guards before focusing on the demon.\n&lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Touch\"&gt;Vampiric Touch&lt;/a&gt;.\nAec'Letec will frequently cast this spell on anything that comes into touch spell range. It heals the demon and increases its survivability considerably when anything other than undead minions attack it.\nDeath Gaze Attack.\nAec'Letec will cast a spell on your characters which first acts like a &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt; spell, and will also add a debuff named 'Dying', which will kill the affected character in 30 seconds, spawning a hostile &lt;a href=\"Ghast\"&gt;Ghast&lt;/a&gt; in its place. This can be countered in a number of ways, such as:\n1: Dispel Magic.\nThe easiest way is by use of the 3rd-level &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; spell Dispel Magic. &lt;a href=\"Yeslick%20Orothiar\"&gt;Yeslick&lt;/a&gt; is good here for his special innate ability to cast Dispel Magic. In the , &lt;a href=\"Inquisitor\"&gt;Inquisitor&lt;/a&gt; paladins also can gain innate, rapid and highly effective daily uses of Dispel Magic. Using &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Dispelling\"&gt;arrows of dispelling&lt;/a&gt; by having one party member shoot another also works. Regardless of delivery, however, it will also dispel any buffs you might have cast.\n2: &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Mirrored%20Eyes\"&gt;Potion of Mirrored Eyes&lt;/a&gt;.\nPotion of Mirrored Eyes is confirmed to make characters immune to Aec'Letec's Death Gaze. This will prevent said character from turning into a ghast for the duration of the potion. The &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt; sells them, as well as &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. Note that the potion does not dispel the Death Gaze attack, so consuming one after a character has been affected by it will do nothing.\n3: Mercy Killing.\n\"[Confirmation Needed]\"Another, and less preferable, way to prevent the permanent death of a character affected by the gaze is to kill the character before they turn into a ghast. It is not advisable to do this if the protagonist is the recipient of said gaze, for obvious reasons.\n4: Buffing with spells and equipment before the battle\nProtection from Evil, Chant, Luck, etc and any other spell that increases your saving throw can give you a decent chance of coming out unaffected. If you have a scroll of Protection from Evil in 10 Radius, this is a good time to use it.\nStrategy.\nParty Configuration.\nYou will probably want at least two clerics or two mages, or one cleric and one mage in order to deal with his gaze attack. Key spells to have memorized are &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; (Level 3 wizard/cleric), &lt;a href=\"Animate%20Dead\"&gt;Animate Dead&lt;/a&gt; and some form of &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Fear\"&gt;Remove Fear&lt;/a&gt;. The aforementioned potions of Mirrored Eyes help a lot as well. Just protect fully your vanguard fighters, haste everyone and go get in the basement with mass invisibility. You can move before the talk, attack the bottom green robe guy, all enemies head there for easy nuking. Dialogue triggers as well after a few blows get exchanged, just don't kill the talker too fast. With a bunch of enemies clustered near one well armored invulnerable to magic fighter its scorched earth time.\nDistracting Aec'Letec.\nSummoned Skeletons are very good at keeping his attention (and the occasional gaze attack) away from your valuable party members. If he lands a gaze on any target, it will, after a few seconds, dismember and turn into an undead ghast, preventing any form of resurrection, so it's best to let a summoned creature die instead of them.\nBy summoning undead creatures directly on top of Aec'Letec, then dispelling magic whenever he casts his gaze on a party member, the characters in the party should be free to move around the outside of the circle killing the Cult Guards (500 XP each). If you run out of &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s to summon, casting &lt;a href=\"Otiluke%27s%20Resilient%20Sphere\"&gt;Otiluke's Resilient Sphere&lt;/a&gt; on the target he is attacking can keep him occupied for a while. Once all the Cult Guards are dead, it is a simple matter of finishing off Aec'Letec for good.\nGameplay (community).\nAlternative strategy.\nSend down one of your fighters to initiate the conversation with Tracea Carol. Afterwards send your fighter back up and Tracea Carol will follow you upstairs. This fight should not be a problem. Now all the Cult Guards need to die first. By having a few invisible mages, one can kill all the Cult Guards with fireballs, skull traps or similar damaging spells or potions from each corner avoiding attacks from Aec'Letec which will not be able to see you. Once all the Cult Guards are dead, Aec'Letec will not be able to respawn. Be aware that anti-hold spells, items, potions, etc., such as Edventar's Gift do NOT render the Death Gaze Attack ineffective. You will avoid the hold but will still suffer the Death debuff. "}
{"id": "4584", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4584", "title": "Aeger's Hide", "text": "The Aeger's Hide +3 is an enchanted &lt;a href=\"Hide%20Armor\"&gt;hide armor&lt;/a&gt; which provides 15% resistance against fire, cold and acid. This armor also grants the wearer immunity to &lt;a href=\"confusion\"&gt;confusion&lt;/a&gt;. Opposed to common hide armor, the Aeger's one doesn't apply penalties to a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Thieving%20Abilities\"&gt;abilities&lt;/a&gt; due to its lower weight."}
