{"id": "12882", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12882", "title": "Aegis-fang", "text": "Aegis-fang is a unique Throwing Hammer/War Hammer +3 found in . It is the weapon of &lt;a href=\"Wulfgar\"&gt;Wulfgar&lt;/a&gt;, made for him by Bruenor Battlehammer, both of them members of &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt;'s party. This weapon has two seemingly identical variations: An unobtainable Throwing Hammer version used by Wulfgar, and a weaker War Hammer version that can be pickpocketed or looted from him.\nThe Throwing Hammer version possesses the THAC0 and damage bonuses of a +5 weapon, deals an additional +2 damage when used in melee, has a throwing range of 100 ft., and can only be used by single class Fighters and Monks. The War Hammer version possesses none of these extra bonuses or restrictions. Both versions have a base damage of 2d4 instead of 1d4+1 like a normal War/Throwing Hammer, have an enchantment level of 0 instead of 3 (effectively treated as 1 in the Enhanced Edition), weigh 1 lb. less than a generic War Hammer +3 (1 lb. more than a generic Throwing Hammer), and require 18 Strength to use."}
