{"id": "5107", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5107", "title": "Aerial Servant", "text": "This spell summons an &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20servant%20%28creature%29\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt; to do the caster's bidding. \nGameplay.\nThe player selects a location in range for the creature to form, and then when the spell is finished casting it will arrive on that spot.\nThe creature is summoned and can be controlled to select where it should move or what to target. Giving it no orders will cause the creature to follow its internal AI script.\nThe creature appears as a translucent air elemental figure when summoned and is a green circled controlled creature.\nThe servant is initially invisible when summoned and will remain so until it engages in an invisibility breaking action, such as attacking something.\nAfter that action the creature is for all intents and purposes no longer in a state of invisibility, although the sprite's cosmetic appearance still retains a quasi-visible appearance.\nThe servant cannot travel to another area map and must remain on the one it is summoned to.\nA servant can be destroyed with a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or if it enters a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; cloud.\nThe servant remains for the spell's duration and disappears from the map after expiration.\nFor stats and powers, abilities and more information, visit the creature page link above.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons Priest spell \"Aerial Servant\" differs from the game's implementation, in that the summoned servant will attack the summoner unless protected by a Protection from Evil spell or protection circle. Unlike some other summoned creatures, the servant will not fight for the caster and will not attack other beings. It is primarily used to carry heavy loads and to seek out and fetch items or other beings which it can capture and bring back to the priest mostly unharmed. See the External links for further reading."}
{"id": "46349", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46349", "title": "Aerial servant (creature)", "text": "Aerial Servant is a type of Air Elemental creature summoned by the spell &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThese creatures will obey their summoner for the duration of the spell, until banished by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Spell\"&gt;Death Spell&lt;/a&gt; or destroyed by damage. Once conjured, the creature is under the effects of &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, which will be broken when it attempts an offensive action.\nThe creature, when visible, has the appearance of a &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Lesser Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt;. It can only attack by way of close quarters melee combat with its ponderous crushing blows, slowly striking only once per round. If the blow connects, it deals 4d8 damage and gets a +11 bonus for strength modifier. The attack is considered a +4 enchanted item for the purposes of what it can hit.\nThe elemental is immune to the effects of any spell or item causing &lt;a href=\"Maze\"&gt;Maze&lt;/a&gt;. Normal weapons will not be able to strike this creature.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod changes the creature summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Aerial%20Servant\"&gt;Aerial Servant&lt;/a&gt; spell, see below for summary:\nThe caster of this spell summons an Aerial Servant to do the caster\u2019s bidding for the duration of the spell. The servant will attack any enemies that the caster decides, staying until the duration of the spell ends or he is slain.&lt;br&gt;\nAerial Servant (13 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 21, DEX 19, CON 17, INT 6, WIS 11, CHA 11; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 122, AC -1, THAC0 5, Saving Throws 5/7/6/5/8&lt;br&gt;\n2 Attacks Per Round, 2d6+11 Crushing Damage (Fist +2)&lt;br&gt;\nSpecial Qualities:&lt;br&gt;\nNatural Invisibility: constantly invisible as if affected by an Improved Invisibility spell&lt;br&gt;\nMovement Rate bonus: 2&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to normal weapons, hold, poison, sleep, &amp; stun effects&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "46351", "revid": "24281669", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46351", "title": "Aerial servant (monster)", "text": ""}
{"id": "4500", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4500", "title": "Aerie", "text": "Aerie is a &lt;a href=\"female\"&gt;female&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"avariel\"&gt;avariel&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"lawful%20good\"&gt;lawful good&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cleric%20/%20Mage\"&gt;cleric/mage&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\".\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may choose her as a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt;. She is the final companion available before chapter two, as further companions will require going through &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;The Slums&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nAerie is from the folk of the &lt;a href=\"Avariel\"&gt;Avariel&lt;/a&gt;, a race of winged elves, and was abducted by slavers when she was young, who sold her to a circus where she was put in a tiny cage. The terrible living conditions damaged her wings so badly, that they had to be cut off and no longer being of use to the circus, she was tossed aside. &lt;a href=\"Quayle\"&gt;Quayle&lt;/a&gt; took pity on her and attended to her wounds, but the damage turned out to be irreparable. He taught her of &lt;a href=\"Baervan%20Wildwanderer\"&gt;Baervan Wildwanderer&lt;/a&gt; and the two of them are still with the circus.\nPersonality.\nAerie is a sweet and timid young woman. She is idealistic through and through but also rather shy and unsure. Deeply traumatized by being abducted, imprisoned and losing her ability to fly, she is driven by the need to help others the best she can and often overexerts herself in the process. She hasn't seen much of the world yet, but she is a very quick learner and will soon be apt at dealing with any challenge thrown at her.\nRelationships.\nRomance.\nMale &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-elf\"&gt;half-elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"protagonist\"&gt;protagonist&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt; Aerie. This can lead to her clashing with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Dorn\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\nRecruitment.\nAerie is available to be recruited into the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; beginning in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. She is found in the second area of the &lt;a href=\"Circus%20Tent\"&gt;Circus Tent&lt;/a&gt; which is located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. She is being held captive and under an illusionary spell that makes her look like an &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt;. She will offer to join the party if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; chooses to free her or after finishing the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20circus%20tent\"&gt;investigation of the circus tent&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf not picked up or if dismissed, she can be found back at that tent.\nGameplay.\nAerie is a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Multi-class\"&gt;multi-class&lt;/a&gt; character with both &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; spells at her disposal, her capability of choosing sequencers from both wizard and priest results in many interesting combinations. Though she can become an excellent tank with the right equipment and spell enhancements, it is best to keep her in the back while using her to cast spells from a safe distance.\nHer weapon proficiencies comply with clerical restrictions and depend on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;'s level at the time of recruitment:\nIn the she will enter at 62500 &lt;a href=\"Experience%20Tables\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; for a level 8 ward and you can choose the 4th proficiency yourself once she hits level 8.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\nRecruitment.\nAerie can be summoned in the main hall of the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane&lt;/a&gt;. If dismissed she will wait there."}
