{"id": "8211", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8211", "title": "Aesgareth", "text": "Aesgareth is a &lt;a href=\"Tanar%27ri\"&gt;Tanar'ri&lt;/a&gt; cambion demon encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. At some point the demon left his own Plane and ended up getting trapped inside the maze along with a loyal &lt;a href=\"Tiefling\"&gt;Tiefling&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Cat\"&gt;Fell Cat&lt;/a&gt; retinue.\nGameplay.\nThis cambion will initiate dialogue when the party enters this area.\nThe dialogue will progress to a juncture where each party member is awarded , and then allow a response.\nIt is possible through choices and replies to basically not agree to participate or accept any proposals from the fiend - leading to a hostile reaction from Aesgareth. If this occurs, then a fight will break out.\nOtherwise, the party will eventually receive the side quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Gambling%20Cambion\"&gt;The Gambling Cambion&lt;/a&gt; through all other dialogue options. See that quest page for details, choices, and potential outcomes.\nIf the party enters into hostilities with Aesgareth, the fiend will initiate its preparatory spell buffs, and occasionally cast other spells as outlined in the InfoBox.\nAesgareth is a competent sword wielder and can go toe to toe as a close quarters' combatant. \nIt is possible that Aesgareth will receive healing assistance or other buffs from the tiefling spell casters during the battle.\nIf the fiend is defeated, then the final required &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20Gem\"&gt;Scepter Gem&lt;/a&gt; to assemble the &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Radiance\"&gt;Scepter of Radiance&lt;/a&gt; can be recovered from the fiend's body.\nAdditionally, the &lt;a href=\"Deck%20of%20Many%20Things\"&gt;Deck of Many Things&lt;/a&gt; can also be obtained from the corpse. Fighting Aesgareth is the only way to obtain this rare item.\nKilling Aesgareth causes all the other surviving servants and Fell Cats to abandon the battle and flee the area.\nNotes.\nNone of Aesgareths items can be stolen, except for the two random treasures, and those items have a -100% pick pocketing penalty. Failure turns Aesgareth hostile.\nIn the original game Aesgareth had a chaotic evil alignment and gender was male.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod places the \"Secret Manual of Golem Building (Vol 5)\" in Aesgareth's inventory.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes only one change to Aesgareth. A Random Scroll is added to his inventory."}
{"id": "49482", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49482", "title": "Afaaq the Djinni Companion", "text": "Excerpts from the Author's Mod Page - As always, have a look at the Mod developers Web content and Readme files for details and content description for the most current information and commentary.\nOverview\nAfaaq is a djinni \u2013 a genie of the Elemental Plane of Air. He is very old even in genie terms. The numerous events he witnessed in his long life have left their marks on his personality. He appears somewhat reserved and radiates a melancholic, sometimes even gloomy aura. Afaaq is more serious than others of his kind and tends to talk in a rather long-winded and convoluted way. He respects wisdom and open-mindedness, but will also tolerate foolhardy behavior to a certain degree. Everything else he can tell you by himself.\nWhen you first meet him, he is equipped with his favorite enchanted scimitar, has a small variety of spells and a couple of unusual innate abilities. The djinni gains experience much like a party member would do and levels up automatically. Depending on the choices you make during the course of the game, he may become even more useful later.\nBG2/BG2:EE content includes:\nIWD:EE content includes:\nFor more information see the link."}
{"id": "4619", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4619", "title": "Agannazar's Scorcher", "text": "Agannazar's Scorcher creates a jet of fire starting at the wizard's fingertip and ending at the target.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single target to aim the scorcher towards.\nAfter the casting time is finished, the scorcher jet leaps from the caster's fingertips and forms a continuous jet of flame ending at the target.\nFor two game seconds the caster is immobilized in terms of movement, and a sound effect is audibled. \nThe jet of flame continues for the spell's duration, and can affect the target on initial contact, and after a short delay, a second contact. Each contact exposes the target to the potentially damaging 3d6 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell can damage friendly party members should they cross the jet.\nTactical positioning from the caster can achieve clever fire damage dealing opportunities to groups of enemy creatures through maneuvering the caster and exposing multiple creatures to the jet. This may take some practice to get best outcomes by the player. In this way, a level 2 Wizard spell can often wreak havoc on enemies that aren't protected from fire.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as any spell protection, such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt; will also block this spell.\nA target protected by &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Minor Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt; will reflect part of the scorcher back to the attacker.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Wand of Fire&lt;/a&gt; can apply a version of this spell, which actually inflicts more damage but allows a saving throw, and of course has limited charges.\nNotes.\nUse of this spell by enemies in the game saga is limited. It is scripted for occasional use in combat situations to a much lesser extent than other fire damage dealing spells. For example, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt; are used much more frequently than the scorcher.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Agannazar's Scorcher\" prohibits the caster from any actions during the second-round phase of the spell cast - including moving around.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, reducing its casting time. See below for description:\nAgannazar\u2019s Scorcher\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Medium\nDuration: 2 rounds\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nUpon casting this spell, a jet of flame appears at the caster\u2019s fingertips and bursts out toward one target of the caster\u2019s choice. That target will be hit by this flame for 3d6 points of damage. The fiery ray will persist for one further round, burning the victim for another 3d6 points of fire damage. Other creatures who cross the path of the flame jet will also take damage as long as they stand in the flame. There is no saving throw against this spell, though anti-fire capabilities such as fire resistance will apply and may reduce or eliminate the damage."}
