{"id": "5036", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5036", "title": "Aid", "text": "Aid is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; that grants the target a bonus to their attack rolls, saving throws, and maximum health.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its effects, duration and description. See below:\nAid\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Necromancy\nSphere: Combat, Necromantic\nRange: Touch\nDuration: 1 turn/level\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: None\nThe recipient of this spell gains a +1 bonus to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws, plus 1d8 additional hit points +1 per level of the caster (up to a maximum of 1d8+10). The Aid spell allows the recipient to temporarily have more hit points than his full normal total. The bonus hit points are lost first when the recipient takes damage. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative.\nThis spell is only usable by Cleric/Paladin classes."}
{"id": "17066", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17066", "title": "Air Aspect", "text": "One Air Aspect is encountered in the Challenge of Air chamber located on Labyrinth Level 3 of &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. It is to be killed as part of the four chamber challenge task that must be completed to proceed to the chess board."}
{"id": "50037", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50037", "title": "Air Elemental", "text": "This Air Elemental is the basic and most common variety in the saga. It is also the most likely version summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Conjure Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; spell. Note that there are a few 10-Hit Dice Air Elementals in the basic and EE game, but their stats and abilities are practically the same as a 12-HD creature.\nMod Content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes minor revisions to all air elementals in the game. It provides them with immunity to &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; effects. It does not do this to the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; versions, as that mod already did this as well. Basically, a floating air creature will not be webbed or entangled. However, it will also be immune to &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Monster\"&gt;Hold Monster&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod re-works and changes most conjured elementals in the game. If you cast the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Conjure Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; spell, then you will get a 12 HD version if your caster's level is below level 15. The 12 Hit Dice Air Elemental has the following Abilities:&lt;br&gt;\nAir Elemental (12 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 16, DEX 19, CON 17, INT 6, WIS 11, CHA 11; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 116, AC 0, THAC0 5, Saving Throws 7/9/8/8/10&lt;br&gt;\n3 Attacks Per Round, 1d8+4 Piercing Damage (Fist +3)\nSpecial Qualities (12 &amp; 16 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to normal weapons&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects&lt;br&gt;\nSlashing, Crushing, &amp; Piercing Resistance 20%; Missile Resistance 60%"}
{"id": "39166", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39166", "title": "Air Elemental (Underdark)", "text": "This particular version of an &lt;a href=\"Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; is unique to the \"Air Gate\" in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. It may be part of the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; questline as well. Up to 11 of these creatures may come through the Air Gate, one at a time, before they cease. It is triggered by a party member in close proximity to the gate. These creatures can be triggered independently of the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mage%27s%20Proposal\"&gt;A Mage's Proposal&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nThis 10-Hit Dice air elemental has no special resistances. However, it has a undroppable ring that protects it from non-magical weapons and enchantment +1 weapons.\nMod Content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes minor revisions to all air elementals in the game. It provides them with immunity to &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Entangle\"&gt;Entangle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; effects. It does not do this to the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; versions, as that mod already did this as well. Basically, a floating air creature will not be webbed or entangled. However, it will also be immune to &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Monster\"&gt;Hold Monster&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod re-works and changes most summoned or conjured elementals in the game. If you cast the &lt;a href=\"Conjure%20Air%20Elemental\"&gt;Conjure Air Elemental&lt;/a&gt; spell, then you will get a 12 HD version if your caster's level is below level 15. The 12 Hit Dice Air Elemental has the following Abilities:&lt;br&gt;\nAir Elemental (12 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nSTR 16, DEX 19, CON 17, INT 6, WIS 11, CHA 11; AL Neutral&lt;br&gt;\nHP 116, AC 0, THAC0 5, Saving Throws 7/9/8/8/10&lt;br&gt;\n3 Attacks Per Round, 1d8+4 Piercing Damage (Fist +3)\nSpecial Qualities (12 &amp; 16 Hit Dice):&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to normal weapons&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to hold, poison, polymorph, sleep, &amp; stun effects&lt;br&gt;\nSlashing, Crushing, &amp; Piercing Resistance 20%; Missile Resistance 60%"}
{"id": "9067", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9067", "title": "Air Elemental Statue", "text": "The Air Elemental Statue is needed in &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon\"&gt;Irenicus's Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. It is needed to unlock the door to the Elemental Plane of Air near the room where &lt;a href=\"Ilyich\"&gt;Ilyich&lt;/a&gt; is. It can be found in the room next to the portal to the second level of the dungeon."}
{"id": "50639", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50639", "title": "Air Elemental Whirlwind", "text": "Air Elemental Whirlwind is an innate ability available to Air Elementals in the game saga. The ability is initiated via script by the AI. The effect is centered on the Air Elemental and will expose all enemy creatures in the area of effect to the potential 2d8 &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20damage\"&gt;Crushing damage&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spells will negate.\nIn addition to the potential crushing damage, creatures with 3 Hit Dice or less will be instantly killed, with a Crushing Death animation. The instant &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; effect has no saving throw.\nThe whirlwind effect will bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; and cannot be blocked by spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "27870", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27870", "title": "Air Library Note", "text": "The Air Library Note is found in \"\" on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;second floor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt; in the Air Library. The note details one of the four tactics to defeating the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48967", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48967", "title": "Air Mephit", "text": "An Air Mephit is an extra-planar \"outsider\" (i.e., linked to various Elemental, Quasi-Elemental and Outer planes of existence). These creatures are similar to &lt;a href=\"Imp\"&gt;Imps&lt;/a&gt;, and are found in a number of areas during the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate II\"&lt;/a&gt; games.\nGameplay.\nAn Air Mephit can attack twice per round in melee for 1d3 damage. It also has two innate abilities, one defensive and one for offensive attacks. These are &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Mephit Blur&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Breathes%20Grit\"&gt;Breathes Grit&lt;/a&gt;. Upon detection of an enemy the Mephit will instantly apply a &lt;a href=\"Blur\"&gt;Blur&lt;/a&gt; spell effect, that is essentially the same as the wizard spell. This will improve armor class and saving throws. \nThe mephit will also launch the \"Breathes Grit\" attack, which can't be blocked by any type of protection except &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;, and it deals a paltry 1d6 damage and has an area of effect similar to a &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;. The unmodified game Air Mephit can only attempt this innate ability attack every 5 rounds after the initial grit launch, meaning that it will likely be dead well before its second attempt. A Mephit is really only a threat in large numbers, and maybe slightly worse if part of a mixed variety of them.\nThe Air Mephit have no magic, physical damage or elemental resistance. The InfoBox summarizes their special abilities and immunities to certain status effects."}
{"id": "41336", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41336", "title": "Air Plane in Irenicus's Dungeon", "text": "This is a manifestation of the Plane of Air created by the mage that imprisoned &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. It is infested with air plane and fiery one to heat things up. \nGameplay.\nIt can be challenging with the limited party we have at this point to deal with the various spells thrown by the mephits on the main platform at the north end. The combination of stuns and fire damage can interrupt heals and prevent usage of potions at critical moments. It is however possible to get only one or two and lure them down the path. Another strategy is to get &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; first and take out the fire mephit through backstab as &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; doesn't have the damage and weapon to do this reliably.\nOnce they're dealt with the bottle with &lt;a href=\"Malaaq\"&gt;Malaaq&lt;/a&gt; can be found in the north-western platform."}
{"id": "27849", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27849", "title": "Air Scepter", "text": "The Air Scepter can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Elemental%20Level\"&gt;Air chamber&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThis item must be wrested from the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20Air\"&gt;Guardian of Air&lt;/a&gt; through combat. When the creature is defeated, the item can be recovered from the ground.\nThe Air scepter acts as a key that can unlock two gates on this dungeon level. These are:\nIn addition, the item is required in order to turn the Fan Control Wheel.\nAnd finally, the item is one of four scepters needed to open the cage holding the &lt;a href=\"Chromatic%20Demon\"&gt;Chromatic Demon&lt;/a&gt;."}
