{"id": "56551", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56551", "title": "Alabaster Sands walkthrough", "text": "This is a walkthrough for the content added by the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;BG2&lt;/a&gt;\" mod \"&lt;a href=\"Alabaster%20Sands\"&gt;Alabaster Sands&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "34768", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34768", "title": "Alai", "text": "Alai is one of seven servants of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;, all of whom are located on the fifth floor of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; and are under orders from Sarevok to eliminate &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; permanently. He will most likely be encountered during the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigating%20the%20Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Investigating the Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; and will fight alongside &lt;a href=\"Zhalimar%20Cloudwulfe\"&gt;Zhalimar Cloudwulfe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Aasim\"&gt;Aasim&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Diyab\"&gt;Diyab&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gardush\"&gt;Gardush&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Naaman\"&gt;Naaman&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; (in the guise of &lt;a href=\"Emissary%20Tar\"&gt;Emissary Tar&lt;/a&gt;).\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Charmed\"&gt;Charmed&lt;/a&gt;, Alai has nothing to say.\nGameplay.\nAlai and his associate Naaman have the following spells memorized:\nAlai will open combat by casting Shadow Door to turn invisible, then will begin casting Confusion at the nearest party member. After this, if he is fairly far from any party members and there is a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; in the party, he will target them with his Fireball (and may likely hit some of his allies in the process). The set of circumstances where he would cast Fireball is unlikely, but is more likely to happen if his Confusion spell worked and your party members including clerics are wandering aimlessly.\nIf party members are too close or he's unable to see a cleric to target, he will cast Flame Arrow, Horror, Melf's Acid Arrow, Agannazar's Scorcher, and Magic Missile at the nearest party member, in that order. Finally he will cast Chromatic Orb at the nearest party member who is not already stunned. Failing all of that, he will move to engage in melee combat.\nHe is immune to spells such as &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Web\"&gt;Web&lt;/a&gt; due to his equipped &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Free%20Action\"&gt;Ring of Free Action&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "9069", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9069", "title": "Alain", "text": "Alain lives in the &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28Beregost%29%23AR3329\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; next door (west side) to &lt;a href=\"The%20Burning%20Wizard\"&gt;The Burning Wizard&lt;/a&gt; inn in the town of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;. He is expecting guests and does not welcome your intrusion, should you enter his home. All is well so long as you don't speak to him, even when he sees you taking items from the locked chest, but if you initiate dialog three times, six &lt;a href=\"Guard%20%28Alain%29\"&gt;guards&lt;/a&gt; will appear and attack. If you defeat the guards, your &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; will be reduced to near zero, and the game may crash."}
{"id": "43944", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43944", "title": "Alan Blackblade", "text": "Alan Blackblade is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; who appears in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found standing in the street, in the shadows of the house located across the street from &lt;a href=\"Gantolandan%27s%20Home\"&gt;Gantolandan's Home&lt;/a&gt; in the district of &lt;a href=\"Southeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nSpeaking to him will provide you with useful information as to what &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; is up to and it will result in a quest entry under the title \"The Rise of Sarevok\"."}
{"id": "49773", "revid": "40332393", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49773", "title": "Alatelo De Bonito", "text": "Alatelo De Bonito is a bar patron in the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt;. Speak with him to hear his interesting dialogue."}
{"id": "20512", "revid": "978785", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20512", "title": "Alatos", "text": ""}
{"id": "8692", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8692", "title": "Alatos \"Ravenscar\" Thuibuld", "text": "Alatos \"Ravenscar\" Thuibuld is the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; in the city of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nSide quest.\n&lt;a href=\"Alatos%20and%20the%20Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Alatos and the Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlatos hires &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve three secret ingredients necessary for the creation of &lt;a href=\"Halruaa\"&gt;Halruaa&lt;/a&gt;n skyships. This bit of thievery has been commissioned by &lt;a href=\"Resar\"&gt;Resar&lt;/a&gt;, an envoy of the mighty nation of Halruua. If you decline Alatos' offer, continually insult him, or insist that he \"should be prepared to pay\" Alatos and the entire guild will turn hostile. Choose the following option to accept the job and avoid combat:\n\"Seems a fairly straightforward bit of burglary, and well within my ability. I accept this challenge, and hope it increases my standing within the guild.\"\nAlatos' reply: \"As it should be! Now that you have agreed, the facilities of the guild are at your disposal. Feel free to make use of them, and make your presence known to the other members. You have my permission, so they will be less likely to kill you on sight. As for your mission, you have a tenday to complete it. Informants have told me that the Duchess intends to take possession of the components that tenth day, and the exchange will be hosted by Oberon at his estate. As I see it, you have several options. Directly 'persuade' any of the involved parties to hand over the items, or burgle them out from under their noses. Good luck.\"\nJournal Update: \"I have been hired by Alatos Thuibuld to do a bit of burglary. I am to sneak into Oberon's estate and steal several magical components from the three daughters of Shandalar. These components are the ingredients for creating a Halruaan flying ship, and the Halruaans want their secret preserved and the items stolen. Alatos suggested that I either 'persuade'\u00a0 the daughters to release the items, or spirit them out from under their noses. The items are as follows: a spellbook that outlines the rituals needed, a statuette of indeterminate origin, and a fragment of a powerful artifact. I am to return to the Thieves' Guild when the items are in my possession.\"\nUpon completion of the quest, Resar will thank you and apologize that he must now kill you due to being a potential \"loose end\". Only Resar will attack you, which does not damage your &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; with the guild (unless, of course, you cause collateral damage to any of the thieves while fighting Resar).\nIf you have completed both &lt;a href=\"Narlen%27s%20Heist\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt; given to you by &lt;a href=\"Narlen%20Darkwalk\"&gt;Narlen Darkwalk&lt;/a&gt; beforehand, he will &lt;a href=\"backstab\"&gt;backstab&lt;/a&gt; Resar (in a cutscene) and no fighting will take place."}
{"id": "10428", "revid": "282262", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10428", "title": "Alatos and the Thieves' Guild", "text": "This quest is given to you by &lt;a href=\"Alatos%20%22Ravenscar%22%20Thuibuld\"&gt;Alatos \"Ravenscar\" Thuibuld&lt;/a&gt;, the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt;, who can be found at guild headquarters in the district of &lt;a href=\"East%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;East Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlatos wants you to steal three items needed for the creation of Halruaan Skyships, and gives you a \"yes or no\" ultimatum. The three items you need to steal are &lt;a href=\"Helshara%27s%20Artifact%20Fragment\"&gt;Helshara's Artifact Fragment&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Delorna%27s%20Spellbook\"&gt;Delorna's Spellbook&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ithmeera%27s%20Statue\"&gt;Ithmeera's Statue&lt;/a&gt;. In the original Baldur's Gate Ithmeera's Statue is incorrectly named Delorna's Statue. If you decline Alatos' offer, continually insult him, or insist that he \"should be prepared to pay,\" Alatos and the entire guild will turn hostile. Choose the following option to accept the job and avoid combat:\n\"Seems a fairly straightforward bit of burglary, and well within my ability. I accept this challenge, and hope it increases my standing within the guild.\"\nAlatos' reply: \"As it should be! Now that you have agreed, the facilities of the guild are at your disposal. Feel free to make use of them, and make your presence known to the other members. You have my permission, so they will be less likely to kill you on sight. As for your mission, you have a tenday to complete it. Informants have told me that the Duchess intends to take possession of the components that tenth day, and the exchange will be hosted by Oberon at his estate. As I see it, you have several options. Directly 'persuade' any of the involved parties to hand over the items, or burgle them out from under their noses. Good luck.\"\nJournal Update: \"I have been hired by Alatos Thuibuld to do a bit of burglary. I am to sneak into Oberon's estate and steal several magical components from the three daughters of Shandalar. These components are the ingredients for creating a Halruaan flying ship, and the Halruaans want their secret preserved and the items stolen. Alatos suggested that I either 'persuade'\u00a0 the daughters to release the items, or spirit them out from under their noses. The items are as follows: a spellbook that outlines the rituals needed, a statuette of indeterminate origin, and a fragment of a powerful artifact. I am to return to the Thieves' Guild when the items are in my possession.\"\nThe items are guarded by &lt;a href=\"Delorna\"&gt;Delorna&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Helshara\"&gt;Helshara&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Ithmeera\"&gt;Ithmeera&lt;/a&gt; on the third floor of &lt;a href=\"Oberan%27s%20Estate\"&gt;Oberan's Estate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Central%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Central Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. You have 10 game days to accomplish this or you will fail the quest and Alatos will rebuke you for your failure the next time you talk to him.\nIf you enter the premises unarmed (fists selected as weapons with main character) and talk to &lt;a href=\"Glanmarie\"&gt;Glanmarie&lt;/a&gt; you can claim to be a servant (dialogue options 'new position' and 'no experience' will do the trick, though she will summon guards if she becomes suspicious). &lt;a href=\"Oberan\"&gt;Oberan&lt;/a&gt; on the second floor will ignore you, and assume you are new guards if you are armed. On the third floor you will be hailed by one of the three daughters. They will get suspicious of you and subsequently fighting will break out. The three items needed for the quest are stored away in an unlocked vanity in one of the bedrooms. Nobody else in the house will have noticed your violent slaughter of the wizards so you can leave undisturbed.\nIt is possible to retrieve the items without any killing if you send in somebody using &lt;a href=\"Stealth\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; to pick them up. There is nobody in the room where the items are stored, so you can easily grab them and sneak out again without being spotted. &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; makes the heist even simpler since there is no need to recast it after collecting the goods. Avoiding conflict is useful if you want to avoid angering &lt;a href=\"Shandalar\"&gt;Shandalar&lt;/a&gt; by killing his daughters.\nIn , if your thief is discovered, you can still complete the quest with only a loss of one &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; point. Leave all extra party members outside the Estate. Take your thief and attempt to bypass the sisters' conversation. If that fails and your &lt;a href=\"Stealth\"&gt;Stealth&lt;/a&gt; doesn't work, allow the combat but do not engage the sisters. Immediately move to the desk and loot it. Then immediately proceed downstairs and exit the Estate. Your party members will attack and kill the sisters, regardless of their alignment. Immediately exit the map to avoid the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; and loss of party members with good &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;Alignment&lt;/a&gt;. Come back to the map and loot.\nEither way, return to the thieves' guild and speak to Alatos again. Alatos will rebuke you if you killed the sisters and use it for justification as &lt;a href=\"Resar\"&gt;Resar&lt;/a&gt; removes the items and attacks you for being a loose end. Only Resar will become hostile, as long as you don't hurt any of the thieves during the fighting, and he can be killed without any loss of reputation within the guild."}
{"id": "7478", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7478", "title": "Alaundo", "text": "Alaundo was an ancient seer who had foretold, among other things, the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt; and creation of the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\", there is a small group of chanters standing in the western inner grounds of &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;, chanting a few of Alaundo's cryptic prophecies."}
{"id": "7584", "revid": "78773", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7584", "title": "Albert", "text": "Albert is a planar traveler who is found in the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Leaf%20Forest\"&gt;Fire Leaf Forest&lt;/a&gt; area, south of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;, at coordinates &lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;1356,968&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe first appears as a human child looking for his \"dog\", &lt;a href=\"Rufie\"&gt;Rufie&lt;/a&gt;. After he rejoins with the pet, or if he is attacked, he reverts to his true form, that of a chaotic &lt;a href=\"Alignment\"&gt;evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Mage\"&gt;Ogre Mage&lt;/a&gt; /lawful evil &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;Pit Fiend&lt;/a&gt; , and uses a &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt; to transport them both to the &lt;a href=\"Nine%20Hells\"&gt;Nine Hells&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8860", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8860", "title": "Albert and His Dog", "text": "Albert and His Dog is the side quest to find and return dear little &lt;a href=\"Rufie\"&gt;Rufie&lt;/a&gt; to his master.\nAcquisition.\n&lt;a href=\"Albert\"&gt;Albert&lt;/a&gt;, found in the northwest part of the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Leaf%20Forest\"&gt;Fire Leaf Forest&lt;/a&gt;, has lost his dog; he gives you the dog's &lt;a href=\"Chew%20Toy\"&gt;Chew Toy&lt;/a&gt; to help bring &lt;a href=\"Rufie\"&gt;Rufie&lt;/a&gt; back. \nFinding Rufie.\nRufie can be found near the northeast corner of the same map&lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;3800.690&lt;/a&gt;. He will run to the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; and follow them peacefully if his toy is in their possession, otherwise he is hostile. When he follows the party, he won't be helping them against any enemies.\nRewards.\nThe experience reward for returning with Rufie is 1000 xp and possibly some item (see below), but the reward for quest \"failure\" \u2014 returning after killing Rufie \u2014 is 1200 XP + 175 XP from killing Rufie! If the party chooses to attack and kill Albert instead, who subsequently transforms to a &lt;a href=\"Pit%20Fiend\"&gt;Pit Fiend&lt;/a&gt; , they will only get , so it's not worth it.\nAlbert's dialogue, \"Here, take this. It's another of his chew things [\u2026]\" indicates an item reward, which ranges from nothing at all to a &lt;a href=\"Bandit%20Scalp\"&gt;Bandit Scalp&lt;/a&gt; to a , depending on the game version and mods that are possibly installed.\nDialog.\n\"'Scuse me. I ever so sowwy to bother, but could you help me? I've lost my little dog and I can't find him. He's probably ever so scared wight now.\"\nIf you return with Rufie:\nIf you return to Albert after killing Rufie:\nJournal.\nIn a unique twist, refusing and failing the quest are a form of quest completion (which actually has better rewards than normal quest completion):"}
