{"id": "49985", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49985", "title": "Alorgoth", "text": "The Dark Moon Monk Collus Darathon is revealed to actually be Alorgoth and is a character from and part of &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nAlorgoth has created a bogus order called the Two-Fold Trust for his own hidden machinations. He has duped and mislead scores of \"Heretics\" - Monks, followers of Selune, Shar and others. Rasaad has his suspicions that Collus and Alorgoth were the same person and has been proved correct. \nAlorgoth will order the attacking Sharrans to destroy the Heretic Temple defenders. He will then quickly depart the map. The quest and plot line has made sure Alorgoth is immune to death and all status effects so as to ensure his survival and exit for later plot purposes. Don't waste your time and resources trying to take down this creature as he is nigh invulnerable.\nAlorgoth has all the abilities, immunities and special bonuses afforded to a Dark Moon Monk, and commensurate with his 19th Level experience. He is not meant to be killed or destroyed as determined by the game script, and he will leave the Heretic Temple exterior after the dialogue with the party is finished, no matter what the outcome."}
{"id": "39506", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39506", "title": "Alorgoth's Journal", "text": "The Alorgoth's Journal is the journal of &lt;a href=\"Alorgoth\"&gt;Alorgoth&lt;/a&gt; and can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Deepstone%20Clanhold\"&gt;Deepstone Clanhold&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt looks like having this item in your possession prevents a trap that destroys items from triggering."}
{"id": "49485", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49485", "title": "Alternatives", "text": "The mod description and text below excerpted from the author's (Jastey) readme and mod description. For further details and latest updates, recommend visiting at the mod's hosted web location.\nThis mod offers two new possibilities to consider when making the decision about whether to side with the Shadow Thieves or with Valen's Mistress. In addition to the traditional two, the player may now opt to side with a group even the paladins in the party could have no objection to... or he may opt to skip the whole decision entirely and set sail for Maztica.\nAlternatives also offers a different way to satisfy Mae Var's demand that the protagonist steal an artifact from a temple.\nIt is nearly impossible for a lawful good character to go through the game and remain completely true to his or her alignment. Siding with thieves is not a very lawful thing to do, nor is allying with undead a particularly good deed. The \"Paladin Route\" offers a third option, the ability to work for an unimpeachably good organization and eliminate two evils. The \"Assassin Route\" came about a bit later, as a result of some musing about how a character who has no real interest in either rescuing Imoen or going out of his or her way to take revenge on Irenicus might want to avoid the whole decision entirely and get the hells out of Amn. Jastey never liked the concept of stealing prized artifacts from temples while running errands for Mae Var, so she created a work-around for that, as well. The latter component is also incorporated in Jastey's Ajantis mod, so Ajantis is installed, the \"Temple Thievery Alternative\" component will not be installed.\nBoth new options begin after Valen and Brus make their traditional appearances. To begin the \"Paladin Route,\" visit the Government District after speaking with Brus. To begin the \"Assassin Route,\" go to the Slums, where a garishly dressed nobleman by the name of Malficus will make an attractive offer. He is standing outside the Copper Coronet, not far from the road that leads to the southern entrance to the Slums.\nOnce the protagonist has committed to performing the first task of the \"Paladin Route,\" all other paths are disabled, but it is possible to do two of the three tasks Malficus sets before you and then change sides.\nTo access the \"Temple Thievery Alternative\" options, speak to people in the temple about your concerns.\nSUGGESTIONS: When one deals with dishonorable people, some treachery and double-dealing is only to be expected. Also, when embarking on a new venture, it is always advisable to tie up loose ends first. Thieves, especially, or those wishing to get to know Renal Bloodscalp a little better or recruit a certain Red Wizard, would be well advised to complete all thieves' guild tasks prior to going to the Five Flagons in or making any final arrangements with Malficus. The quest givers of both routes will warn you when you are approaching the point of no return.\nFor more information see the link."}
{"id": "7883", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7883", "title": "Alturiak", "text": ""}
{"id": "40542", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40542", "title": "Alu-Fiend", "text": "The Alu-Fiend is a hybrid creature formed from a &lt;a href=\"Succubus\"&gt;Succubus&lt;/a&gt; mother and a mortal (usually human) father.\nSeveral of these fiends are encountered in a specific area of the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;. See the InfoBox.\nGameplay.\nThe Alu-Fiend is designed to avoid melee combat initially during combat and throw it's &lt;a href=\"Dart%20of%20Wounding\"&gt;Dart of Wounding&lt;/a&gt; ammunition by keeping distance from detected targets through maneuver.\nEnemies detected will also be targeted with the super potent &lt;a href=\"Succubus%20charm%20male\"&gt;Succubus charm male&lt;/a&gt; innate spell. Not only can it charm, but it also temporarily lowers the target's saving throws vs. Spells.\nThis charm can be used over and over again, as long as the fiend is still functioning, but the AI does keep track of which opponent it attempted to charm previously and will select another target if available.\nIf forced into melee combat, the fiend battles with its dual-wielded undroppable &lt;a href=\"Kundane\"&gt;Kundane&lt;/a&gt; short swords. Rapid attacks per round are possible.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Succubus\"&gt;Succubus&lt;/a&gt; in this area departs the battlefield via &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt; (due to enough HP loss), the Alu-Fiend will attempt to do the same. It may also do this independently if its HP falls to only &lt;25% remaining.\nThis creature may quaff a healing potion when damaged past a certain threshold. It may also apply an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; if it detects an enemy creature with a &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Alu-Fiend%20%2820%20Hit%20Dice%29\"&gt;Alu-Fiend (20 Hit Dice)&lt;/a&gt; for a different variety of the fiend.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod, and especially with the \"Improved Fiends and Celestials\" component will revise this creature in several ways.\nThe creature now has a &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt; kit, although the creature isn't configured for this kit as a true Kensai, but regardless, the Berserker kit is removed.\nThe fiend's stats are changed to Dex 17, Con 19, Int 18, Wis 16 and Chr 16, and it is now a 12 HD creature that cast spells at level 12.\nThe AI is changed. The creature now gains the use of &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt; Wizard spells.\nIt still has the uses of &lt;a href=\"Succubus%20charm%20male\"&gt;Succubus charm male&lt;/a&gt; innate spell, as well as a \"Succubus charm female\" version as well (SPIN929).\nThe creature gains immunity to several electricity-based spells."}
{"id": "55917", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55917", "title": "Alu-Fiend (20 Hit Dice)", "text": "The Alu-Fiend (20 Hit Dice) creature is a variety of fiend found as a potential random spawn in two areas inside the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Teleport%20Maze\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Teleport Maze&lt;/a&gt;, as well as a spawned creature during a particular phase of the final battle in &lt;a href=\"The%20Throne%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;The Throne of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe Alu-Fiend is designed to avoid melee combat initially during combat and throw it's &lt;a href=\"Dart%20of%20Wounding\"&gt;Dart of Wounding&lt;/a&gt; ammunition by keeping distance from detected targets through maneuver.\nEnemies detected will also be targeted with a super potent &lt;a href=\"Succubus%20charm%20male\"&gt;Charm person&lt;/a&gt; innate spell. Not only can it charm, but it also temporarily lowers the target's saving throws vs. Spells.\nThis charm can be used over and over again, as long as the fiend is still functioning, but the AI does keep track of which opponent it attempted to charm previously and will select another target if available.\nIf forced into melee combat, the fiend battles with its enchanted &lt;a href=\"Water%27s%20Edge\"&gt;Water's Edge&lt;/a&gt; scimitar. The creature has no weapon proficiency with this weapon type, and thus gets a THAC0 penalty. The values in the InfoBox take this into account.\nThe fiend will attempt to depart the battlefield and flee via &lt;a href=\"Dimension%20Door\"&gt;Dimension Door&lt;/a&gt; if its HP falls to only &lt;25% remaining.\nThis creature may quaff a healing potion when damaged past a certain threshold. It may also apply an &lt;a href=\"Oil%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Oil of Speed&lt;/a&gt; if it detects an enemy creature with a &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Alu-Fiend\"&gt;Alu-Fiend&lt;/a&gt; for a different variety of the creature.\nMod Content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod, and especially with the \"Improved Fiends and Celestials\" component will revise this creature in several ways.\nThe creature's base &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; is now 0.\nThe fiend's stats are changed to Dex 17, Con 19, Int 18, Wis 16 and Chr 16, and it is now a 12 HD creature that cast spells at level 12.\nThe AI is changed. The creature now gains the use of &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Secret%20Word\"&gt;Secret Word&lt;/a&gt; Wizard spells.\nIt still has the uses of &lt;a href=\"Succubus%20charm%20male\"&gt;Succubus charm male&lt;/a&gt; innate spell, as well as a \"Succubus charm female\" version as well (SPIN929).\nSCS provides the fiend with elemental damage resistance (50% fire, cold, and 100% electricity). The creature is also immune to &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt; and can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe creature gains immunity to several electricity-based spells."}
{"id": "7398", "revid": "34236415", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7398", "title": "Alustriel Silverhand", "text": "Alustriel Silverhand is both a &lt;a href=\"Chosen\"&gt;Chosen&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Mystra\"&gt;Mystra&lt;/a&gt; and one of her daughters, one of the Seven Sisters, and the ruler of Silverymoon.\nShe appears in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Caverns\"&gt;City of Caverns&lt;/a&gt; as an illusion created by &lt;a href=\"Riddle%20of%20the%20Imps\"&gt;two imps for their riddle game&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "7032", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7032", "title": "Alvanhendar", "text": "Alvanhendar runs the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Yondalla%20and%20Alvanhendar%27s%20Fine%20Wines\"&gt;Temple of Yondalla and Alvanhendar's Fine Wines&lt;/a&gt; in the area of &lt;a href=\"Gullykin\"&gt;Gullykin&lt;/a&gt;. He offers the usual temple services, and berates the party as \"intrepid fools on the way to a beating\", amid other pithy comments.\nThere is no &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt; loss if he is killed.\nDialogue.\n\"Eh? Who's this then? More intrepid fools on the road to a beating? I suppose ye need the healing or some such to repair whatever damage ye marched headlong into. Well, the Provider provides and the Provider protects, but don't ye go messing up her handiwork anytime soon! And stand ye away from them barrels of ale! Littleman watches over all, and he'll turn you out on your ear if you damage a cork in his spiritual home.\""}
