{"id": "51771", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51771", "title": "Amac", "text": "Amac is a boy in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; who is frightened and doesn't like the genies or the druids that have caused so much trouble.\nGameplay.\nSpeaking with the child results in some shrill comments from the lad.\nIf Cernd is in the party, the boy will shout \"\"That's that nasty druid that my daddy said they were gonna burn! Ye're gonna pay, nasty druid!\"\nIf you keep talking with him, perhaps trying to calm him down, his eyes widen and shouts: \"Ahhh! Ye're those people with the swords an' spells an' scars an' stuff! Ahhh!\"\nThe child may run away saying: \"My daddy says ye're gonna kill everyone! Yahhhh!\"\"\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Afaaq%20the%20Djinni%20Companion\"&gt;Afaaq the Djinni Companion&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, and Afaaq out of his bottle and moving as a companion, Amac will have additional anti-genie comments."}
{"id": "26943", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26943", "title": "Amalas", "text": "Amalas is a &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;, standing in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; next to two ruffian pals.\nGameplay.\nHe will initiate bullying dialogue when a Gorion's Ward is close enough - and he'll attempt to insult and goad the PC into a duel in the fighting pit, managed by &lt;a href=\"Surly\"&gt;Surly&lt;/a&gt;. Seems like he must have done this sort of thing before.\nIf &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; is a companion, she has some words that you should restrain yourself from accepting the challenge.\nIf you turn down his challenge to fight and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt; is in the group, he will attack Amalas for insulting &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, leading to a battle with Amalas and the Ruffians.\nWinning the duel nets 9,500 experience (plus 1,800 for killing Amalas).\nIf the Ward defeats Amalas, the two remaining ruffians won't be hostile or say anything, but they can be attacked and fought with no consequences, if desired. The Copper Coronet is one of those places where deadly fights can frequently occur.\nNote.\nAmalas has a Chaotic Neutral alignment in the original game, but it is changed to LE in the Enhanced Edition.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Amalas and his ruffian pals with a new default fighter script for smarter tactical behavior and potion use.\nHis weapon proficiencies are revised to 4 pips in long sword and adding 2 pips in single weapon fighting style.\nA potion is assigned to the quick slot for healing purposes when wounded to 50% damage."}
