{"id": "48160", "revid": "270839", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48160", "title": "Amnian Legionary", "text": "Amnian Legionaries are members of the Amnian Military who concentrate on keeping the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; safe from those that would flaunt the rules of civility, including violence and theft of property, and other unlawful conduct.\nAppearances.\nAMNLEG1.cre.\nFour of these Amnian Legionaries are part of the contingent of enforcers that will appear when an individual or a party with a low &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; triggers reputation alarm points within the city.\nBetween two to four will appear if any type of attempted thievery has been observed by the local populace whether indoors in some area, or outdoors. \nThis can be triggered with CTALARM.bcs script as well, which is initiated by the opening of certain containers (like a chest or drawer). An example would be the containers in &lt;a href=\"Pimlico%20Estate\"&gt;Pimlico Estate&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Cromwell%27s%20Home\"&gt;Cromwell's Home&lt;/a&gt;, and other places.\nThey also make an appearance if you:\nThis Legionary will always appear as an enemy and killing them will not affect your reputation.\nAMNLEGS.cre.\nThis Amnian Legionary will appear when citizens attempt to sleep outside within the city limits (except for the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;City Gates&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; districts). After rousting you from your attempted slumber, he'll leave and disappear. Killing this Legionary will result in a loss of reputation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nohnamns.cre.\nIn during &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest, four of these Amnian Legionaries will accompany the &lt;a href=\"minotaur\"&gt;minotaur&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ghallus\"&gt;Ghallus&lt;/a&gt; when the creature returns to help defeat &lt;a href=\"Lanneth\"&gt;Lanneth&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt;. They will fight on your behalf and no reputation loss will be incurred should they die as a result of friendly fire or if they become &lt;a href=\"Domination\"&gt;dominated&lt;/a&gt; by enemy wizards during battle."}
