{"id": "49926", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49926", "title": "Amphitheater Guard", "text": "The Ampitheater Guard is a character from . He is a Dark Moon Monk who challenges anyone trying to enter the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Amphitheater\"&gt;Abandoned Amphitheater&lt;/a&gt;. If you give the correct response, he will let you pass unmolested. \nAlthough he is a 13th level Monk kitted as a Dark Moon Monk, the creature has not been provided any kit specific innate abilities associated with a Dark Moon Monk of this experience level. He will fight with his Monk fists and kick attacks. This creature does however have all the immunities, movement modifiers, defensive bonuses that a level 13 Monk naturally should have, including attack speed (initiative bonus), free action and 100% poison resistance etc."}
{"id": "38932", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38932", "title": "Amuana", "text": "Amuana was a female child prophet born to the faith of &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;, the now-deceased God of the Sun, generations before the &lt;a href=\"Time%20of%20Troubles\"&gt;Time of Troubles&lt;/a&gt;. Although it was hoped that she would lead a resurgence in the waning faith of her patron, it was not to be; slain in her youth by enemies of Amaunator, her remains were entombed at what is now the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; passes that way, &lt;a href=\"Amuana%27s%20Bones\"&gt;her skeletal remains&lt;/a&gt; are being desecrated by the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Wolf\"&gt;shadow-spawned wolves&lt;/a&gt; that have made their lair inside of the now-corrupted temple. The ghosts of &lt;a href=\"Badon%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Badon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dettseh%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Dettseh&lt;/a&gt;, her custodians in life, are powerless to rescue them, and plead with Gorion's Ward to restore them to her coffin. Doing so is mandatory to complete the quest &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the Deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;; only by restoring her bones and resanctifying her coffin will the ghost of Amuana appear in order to grant the &lt;a href=\"Dawn%27s%20Light%20Symbol\"&gt;Dawn's Light Symbol&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt;, allowing them access to the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Altar\"&gt;Shadow Altar&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt; at the end of the dungeon."}
{"id": "28151", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28151", "title": "Amuana's Bones", "text": "Amuana's Bones are the preserved skeleton of &lt;a href=\"Amuana\"&gt;Amuana&lt;/a&gt;, a child-prophetess (who was struck down before her time) of the faded sun-deity &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt;. \nPurpose.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;, a pair of ghostly fighter-servants of Amuana named &lt;a href=\"Badon%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Badon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dettseh%27s%20Ghost\"&gt;Dettseh&lt;/a&gt;, will plead for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve Amuana's Bones and restore them to her tomb, which they guard. In exchange, they offer a piece of the &lt;a href=\"Dawn%27s%20Light%20Symbol\"&gt;Dawn's Light Symbol&lt;/a&gt;, a key necessary to reach the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Altar\"&gt;Shadow Altar&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Lord\"&gt;Shade Lord&lt;/a&gt; guarding it.\nLocation.\nAmuana's Bones can be found in the first room of the Ruined Temple, the &lt;a href=\"Shade%20Wolf\"&gt;Shade Wolf&lt;/a&gt; lair, tucked into a bundle of rocks."}
