ven.\nRewards.\nThe exact reward and the final &lt;a href=\"journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; entry depend on &lt;a href=\"Fuller\"&gt;Fuller&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"reaction\"&gt;reaction&lt;/a&gt; to the character who returns the &lt;a href=\"bolt\"&gt;bolt&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "9966", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9966", "title": "An Offer from Taerom", "text": "An Offer from Taerom (aka \"A New Suit of Armor\") is a side quest in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; that can be undertaken after acquiring an &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Shell\"&gt;Ankheg Shell&lt;/a&gt;. Take the shell to &lt;a href=\"Taerom%20Fuiruim\"&gt;Taerom Fuiruim&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Thunderhammer%20Smithy\"&gt;his shop&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt; and he will offer to buy it. Either sell it for 500 , or refuse his initial offer and get a nice set of custom &lt;a href=\"Ankheg%20Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Ankheg Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt; armor made instead (which can only be done once). This will cost 4,000 and will take ten days to forge (three days in the ). Also in the Enhanced Edition, if he's paid 6,000 he'll get it done in one day. Whether or not he makes the armor, it is possible to bring him more shells for additional gold."}
