{"id": "41340", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41340", "title": "Ancient Menhirs", "text": "Ancient Menhirs is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki/Baldur%2527s_Gate%3A_Siege_of_Dragonspear\"&gt;Baldur's Gate: Siege of Dragonspear&lt;/a&gt;\", available in &lt;a href=\"https%3A//baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki/Coast_Way_Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt; during chapter eight.\nWalkthrough.\n1. Talk to &lt;a href=\"Prin\"&gt;Prin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Coast%20Way%20Crossing\"&gt;Coast Way Crossing&lt;/a&gt;.\n2. Find all six menhirs in the area. Using a character with at least 16 &lt;a href=\"Charisma\"&gt;Charisma&lt;/a&gt;, sing to each menhir to activate it. If your Charisma is lower than 16, the following will occur:\nNote: Console players going for &lt;a href=\"achievements\"&gt;achievements&lt;/a&gt; or trophies must deliberately use a low Charisma character, such as Dynaheir, Viconia or Minsc, to trigger the riddle, as answering it correctly is required for the Riddlemaster achievement.\n3. When the last menhir is activated, &lt;a href=\"Crommus\"&gt;Crommus&lt;/a&gt; will appear. He will inform you about a treasure cache located in the &lt;a href=\"Dwarven%20Dig%20Site\"&gt;Dwarven Dig Site&lt;/a&gt;; this cache will only appear after you have talked to Crommus. Crommus will tell you that Karnass had arranged Carline to marry Artipheon.4. In the cache is the &lt;a href=\"Bard%20Hat\"&gt;Bard Hat&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Tangled%20Strings\"&gt;Tangled Strings&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Star-Strewn%20Boots\"&gt;Star-Strewn Boots&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Crommus%27s%20Capelet\"&gt;Crommus's Capelet&lt;/a&gt;.\n5. Return to Prin and tell her what you have learned about the menhirs. She will give you the &lt;a href=\"Reed%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Reed of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;."}
