{"id": "7969", "revid": "4896558", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7969", "title": "Andarsson", "text": "Andarsson is one of many slaves found in the &lt;a href=\"Cloakwood%20Mines\"&gt;Cloakwood Mines&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". He's a bit more willful than the other slaves and not particularly afraid of punishment, given what he and others have to say.\nLike most slaves in the area, he merely serves to help reinforce the setting and their predicament; in Andarsson's case, his dialogue implies that he wasn't always a slave and that he has a very bleak future."}
{"id": "8936", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8936", "title": "Ander", "text": "Ander is a farmer who now lives with his wife &lt;a href=\"Johanna\"&gt;Johanna&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale\"&gt;Imnesvale&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. Originally living in a farmhouse, he and his wife often had to stay in the village's &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; due to his house being damaged. Learn more by speaking with him."}
{"id": "49836", "revid": "49127847", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49836", "title": "Andorian", "text": "Andorian is a &lt;a href=\"minotaur\"&gt;minotaur&lt;/a&gt; found battling a &lt;a href=\"Myconid%20King\"&gt;Myconid King&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Myconid\"&gt;Myconid&lt;/a&gt;s, surrounded by his fallen comrades in a small earthen cave, accessed from northeren part of the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;Sewers of the Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs Andorian is either killed by the myconids, or dies by script after they are defeated, little is known about the minotaur's background. Although , one of the Baldur's Gate 2 game designers later revealed, that it was a D&amp;D character of one of his friends, which was added when populating the game.\nDespite having 100 maximum hp, Andorian will only have 10 hp when the player enters the room, which means almost any damaging area of effect spell can be used to finish him off inside the fog of war, before the Myconids get him, for 3000XP.\nMod Content.\nInstalling the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//spellholdstudios.github.io/readmes/slandor-readme-english.html\"&gt;The Minotaur and Lilarcor&lt;/a&gt; mod adds some content to Andorian if you speak with him. This is just a short mod with a few extra features to flesh out the Sewers."}
