{"id": "5522", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5522", "title": "Angelo Dosan", "text": "Angelo Dosan is a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; and corrupt &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; officer who is a lackey of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; and briefly becomes head of the organization when &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt; is incapacitated, and &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt; is killed by a doppelganger. He is the father of &lt;a href=\"Shar%20Teel\"&gt;Shar Teel&lt;/a&gt;. He'll make a second appearance in the .\nBaldur's Gate.\nFlaming Fist Headquarters.\nThe player first encounters Angelo in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; during a cut scene. If the player gets captured by the Flaming Fist after being accused of \"murder most foul\" whilst in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, the player and their party will be sentenced by Angelo to be hanged and will wait in the Flaming Fist HQ jail cells until the time for their death comes. Due to family relations, if Shar-Teel is in the party Angelo will simply let you go.\nTemple of Bhaal.\nAngelo is then encountered at the end of Chapter Seven with Sarevok, &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Semaj\"&gt;Semaj&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;. During the battle between them and the player, Angelo will be wearing a ring of invisibility and is equipped with arrows of detonation which release fireballs upon reaching its target.\nThrone of Bhaal.\nAngelo will appear in the second challenge in the &lt;a href=\"Pocket%20Plane%20%28area%29\"&gt;Pocket Plane&lt;/a&gt; after you have killed &lt;a href=\"Yaga-Shura\"&gt;Yaga-Shura&lt;/a&gt;. You will have to fight him, Tamoko, Semaj, and an aspect of yourself had &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt; chosen Sarevok over you."}
{"id": "50399", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50399", "title": "Angelo NPC", "text": "The Angelo NPC for Baldur's Gate II mod adds &lt;a href=\"Angelo%20Dosan\"&gt;Angelo Dosan&lt;/a&gt;, the minor &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt; character, to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;BG2&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;joinable NPC&lt;/a&gt;.\nNPC background.\nRaised by a Yakuza-style crime syndicate in &lt;a href=\"Kara-Tur\"&gt;Kara-Tur&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nLater served &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nRecently fled the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;, seeking to join &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrossmod content.\nThe following mods provide an alternative portrait for Angelo:"}
{"id": "50391", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50391", "title": "Angelo NPC walkthrough", "text": "The \"&lt;a href=\"Angelo%20NPC\"&gt;Angelo NPC for Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" mod by \"Sister Vigilante\" adds &lt;a href=\"Angelo%20Dosan\"&gt;Angelo Dosan&lt;/a&gt;, the minor &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt; character, to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;BG2&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;joinable NPC&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe comes with two personal quests.&lt;br&gt;\nThis is a walkthrough for that quest content.&lt;br&gt;\nSPOILER WARNING!\nHow to get him to join.\nHe stands in the &lt;a href=\"Graveyard%20District\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; \"(outdoors, near the northern exit)\". Talk to him."}
{"id": "39162", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39162", "title": "Anguiliian", "text": "The Anguiliian is a creature that appears like a Frost Salamander, and is meant to be some kind of spear wielding avenging warrior of the Shark Father Sekolah.\nGameplay.\nThis is a summoned creature that may appear only in the &lt;a href=\"Underwater%20City\"&gt;Underwater City&lt;/a&gt;. It is actually summoned by script, not some kind of conjuring from a specific spell casting &lt;a href=\"Sahuagin\"&gt;Sahuagin&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe triggered events that lead to this creature's appearance relate to whether the party is viewed as an enemy of the &lt;a href=\"King%20Ixilthetocal\"&gt;King Ixilthetocal&lt;/a&gt; and the entire city populace is made hostile to the PC. Once a global called \"hatePC's\" is set, then it's too late, and the events will initiate.\nFor example, right from the very first exchange of dialogue with &lt;a href=\"Royal%20High%20Priestess%20Senityili\"&gt;Royal High Priestess Senityili&lt;/a&gt; the party can refuse to cooperate even a little bit with the sahuagin. This will make the entire populace hostile to the party (shuttering &lt;a href=\"The%20prophecy%20of%20Sekolah\"&gt;The prophecy of Sekolah&lt;/a&gt; quest elements). If that occurs, then the script will trigger that can summon the Anguillan and other creatures to help defend the city.\nThe summoning of the Anguiliian is also accompanied by various summoned &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; (such as several &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Warrior\"&gt;Skeleton Warrior&lt;/a&gt; creatures, and holy retribution spell casts on the party (ostensibly by Sekolah), including &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Strike\"&gt;Flame Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Command\"&gt;Command&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Rigid%20Thinking\"&gt;Rigid Thinking&lt;/a&gt;. \nThese creatures appear alongside other sahuagin defenders in the center part of the map, and there are two scripted summoning events.\nAs interesting as this event may sound, these summoned creatures really aren't a threat of any consequence to a party at this stage of the saga. The retribution of Sekola is mostly for visual enhancement and a bit of flavor to the fact that the party has decided to take on the whole populace and forego any role-playing opportunities in this area. Every sahuagin will be an enemy on this map from now on. Let the slaughter commence.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the creature by assigning spear and two-handed weapon style proficiencies (which the base game did not do).\nIt also provides immunities to entangle, web and few other effects that are to reflect that these creatures are large and can't be restricted by that sort of stuff.\nThe original &lt;a href=\"Tactics%20Mod\"&gt;Tactics Mod&lt;/a&gt; which can still work with the non-EE original classic game made the challenge level much greater in the City of Caverns. That mod increases the difficulty factor to a real threat."}
{"id": "5402", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5402", "title": "Angurvadal", "text": "Angurvadal +4, also known as the Stream of Anguish, is an cold iron and silver longsword. It is obtainable in and .\nAquisition.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Captain%20%28githyanki%20WK%29\"&gt;Captain (githyanki WK)&lt;/a&gt; wields this blade on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt; area, a submap reachable from the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Machine%20of%20Lum%20the%20Mad\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Machine of Lum the Mad&lt;/a&gt; area.\nIt can only be obtained if taken by force from the githyanki Captain.\nGameplay.\nThis long sword inflicts 1d8+4 points of &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; and 1 point of &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; on any successful hit. \nIt has a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus of 4, a reach of 1 and a speed factor of 1. \nOnce per day, the blade provides the wielder with an opportunity to \"cast\" a spell-like effect on self, which sets the &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute to 22. \nThis lasts for 1 turn (10-rounds), and it can't be dispelled.\nAfter a standard 8-hour rest period, the blade recharges and the ability can be used again.\nThis sword can be upgraded by &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; the imp for and it requires the &lt;a href=\"Liquid%20Mercury\"&gt;Liquid Mercury&lt;/a&gt; component. \nUpgraded.\nGameplay.\nOnce upgraded by Cespenar, the blade is improved to Angurvadal +5 and it deals 1d8+5 points of slashing damage plus 1d4+1 points of fire damage and grants a THAC0 bonus of 5.\nThe speed factor improves from 1 to 0, allowing first strike capability in many melee battles. \nAdditionally, the wielder is immune to &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; effects and &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; attribute is set to 22.\nLegend.\nb = Before the upgrade;\na = After the upgrade"}
