{"id": "5951", "revid": "1966519", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5951", "title": "Animal trouble in Trademeet", "text": "Animal trouble in Trademeet is a &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; that the party first learns about from a messenger sent from Trademeet to find aid.\nAcquisition.\nThe first time the party enters the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flydian\"&gt;Flydian&lt;/a&gt; will approach and ask them to help his town with its animal problems.\"I am a messenger sent by the High Merchant of Trademeet to find someone to help our town.\u00a0 You look like adventurers... you might be just the sort of help we need. ...Lord Logan Coprith, mayor and High Merchant of Trademeet\" [is] \"willing to offer a substantial reward for anyone who can help Trademeet out of its... difficulties.\"Agree to help and he adds the area of &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; to the player's map: \"Here, I can show you on your map.\u00a0 Do you think you might be able to help us?\" Afterwards, Flydian, being just the messenger, wanders off into Athkatla to \"...stay and enjoy the ale of this marvelous place.\" The player's &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; is then updated under Animal Trouble in Trademeet.\"I have agreed to try and help Trademeet, which is southeast of Athkatla. They are suffering from a strange animal-based siege, and the local Druids are suspected. High Merchant Lord Logan Coprith may have information for me.\""}
